{"type":"message","id":"6142d845","parentId":"1f948152","timestamp":"2026-03-05T17:12:09.707Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 12:12 EST] Update and correct the `error-learning-loop` skill so that the learning retrieval system follows the proper architecture. \n\n \n\nThe current implementation of Step 8 builds a large consolidated report inside `.learnings/INDEX.md`. This is not ideal. The INDEX must act as a lightweight retrieval layer, not a verbose report. \n\n \n\nApply the following corrections. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\n1. Canonical location \n\n \n\nThe canonical learning directory must be: \n\n \n\n<workspace>/.learnings/ \n\n \n\nAll learning files must live there: \n\n \n\n<workspace>/.learnings/ \n\n ERRORS.md \n\n LEARNINGS.md \n\n INDEX.md \n\n REPORT.md (optional analytics) \n\n \n\nDo NOT place `.learnings` inside the skill directory anymore. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\n2. Convert INDEX.md into a minimal retrieval index \n\n \n\n`INDEX.md` must be lightweight and optimized for quick scanning. \n\n \n\nEach Pattern-Key entry must contain only: \n\n \n\nPattern-Key \n\nTags (3–6 short tags) \n\nRule (1 line prevention rule) \n\nPromoted (optional: AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md) \n\n \n\nExample entry: \n\n \n\n- Pattern-Key: validation|TOOL_FAILURE|openclaw_validator|timeout|excessive_workload \n\n Tags: validator, batching, timeout \n\n Rule: validators must process ≤5 items per batch \n\n Promoted: AGENTS.md \n\n \n\nEntries must be grouped under fixed domain sections: \n\n \n\ntools \n\nrequirements \n\nplanning \n\nmulti-agent \n\nvalidation \n\nother \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\n3. Move analytics to REPORT.md \n\n \n\nThe following sections must NOT exist in INDEX.md anymore: \n\n \n\nSummary \n\nPattern-Key tables \n\nTrend analysis \n\nNext steps \n\nMetrics \n\n \n\nThese must be written to: \n\n \n\n<workspace>/.learnings/REPORT.md \n\n \n\nREPORT.md may contain: \n\n \n\nincident metrics \n\nPattern-Key table \n\ntrend analysis \n\npromotion statistics \n\ntimestamps \n\n \n\nINDEX.md must stay small. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\n4. Deduplication rules \n\n \n\nDuring index rebuild: \n\n \n\n• Each Pattern-Key must appear exactly once globally. \n\n• If duplicates exist across sources: \n\n - keep the highest Count \n\n - keep the newest Last Seen \n\n - prefer guardrail rule text if promoted \n\n \n\nThe index must always be rebuilt from source files, not appended. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\n5. Update Step 8 in SKILL.md \n\n \n\nReplace the current Step 8 with: \n\n \n\nStep 8 — Update Learning Retrieval Index \n\n \n\nPurpose: \n\nMaintain a lightweight retrieval index so the agent can quickly find relevant Pattern-Keys without scanning full logs. \n\n \n\nActions: \n\n \n\n1. Read: \n\n <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md \n\n <workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md \n\n \n\n2. Extract all Pattern-Keys and derive: \n\n domain \n\n tags (3–6) \n\n rule (one line) \n\n promoted_to (AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md / none) \n\n \n\n3. Read: \n\n AGENTS.md \n\n TOOLS.md \n\nto detect promoted guardrails. \n\n \n\n4. Rebuild <workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md from scratch with fixed domain sections. \n\n \n\n5. Deduplicate Pattern-Keys globally. \n\n \n\n6. Ensure each entry contains at most 3–4 short lines. \n\n \n\n7. Write analytics and trend information to <workspace>/.learnings/REPORT.md. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\n6. Update update_index.py \n\n \n\nModify the script so that it: \n\n \n\n• rebuilds INDEX.md from scratch \n\n• enforces global Pattern-Key deduplication \n\n• writes analytics to REPORT.md \n\n• keeps INDEX entries minimal \n\n• supports the workspace path \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\n7. Rebuild the index now \n\n \n\nAfter updating the skill: \n\n \n\n• regenerate INDEX.md \n\n• regenerate REPORT.md \n\n• confirm that every Pattern-Key appears only once in INDEX.md \n\n• show the final INDEX.md"}],"timestamp":1772730729705}}
