al \n\n• supports the workspace path \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\n7. Rebuild the index now \n\n \n\nAfter updating the skill: \n\n \n\n• regenerate INDEX.md \n\n• regenerate REPORT.md \n\n• confirm that every Pattern-Key appears only once in INDEX.md \n\n• show the final INDEX.md"}],"timestamp":1772730732167}}
{"type":"message","id":"a8adcf01","parentId":"6566382b","timestamp":"2026-03-05T17:12:19.791Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to update the error-learning-loop skill according to the requirements. First, let's examine the current skill structure. I'll read the SKILL.md file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_AdNHu5Fgm8l5tbwEewBmWs7w","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":18581,"output":127,"cacheRead":1728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20436,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772730732169}}
{"type":"message","id":"abc20410","parentId":"a8adcf01","timestamp":"2026-03-05T17:12:19.819Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_AdNHu5Fgm8l5tbwEewBmWs7w","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: error-learning-loop\ndescription: Capture errors and near-misses from the current task and from sub-agent handoff reports, perform semantic deduplication of incidents, convert them into actionable learnings, and promote guardrails into AGENTS.md and TOOLS.md so the main agent avoids repeating mistakes. Supports manual invocation and end-of-task wrap-up.\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"category\":\"meta\",\"user-invocable\":true,\"command-dispatch\":\"model\",\"requires\":[\"workspace_write\"],\"optional_requires\":[\"sessions_history\",\"python\",\"bash\"],\"safety_level\":\"high\",\"wrap_up_enabled\":true}}\n---\n\n# error-learning-loop\n\n## Purpose\nCreate a structured feedback loop where the **main agent** learns from:\n- its own errors/near-misses, and\n- **sub-agent handoff reports** (Option 1: chat-based reporting),\nso repeated mistakes become guardrails in the workspace.\n\nThis skill is designed to be installed **only in the main agent workspace**.\n\n## Operating Modes\n### Manual Mode\nTriggered explicitly by the user.\n\nExample:\n\"Run the learning loop.\"\n\n### Wrap-Up Mode\nExecuted at the end of a task **ONLY IF** at least one incident occurred:\n- tool failure / exception / non-zero exit\n- user correction or new requirement that invalidates prior work\n- near-miss detected\n- sub-agent handoff indicates failure/partial or an incident\n\nIf no incident occurred, wrap-up should not execute.\n\n## Multi-agent data source (Option 1 — REQUIRED)\nThe main agent must collect incidents from sub-agents via a mandatory **Handoff Report** appended to every sub-agent’s final response.\n\n### Handoff Report (required format)\nSub-agents must end with:\n\nOutcome: success|partial|failure\nIncidents:\n- [TYPE=ERROR|NEAR_MISS|MISUNDERSTANDING|TOOL_FAILURE|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF; SEV=S1|S2|S3|S4] <symptom in 1 line> (evidence: <1 line, no secrets>)\nPattern hint: <optional, 1 line>\nPrevention rule: <optional, 1 line>\nFiles touched: <list or \"none\">\nNext action: <1 line>\n\n### Rules for sub-agents\n- Do NOT include secrets/tokens/credentials.\n- Keep evidence brief and concrete.\n- If there were no incidents: set Outcome=success and Incidents: none.\n\n## Core Concept: Semantic Dedupe\nTraditional dedupe compares exact strings.\nSemantic dedupe groups incidents by **meaning** into stable Pattern-Keys.\n\nExample (all same semantic class):\n- \"rg command not found\"\n- \"ripgrep missing\"\n- \"bash failed because rg not installed\"\n→ Pattern-Key: tools|TOOL_FAILURE|bash|missing_binary|binary_not_in_path\n\n## Pattern-Key\nFormat:\n<domain>|<type>|<tool>|<failure_class>|<root_cause_signature>\n\n## Hard Safety Rules (non-negotiable)\n1) Only read/write inside the current workspace and {baseDir}. Never edit outside.\n2) Never store secrets, tokens, passwords, keys, or private identifiers in learnings/logs.\n3) Do NOT install dependencies; do NOT auto-refactor code; do NOT change global OpenClaw config.\n4) Session/history access (if available) is allowed only when invoked and only for relevant sessions.\n5) Prefer minimal, auditable edits: small diffs, clear headings, and dated entries.\n6) If unsure whether something is sensitive: redact it.\n\n## Mitigations (to prevent common failure modes)\n### M1 — Prevent overfitting (bad generalizations)\nPromote a learning to AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md only if it is generalizable AND:\n- repeated Pattern-Key occurrences >= 2, OR\n- Severity is S1/S2 structural issue.\n\nOtherwise keep it in .learnings only.\n\n### M2 — Prevent logging noise\nKeep entries concise:\n- Symptoms: max 6 bullets\n- Root Cause: max 4 bullets\n- 1 learning sentence\n- 1 prevention rule\n- Preflight: 2–6 checks max\n\n### M3 — Prevent sensitive-data leakage\nBefore writing:\n- redact tokens/keys/passwords\n- replace emails/phones with placeholders\n- avoid customer names unless explicitly required\n\n### M4 — Prevent uncontrolled scope creep\nIf the fix requires new capability:\n- log as FEATURE_REQUEST\n- do not implement automatically\n\n## Inputs\nFrom current context:\n- Task goal (1–2 sentences)\n- Evidence: tool outputs, user corrections\n- Tags (mandatory):\n  - agent=<name>\n  - session=<id>\n  - task=<short>\n\nFrom sub-agents (required):\n- Handoff Report blocks (as provided in chat)\n\nOptional (only for dedupe confirmation):\n- Minimal relevant session history snippets (if tools exist)\n\n## Outputs\nAlways update at least one:\n- {baseDir}/.learnings/ERRORS.md\n- {baseDir}/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\n\nSometimes:\n- {baseDir}/.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\n- Workspace patches (minimal):\n  - {workspace}/AGENTS.md\n  - {workspace}/TOOLS.md\n\n**New mandatory output** (added in this version):\n- {baseDir}/.learnings/INDEX.md – consolidated index of Pattern‑Keys, guardrails, and trends. Must be updated and deduplicated after every learning‑loop run.\n\n## Step-by-step instructions\n\n### Step 0 — Ensure learning store exists\nCreate if missing:\n- {baseDir}/.learnings/ERRORS.md\n- {baseDir}/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\n- {baseDir}/.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\n\n### Step 1 — Detect incidents (wrap-up gate)\nIf running wrap-up:\n- Confirm at least one incident occurred (from main execution or sub-agent handoff).\n- If none: STOP. No logging.\n\n### Step 2 — Collect evidence (main + sub-agents)\nFrom the main task:\n- what we attempted\n- what happened\n- root cause hypothesis\n- what fixed it\n\nFrom sub-agents:\n- parse each Handoff Report\n- extract Outcome + each Incident line\n- discard/redact anything sensitive\n\n### Step 3 — Generate Semantic Pattern-Key\nFor each incident:\n- normalize into a stable Pattern-Key using:\n  domain + type + tool (if any) + failure_class + root_cause_signature\n\n### Step 4 — Semantic Deduplication\nCompare against existing Pattern-Keys in:\n- .learnings/ERRORS.md\n- .learnings/LEARNINGS.md\n\nIf a semantically matching Pattern-Key exists:\n- increment Count\n- update Last Seen\n- append an Occurrence entry\n\nElse:\n- create a new entry\n\n### Step 5 — Extract Learning\nFor each (new or repeated) Pattern-Key:\n- 1 learning statement\n- 1 prevention rule\n- optional preflight checklist (tools-related only)\n\n### Step 6 — Promotion\nApply Mitigation M1.\nPromote:\n- workflow/coordination guardrails → AGENTS.md (\"## Guardrails (Auto-learnings)\")\n- tool-specific guardrails → TOOLS.md (\"## Tool Guardrails\")\n\nEdits must include:\n- date\n- Pattern-Key\n- rule (+ preflight if any)\n\n### Step 7 — Close\nAdd an applied note:\nApplied: yes/no\nPromoted to: AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md / none\nNext time: expected behavior\n\n### Step 8 — Update Consolidated Index\n**Purpose**: Ensure `.learnings/INDEX.md` reflects the current state of all incidents, learnings, and guardrails, with each Pattern‑Key appearing exactly once (deduplicated).\n\n**Actions**:\n1. Read the updated `.learnings/ERRORS.md` and `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md`.\n2. Extract all Pattern‑Keys, their metadata (type, severity, count, first/last seen, status), learning statements, prevention rules, and promotion status.\n3. Read `AGENTS.md` and `TOOLS.md` to identify which guardrails have been promoted (look for sections “Guardrails (Auto‑learnings)” and “Tool Guardrails”).\n4. Reconstruct the consolidated index with the following sections:\n   - **Summary** (total incidents, unique Pattern‑Keys, guardrails promoted, etc.)\n   - **Pattern‑Key Index** (table with Pattern‑Key, type, severity, count, first/last seen, status, learning, promoted‑to)\n   - **Guardrails Promoted** (list of rules already in AGENTS.md/TOOLS.md)\n   - **Trend Analysis** (domain distribution, severity, promotion rate)\n   - **Next Steps** (monitoring, enforcement, index‑update process)\n   - **File Reference** (links to ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, FEATURE_REQUESTS.md)\n5. **Deduplication**: Ensure each Pattern‑Key appears only once in the index. If duplicate entries are found (same Pattern‑Key with different counts or status), merge them, keeping the latest `Last Seen` and the highest `Count`.\n6. Write the updated index to `.learnings/INDEX.md`, updating the “Last Updated” timestamp.\n7. If `FEATURE_REQUESTS.md` exists, include its summary in the index.\n\n**Note**: This step must be executed **after** any changes to ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, AGENTS.md, or TOOLS.md. It guarantees that INDEX.md is always a single source of truth for the learning‑loop state.\n\n## Example usage\nManual:\n\"Run the learning loop using the sub-agent handoff reports from this task.\"\nWrap-up:\nIf incidents occurred, run Steps 2–8; otherwise skip.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772730739815}}
