{"type":"message","id":"ca93f3c2","parentId":"e95c7b83","timestamp":"2026-03-05T17:28:14.712Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Continuando con la actualización del skill `error-learning-loop`. Ya modifiqué Step 8 en SKILL.md, ahora necesito reescribir completamente `update_index.py` para que genere dos archivos: un INDEX.md minimalista y un REPORT.md con analytics. Además, debo ajustar el sistema para usar el workspace path.\n\nPrimero, voy a leer el contenido actual de .learnings/INDEX.md para ver cómo está estructurado actualmente, y luego crearé el nuevo script. También necesito verificar si existe .learnings/REPORT.md, probablemente no.\n\nAhora crearé una nueva versión del script `update_index.py` que cumpla con los requisitos:\n\n1. **INDEX.md minimalista**: con secciones fijas (tools, requirements, planning, multi-agent, validation, other), cada entrada con solo Pattern-Key, Tags, Rule, Promoted.\n\n2. **REPORT.md con analytics**: tendrá Summary, Pattern-Key table, trend analysis, promotion statistics, timestamps.\n\n3. **Deduplicación global**: cada Pattern-Key aparece solo una vez.\n\n4. **Extraer dominio**: del Pattern-Key (primera parte antes del primer '|').\n\n5. **Generar tags**: 3-6 tags cortos basados en el Pattern-Key y otros metadatos.\n\n6. **Leer AGENTS.md y TOOLS.md** para detectar guardrails promovidos.\n\nPrimero, examinaré los Pattern-Keys existentes: ya los tengo de ERRORS.md y LEARNINGS.md. Los tres existentes son:\n\n1. validation|TOOL_FAILURE|openclaw_validator|timeout|excessive_workload\n2. model|ERROR|deepseek_reasoner|missing_field|reasoning_content_required\n3. multi_agent|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF|openclaw_subagent|missing_report|handoff_contract_not_enforced\n\nSus dominios: validation, model, multi_agent.\n\nLas secciones fijas son: tools, requirements, planning, multi-agent, validation, other.\n\nMapeo: \n- validation → sección validation\n- multi_agent → sección multi-agent  \n- model → ¿tools? Tal vez \"tools\" (porque es sobre modelo). Pero modelo es más sobre herramientas de modelo. O podría ir en \"other\". Seguiré el dominio.\n\nCrearé el nuevo script ahora. Primero leeré los archivos necesarios para entender mejor la estructura.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_thqz9QXe1moPmldKad7In1pg","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/.learnings/INDEX.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":18522,"output":1126,"cacheRead":20288,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39936,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772731667348}}
{"type":"message","id":"6133183f","parentId":"ca93f3c2","timestamp":"2026-03-05T17:28:14.734Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_thqz9QXe1moPmldKad7In1pg","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LEARNING INDEX – Consolidated View of Incidents, Learnings & Guardrails\n\n*Generated by error‑learning‑loop. Updated: 2026-03-04T19:12:39*\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Summary\n\n| Metric | Count |\n|--------|-------|\n| **Total incidents logged** | 3 |\n| **Unique Pattern‑Keys** | 3 |\n| **Active incidents** | 3 |\n| **Learnings extracted** | 3 |\n| **Guardrails promoted** | 3 |\n| **Feature requests** | 0 |\n\n**Last refresh**: 2026-03-04T19:12:39 (America/Panama)\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 Pattern‑Key Index\n\n| Pattern‑Key | Type | Severity | Count | First Seen | Last Seen | Status | Learning | Promoted To |\n|-------------|------|----------|-------|------------|-----------|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `model|ERROR|deepseek_reasoner|missing_field|reasoning_content_required` | ERROR | S2 | 1 | 2026-03-02 | 2026-03-02 | active | DeepSeek’s reasoning mode may require a `reasoning_content` field even when not explicitly enabled, causing sub‑agent failures on long tasks. | TOOLS.md (Tool Guardrails) |\n| `multi_agent|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF|openclaw_subagent|missing_report|handoff_contract_not_enforced` | MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF | S3 | 1 | 2026-03-04 | 2026-03-04 | active | Without enforced handoff reporting, incidents from sub‑agents are lost, breaking the error‑learning loop. | AGENTS.md (Guardrails section) |\n| `validation|TOOL_FAILURE|openclaw_validator|timeout|excessive_workload` | TOOL_FAILURE | S2 | 1 | 2026-03-02 | 2026-03-02 | active | Validators tend to timeout when tasked with too many items (≥6) within a 10‑minute window. Splitting work into smaller batches improves completion reliability. | AGENTS.md (Guardrails section) |\n\n*Click on a Pattern‑Key to jump to its detailed entry in [ERRORS.md](./ERRORS.md) or [LEARNINGS.md](./LEARNINGS.md).*\n\n---\n\n## 🛡️ Guardrails Promoted\n\n### In AGENTS.md ([view](../AGENTS.md#guardrails-auto-learnings))\n1. **Validator Batch Size**  \n   *Pattern‑Key*: `validation|TOOL_FAILURE|openclaw_validator|timeout|excessive_workload`\n1. **Handoff Report Enforcement**  \n   *Pattern‑Key*: `multi_agent|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF|openclaw_subagent|missing_report|handoff_contract_not_enforced`\n\n### In TOOLS.md ([view](../TOOLS.md#tool-guardrails))\n1. **DeepSeek Reasoning Mode**  \n   *Pattern‑Key*: `model|ERROR|deepseek_reasoner|missing_field|reasoning_content_required`\n\n---\n\n## 📈 Trend Analysis\n\n- **Most frequent domain**: validation (1 incidents).\n- **Domain distribution**: validation: 1, model: 1, multi_agent: 1.\n- **Severity distribution**: S2: 2, S3: 1.\n- **Promotion rate**: 3/3 (100.0% of Pattern‑Keys have guardrails promoted).\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Next Steps\n\n1. **Monitor validator timeouts** – After implementing batch splitting, verify that validators complete within allotted time.\n2. **Enforce Handoff Reports** – Ensure future sub‑agents include the mandatory report block.\n3. **Update INDEX.md** – Refresh this file after each learning‑loop run (manual or wrap‑up).\n4. **Feature‑request tracking** – As capability gaps are identified, add them to `FEATURE_REQUESTS.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 📁 File Reference\n\n| File | Purpose | Last Updated |\n|------|---------|--------------|\n| [ERRORS.md](./ERRORS.md) | Deduplicated incident log with root‑cause analysis. | 2026-03-04T19:12:39 |\n| [LEARNINGS.md](./LEARNINGS.md) | Actionable learnings, prevention rules, preflight checks. | 2026-03-04T19:12:39 |\n| [FEATURE_REQUESTS.md](./FEATURE_REQUESTS.md) | Capability gaps identified from incidents. | 2026-03-04T19:12:39 |\n| **INDEX.md** (this file) | Consolidated view, guardrail inventory, trend analysis. | 2026-03-04T19:12:39 |\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Update Process\n\nThis index is **automatically reconstructed** by the `update_index.py` script after each learning‑loop run.  \nTo refresh manually:\n\n1. Run `python3 skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py`.\n2. Commit the updated index.\n\n*For automated refresh, the error‑learning‑loop skill now includes Step 8, which calls this script.*\n\n---\n\n**Maintained by**: main agent (session `workspace`)  \n**Skill**: `error‑learning‑loop`"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772731694727}}
{"type":"message","id":"bc04da77","parentId":"6133183f","timestamp":"2026-03-05T17:31:04.049Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ahora crearé el nuevo script. Primero, verificaré si existe un archivo de reporte. Luego, escribiré el nuevo script que genera ambos archivos. También necesito modificar la ruta baseDir para que apunte al workspace (no al directorio actual). El script debe aceptar un argumento baseDir opcional, pero por defecto debe usar el workspace del entorno OpenClaw. Sin embargo, el script actual asume el directorio actual. Podemos mantenerlo flexible pero cuando se llame desde el skill, se pasará el workspace.\n\nAhora crearé el nuevo script con las funciones necesarias:\n\n1. parse_errors_md y parse_learnings_md para extraer Pattern-Keys, reglas, etc.\n2. extract_guardrails para detectar promociones.\n3. classify_domain: mapear dominio a sección fija.\n4. generate_tags: crear tags cortos.\n5. generate_index: construir INDEX.md minimalista.\n6. generate_report: construir REPORT.md con analytics.\n\nTambién necesito manejar deduplicación: cada Pattern-Key solo una vez, eligiendo la entrada con mayor count y más reciente.\n\nComencemos escribiendo el nuevo script. Primero, haré una copia de seguridad del script actual, luego lo reemplazaré. Pero primero, voy a crear el nuevo script en un archivo temporal y luego lo moveré. Usaré edit para modificar el archivo existente. Primero leeré todo el contenido actual y luego lo reemplazaré completamente.\n\nPero antes de editar, necesito entender bien los datos de entrada. Voy a examinar la estructura de ERRORS.md y LEARNINGS.md nuevamente para ver los campos disponibles. Ya los leí antes. Extraeré la regla de prevención de LEARNINGS.md, que está en \"Prevention Rule\". También necesito tags: puedo generar tags del Pattern-Key: por ejemplo, dividir por '|' y usar las partes relevantes, también usar el tipo y dominio.\n\nAhora editaré el script. Será largo, así que lo haré paso a paso. Primero, abriré el archivo para editarlo completamente. Usaré edit con oldText como el contenido completo y newText como el nuevo script.\n\nPero es mejor escribir el nuevo script en un archivo separado y luego reemplazar, para evitar errores. Usaré write para crear un archivo temporal y luego edit para reemplazar. Sin embargo, el script actual está en `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py`. Lo editaré directamente.\n\nPrimero, crearé el contenido del nuevo script.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_SxgoHfFgGjoIXC4lXdZ2jc3m","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nupdate_index.py – Rebuild INDEX.md (lightweight retrieval index) and REPORT.md (analytics)\nfrom ERRORS.md, LEARNINGS.md, AGENTS.md, and TOOLS.md.\n\nINDEX.md is minimal, grouped by fixed domain sections, each entry 3–4 lines.\nREPORT.md contains summary, tables, trends, and promotion stats.\n\nPattern‑Keys are deduplicated globally (keep highest count, newest last seen).\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\n# Fixed domain sections (in order)\nDOMAIN_SECTIONS = [\n    \"tools\",\n    \"requirements\",\n    \"planning\",\n    \"multi-agent\",\n    \"validation\",\n    \"other\"\n]\n\ndef classify_domain(pattern_key):\n    \"\"\"Map Pattern‑Key's first segment to a fixed domain section.\"\"\"\n    if '|' not in pattern_key:\n        return \"other\"\n    first = pattern_key.split('|')[0].strip().lower()\n    # Direct mapping for known domains\n    if first == \"validation\":\n        return \"validation\"\n    if first == \"multi_agent\":\n        return \"multi-agent\"\n    if first in (\"model\", \"tool\", \"tools\", \"exec\", \"browser\", \"web\", \"tts\", \"image\", \"pdf\"):\n        return \"tools\"\n    if first in (\"requirement\", \"requirements\", \"spec\", \"specification\"):\n        return \"requirements\"\n    if first in (\"plan\", \"planning\", \"strategy\", \"design\"):\n        return \"planning\"\n    return \"other\"\n\ndef generate_tags(pattern_key, learning_entry):\n    \"\"\"Produce 3–6 short tags from Pattern‑Key and metadata.\"\"\"\n    parts = [p.strip() for p in pattern_key.split('|') if p.strip()]\n    tags = set()\n    # Add domain (first part)\n    if len(parts) > 0:\n        domain = parts[0].lower()\n        tags.add(domain)\n    # Add type (second part) if present\n    if len(parts) > 1:\n        typ = parts[1].lower()\n        if typ not in (\"error\", \"tool_failure\", \"multi_agent_handoff\"):  # too generic\n            tags.add(typ.replace('_', ' '))\n    # Add tool (third part) if present and not generic\n    if len(parts) > 2:\n        tool = parts[2].lower()\n        if tool not in (\"openclaw\", \"unknown\", \"none\"):\n            tags.add(tool.replace('_', ' '))\n    # Add failure class (fourth part) if present\n    if len(parts) > 3:\n        fail = parts[3].lower()\n        if fail not in (\"timeout\", \"missing_field\", \"missing_report\"):\n            tags.add(fail.replace('_', ' '))\n    # Ensure at least 3 tags, fallback to generic\n    while len(tags) < 3:\n        tags.add(\"incident\")\n        tags.add(\"learning\")\n        tags.add(\"guardrail\")\n    # Keep only first 6\n    return list(sorted(tags))[:6]\n\ndef parse_errors_md(path):\n    \"\"\"Extract Pattern‑Keys from ERRORS.md entries.\"\"\"\n    with open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    \n    pattern = r'### Pattern-Key:\\s*(.+?)\\n(.*?)(?=\\n### Pattern-Key:|\\Z)'\n    matches = re.findall(pattern, content, re.DOTALL)\n    keys = []\n    for pk_line, block in matches:\n        pk = pk_line.strip().strip(':')\n        data = {'pattern_key': pk}\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in block.split('\\n') if l.strip()]\n        for line in lines:\n            if line.startswith('- **First Occurrence**:'):\n                match = re.search(r'(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})', line)\n                if match:\n                    data['first_seen'] = match.group(1)\n            elif line.startswith('- **Latest Occurrence**:'):\n                match = re.search(r'(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})', line)\n                if match:\n                    data['last_seen'] = match.group(1)\n            elif line.startswith('- **Count**:'):\n                match = re.search(r'(\\d+)', line)\n                if match:\n                    data['count'] = int(match.group(1))\n            elif line.startswith('- **Type**:'):\n                data['type'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\n            elif line.startswith('- **Severity**:'):\n                data['severity'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\n        data.setdefault('count', 1)\n        data.setdefault('first_seen', 'unknown')\n        data.setdefault('last_seen', 'unknown')\n        data.setdefault('type', 'unknown')\n        data.setdefault('severity', 'unknown')\n        data['status'] = 'active'\n        keys.append(data)\n    return keys\n\ndef parse_learnings_md(path):\n    \"\"\"Extract learning statements, prevention rules, and promotion status from LEARNINGS.md.\"\"\"\n    with open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    \n    pattern = r'### Pattern-Key:\\s*(.+?)\\n(.*?)(?=\\n### Pattern-Key:|\\Z)'\n    matches = re.findall(pattern, content, re.DOTALL)\n    learnings = {}\n    for pk_line, block in matches:\n        pk = pk_line.strip().strip(':')\n        data = {'learning': '', 'prevention_rule': '', 'preflight': '', 'promoted_to': ''}\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in block.split('\\n') if l.strip()]\n        for line in lines:\n            if line.startswith('- **Learning Statement**:'):\n                data['learning'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\n            elif line.startswith('- **Prevention Rule**:'):\n                data['prevention_rule'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\n            elif line.startswith('- **Preflight Checks**:'):\n                data['preflight'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\n            elif line.startswith('- **Promoted To**:'):\n                data['promoted_to'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\n        learnings[pk] = data\n    return learnings\n\ndef extract_guardrails(agents_path, tools_path):\n    \"\"\"Detect which Pattern‑Keys have guardrails in AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md.\"\"\"\n    promoted = set()\n    def search_in_file(path):\n        try:\n            with open(path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                content = f.read()\n        except FileNotFoundError:\n            return set()\n        # Look for Pattern‑Key mentions in guardrail sections\n        # The guardrail entries have \"Pattern‑Key:\" lines\n        pk_matches = re.findall(r'Pattern[\\-‑]Key:\\s*([^\\s]+)', content)\n        return set(pk_matches)\n    promoted.update(search_in_file(agents_path))\n    promoted.update(search_in_file(tools_path))\n    return promoted\n\ndef deduplicate_entries(errors_keys, learnings):\n    \"\"\"\n    Merge duplicate Pattern‑Keys across sources.\n    Returns a dict {pattern_key: merged_data}.\n    \"\"\"\n    merged = {}\n    for k in errors_keys:\n        pk = k['pattern_key']\n        if pk not in merged:\n            merged[pk] = {\n                'pattern_key': pk,\n                'count': k['count'],\n                'first_seen': k['first_seen'],\n                'last_seen': k['last_seen'],\n                'type': k['type'],\n                'severity': k['severity'],\n                'status': k['status']\n            }\n        else:\n            # Keep highest count\n            if k['count'] > merged[pk]['count']:\n                merged[pk]['count'] = k['count']\n            # Keep newest last_seen (string comparison works for YYYY-MM-DD)\n            if k['last_seen'] > merged[pk]['last_seen']:\n                merged[pk]['last_seen'] = k['last_seen']\n            # Prefer non‑unknown type/severity\n            if k['type'] != 'unknown':\n                merged[pk]['type'] = k['type']\n            if k['severity'] != 'unknown':\n                merged[pk]['severity'] = k['severity']\n    # Add learning data\n    for pk, data in learnings.items():\n        if pk in merged:\n            merged[pk]['learning'] = data['learning']\n            merged[pk]['prevention_rule'] = data['prevention_rule']\n            merged[pk]['preflight'] = data['preflight']\n            merged[pk]['promoted_to'] = data['promoted_to']\n        else:\n            # Learning without error entry? Should not happen, but create stub.\n            merged[pk] = {\n                'pattern_key': pk,\n                'count': 0,\n                'first_seen': 'unknown',\n                'last_seen': 'unknown',\n                'type': 'unknown',\n                'severity': 'unknown',\n                'status': 'active',\n                'learning': data['learning'],\n                'prevention_rule': data['prevention_rule'],\n                'preflight': data['preflight'],\n                'promoted_to': data['promoted_to']\n            }\n    return merged\n\ndef generate_index(merged_entries, promoted_set, base_dir):\n    \"\"\"Create lightweight INDEX.md grouped by fixed domain sections.\"\"\"\n    now = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')\n    # Group by domain section\n    sections = {sec: [] for sec in DOMAIN_SECTIONS}\n    for pk, data in sorted(merged_entries.items(), key=lambda x: x[0]):\n        domain = classify_domain(pk)\n        section = domain if domain in DOMAIN_SECTIONS else \"other\"\n        tags = generate_tags(pk, data)\n        rule = data.get('prevention_rule', '').strip()\n        if not rule:\n            rule = data.get('learning', '').strip()\n            if rule:\n                rule = rule[:120] + \"…\" if len(rule) > 120 else rule\n        promoted = \"\"\n        if pk in promoted_set:\n            promoted = \"AGENTS.md\" if \"AGENTS.md\" in data.get('promoted_to', '') else \"TOOLS.md\"\n        entry_lines = [\n            f\"- Pattern-Key: {pk}\",\n            f\"  Tags: {', '.join(tags)}\",\n            f\"  Rule: {rule}\" if rule else \"\",\n            f\"  Promoted: {promoted}\" if promoted else \"\"\n        ]\n        entry = \"\\n\".join([l for l in entry_lines if l])\n        sections[section].append(entry)\n    \n    # Build content\n    lines = [\n        \"# INDEX.md – Lightweight Retrieval Index\",\n        \"\",\n        \"*Generated by error‑learning‑loop. Updated: \" + now + \"*\",\n        \"\",\n        \"---\",\n        \"\"\n    ]\n    for section in DOMAIN_SECTIONS:\n        entries = sections[section]\n        if not entries:\n            continue\n        lines.append(f\"## {section.title()}\")\n        lines.append(\"\")\n        lines.extend(entries)\n        lines.append(\"\")\n    lines.append(\"---\")\n    lines.append(\"\")\n    lines.append(\"*Sections: \" + \", \".join(DOMAIN_SECTIONS) + \"*\")\n    lines.append(\"\")\n    lines.append(\"**Purpose**: Quick scanning of Pattern‑Keys, tags, rules, and promotion status.\")\n    lines.append(\"For detailed analytics, see [REPORT.md](./REPORT.md).\")\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\ndef generate_report(merged_entries, promoted_set, base_dir):\n    \"\"\"Create REPORT.md with analytics, tables, and trends.\"\"\"\n    now = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')\n    total_incidents = sum(d['count'] for d in merged_entries.values())\n    unique_pks = len(merged_entries)\n    promoted_count = len(promoted_set)\n    \n    # Domain distribution\n    domains = defaultdict(int)\n    for pk in merged_entries:\n        dom = classify_domain(pk)\n        domains[dom] += 1\n    \n    # Severity distribution\n    severities = defaultdict(int)\n    for d in merged_entries.values():\n        sev = d.get('severity', 'unknown')\n        severities[sev] += 1\n    \n    # Type distribution\n    types = defaultdict(int)\n    for d in merged_entries.values():\n        typ = d.get('type', 'unknown')\n        types[typ] += 1\n    \n    # Pattern‑Key table rows\n    table_rows = []\n    for pk, data in sorted(merged_entries.items(), key=lambda x: x[0]):\n        promoted = \"✅\" if pk in promoted_set else \"❌\"\n        table_rows.append(\n            f\"| `{pk}` | {data.get('type', '?')} | {data.get('severity', '?')} | \"\n            f\"{data['count']} | {data.get('first_seen', '?')} | {data.get('last_seen', '?')} | \"\n            f\"{promoted} |\"\n        )\n    \n    content = f'''# REPORT.md – Learning‑Loop Analytics\n\n*Generated by error‑learning‑loop. Updated: {now}*\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Summary\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| **Total incidents logged** | {total_incidents} |\n| **Unique Pattern‑Keys** | {unique_pks} |\n| **Pattern‑Keys with guardrails promoted** | {promoted_count} |\n| **Promotion rate** | {promoted_count}/{unique_pks} ({promoted_count/unique_pks*100 if unique_pks else 0:.1f}%) |\n| **Last refresh** | {now} |\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 Pattern‑Key Table\n\n| Pattern‑Key | Type | Severity | Count | First Seen | Last Seen | Promoted |\n|-------------|------|----------|-------|------------|-----------|----------|\n{\"\\n\".join(table_rows)}\n\n---\n\n## 📈 Trend Analysis\n\n### Domain Distribution\n{chr(10).join(f\"- **{dom}**: {cnt} Pattern‑Key(s)\" for dom, cnt in sorted(domains.items()))}\n\n### Severity Distribution\n{chr(10).join(f\"- **{sev}**: {cnt} Pattern‑Key(s)\" for sev, cnt in sorted(severities.items()))}\n\n### Type Distribution\n{chr(10).join(f\"- **{typ}**: {cnt} Pattern‑Key(s)\" for typ, cnt in sorted(types.items()))}\n\n---\n\n## 🛡️ Promotion Statistics\n\n- **Promoted to AGENTS.md**: {sum(1 for pk in promoted_set if \"AGENTS.md\" in merged_entries.get(pk, {}).get('promoted_to', ''))}\n- **Promoted to TOOLS.md**: {sum(1 for pk in promoted_set if \"TOOLS.md\" in merged_entries.get(pk, {}).get('promoted_to', ''))}\n- **Not promoted**: {unique_pks - promoted_count}\n\n---\n\n## 📁 File Reference\n\n| File | Purpose | Last Updated |\n|------|---------|--------------|\n| [ERRORS.md](./ERRORS.md) | Deduplicated incident log with root‑cause analysis. | {now} |\n| [LEARNINGS.md](./LEARNINGS.md) | Actionable learnings, prevention rules, preflight checks. | {now} |\n| [FEATURE_REQUESTS.md](./FEATURE_REQUESTS.md) | Capability gaps identified from incidents. | {now} |\n| [INDEX.md](./INDEX.md) | Lightweight retrieval index (this file’s companion). | {now} |\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Update Process\n\nThis report is regenerated each time `update_index.py` runs, usually after a learning‑loop execution.\n\n**Script location**: `{Path(__file__).relative_to(base_dir)}`\n\n**Manual refresh**:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\npython3 {Path(__file__).relative_to(base_dir)}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n**Maintained by**: main agent  \n**Skill**: `error‑learning‑loop`'''\n    return content\n\ndef main():\n    if len(sys.argv) > 1:\n        base_dir = Path(sys.argv[1])\n    else:\n        base_dir = Path.cwd()\n    \n    learnings_dir = base_dir / '.learnings'\n    if not learnings_dir.exists():\n        print(f\"ERROR: .learnings directory not found in {base_dir}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    errors_path = learnings_dir / 'ERRORS.md'\n    learnings_path = learnings_dir / 'LEARNINGS.md'\n    agents_path = base_dir / 'AGENTS.md'\n    tools_path = base_dir / 'TOOLS.md'\n    \n    if not errors_path.exists():\n        print(f\"ERROR: {errors_path} not found\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    if not learnings_path.exists():\n        print(f\"ERROR: {learnings_path} not found\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    errors_keys = parse_errors_md(errors_path)\n    learnings_dict = parse_learnings_md(learnings_path)\n    promoted_set = extract_guardrails(agents_path, tools_path)\n    merged = deduplicate_entries(errors_keys, learnings_dict)\n    \n    # Generate new files\n    index_content = generate_index(merged, promoted_set, base_dir)\n    report_content = generate_report(merged, promoted_set, base_dir)\n    \n    index_path = learnings_dir / 'INDEX.md'\n    with open(index_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        f.write(index_content)\n    print(f\"✅ INDEX.md updated at {index_path}\")\n    \n    report_path = learnings_dir / 'REPORT.md'\n    with open(report_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        f.write(report_content)\n    print(f\"✅ REPORT.md updated at {report_path}\")\n    \n    # Verify each Pattern‑Key appears only once in INDEX.md\n    with open(index_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        index_text = f.read()\n    pk_matches = re.findall(r'Pattern-Key: ([^\\n]+)', index_text)\n    if len(pk_matches) != len(set(pk_matches)):\n        print(\"⚠️  WARNING: Duplicate Pattern‑Keys found in INDEX.md\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"✓ Each Pattern‑Key appears exactly once ({len(pk_matches)} total).\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":1786,"output":5342,"cacheRead":38784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45912,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772731694735}}
