{"type":"message","id":"fd666605","parentId":"f089c020","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:03:12.911Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_Bjse8U4zujND7VNAGPGOqwqX","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# INDEX.md – Lightweight Retrieval Index\n\n*Generated by error‑learning‑loop. Updated: 2026-03-05 13:03:06*\n\n---\n\n## tools\n\n- Pattern-Key: model|ERROR|deepseek_reasoner|missing_field|reasoning_content_required\n  Tags: deepseek, model, model-error, reasoning\n  Rule: For long multi‑step tasks, avoid DeepSeek reasoning mode; use standard completion mode or a different model.\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n\n## multi-agent\n\n- Pattern-Key: multi_agent|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF|openclaw_subagent|missing_report|handoff_contract_not_enforced\n  Tags: multi-agent, multi_agent, not, subagent\n  Rule: Every sub‑agent must end its final response with a structured Handoff Report (Outcome + Incidents).\n  Promoted: AGENTS.md\n\n## validation\n\n- Pattern-Key: validation|TOOL_FAILURE|openclaw_validator|timeout|excessive_workload\n  Tags: items, tool-failure, validation, validator\n  Rule: Never assign more than 5 items to a single validator agent. If more items need validation, spawn multiple validators each with a subset.\n  Promoted: AGENTS.md\n\n---\n\n*Sections: tools, requirements, planning, multi-agent, validation, other*\n\n[3 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772733792904}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd2a349c","parentId":"fd666605","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:03:32.239Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesante. Los tags han cambiado, pero veo algunos problemas:\n\n1. Para \"multi_agent\": aparece \"multi-agent\" y \"multi_agent\". Además \"not\" parece ser una palabra extraída de \"handoff_contract_not_enforced\". \"not\" es una palabra genérica y no debería estar allí. Necesito ajustar la función para excluir palabras como \"not\". También \"subagent\" está bien.\n\n2. Para \"validation\": \"items\" viene de la regla, está bien. \"tool-failure\" está bien. \"validation\" y \"validator\" están bien.\n\n3. Para \"tools\": \"deepseek\", \"model\", \"model-error\", \"reasoning\". Está bien.\n\nNecesito mejorar la exclusión de palabras genéricas. Voy a agregar más palabras genéricas a excluir: \"not\", \"and\", \"or\", \"the\", \"a\", \"an\", \"is\", \"are\", \"was\", \"were\", \"be\", \"been\", \"being\", \"have\", \"has\", \"had\", \"do\", \"does\", \"did\", \"will\", \"would\", \"should\", \"could\", \"may\", \"might\", \"must\", \"can\", \"cannot\", \"etc.\"\n\nPero mejor, en lugar de excluir palabras específicas, podríamos excluir palabras demasiado cortas (menos de 3 letras) y palabras comunes en inglés. Sin embargo, \"not\" tiene 3 letras. Podemos excluir una lista de stop words.\n\nModificaré la función `add_meaningful` para excluir una lista más completa de stop words. También evitaré añadir tags que sean solo números o muy cortos.\n\nVoy a editar nuevamente `generate_tags`. Primero veo el código actual.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_uoEbmI5l5iTyIlK4lqlqI77y","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py","offset":50,"limit":80}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":439,"output":861,"cacheRead":67520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68820,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772733792915}}
{"type":"message","id":"62843699","parentId":"bd2a349c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:03:32.265Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_uoEbmI5l5iTyIlK4lqlqI77y","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    \n    # Helper to split snake_case into words and add meaningful ones\n    def add_meaningful(text, exclude_generic=True):\n        words = text.lower().split('_')\n        generic = {\"error\", \"failure\", \"handoff\", \"missing\", \"required\", \"content\", \n                   \"field\", \"report\", \"contract\", \"enforced\", \"excessive\", \"workload\",\n                   \"timeout\", \"unknown\", \"none\", \"openclaw\"}\n        for w in words:\n            if not w or len(w) < 2:\n                continue\n            if exclude_generic and w in generic:\n                continue\n            tags.add(w)\n    \n    # Domain (first part) - always add\n    if len(parts) > 0:\n        domain = parts[0].lower()\n        if domain not in (\"unknown\", \"none\"):\n            tags.add(domain)\n    \n    # Type (second part) - map to more descriptive tags\n    if len(parts) > 1:\n        typ = parts[1].lower()\n        # Map generic types to more specific concepts\n        type_map = {\n            \"error\": \"model-error\",\n            \"tool_failure\": \"tool-failure\",\n            \"multi_agent_handoff\": \"multi-agent\"\n        }\n        if typ in type_map:\n            tags.add(type_map[typ])\n        else:\n            add_meaningful(typ, exclude_generic=True)\n    \n    # Tool (third part) - extract tool name, strip prefixes\n    if len(parts) > 2:\n        tool = parts[2].lower()\n        if tool.startswith(\"openclaw_\"):\n            tool = tool.replace(\"openclaw_\", \"\")\n        if tool.endswith(\"_reasoner\"):\n            tool = tool.replace(\"_reasoner\", \"\")\n        if tool.endswith(\"_validator\"):\n            tool = tool.replace(\"_validator\", \"\")\n        if tool.endswith(\"_subagent\"):\n            tool = tool.replace(\"_subagent\", \"\")\n        if tool not in (\"\", \"unknown\", \"none\"):\n            tags.add(tool)\n    \n    # Failure class (fourth part) - key failure mode\n    if len(parts) > 3:\n        fail = parts[3].lower()\n        # Add as tag, but split if snake_case\n        add_meaningful(fail, exclude_generic=True)\n    \n    # Root cause signature (fifth part) - extract keywords\n    if len(parts) > 4:\n        root = parts[4].lower()\n        add_meaningful(root, exclude_generic=True)\n    \n    # Add contextual tags from prevention rule if we have too few\n    rule = learning_entry.get('prevention_rule', '').lower()\n    if rule and len(tags) < 4:\n        # Extract key words from rule\n        keywords = [\"batch\", \"split\", \"limit\", \"timeout\", \"handoff\", \"report\",\n                    \"reasoning\", \"mode\", \"sub-agent\", \"validator\", \"items\", \"count\"]\n        for kw in keywords:\n            if kw in rule:\n                tags.add(kw)\n    \n    # Ensure we have at least 3 tags, but avoid generic filler\n    # If still too few, add domain-specific fallbacks\n    if len(tags) < 3:\n        # Add from predefined contextual set based on domain\n        domain = parts[0].lower() if parts else \"\"\n        if domain == \"validation\":\n            tags.update([\"batching\", \"timeout\", \"workload\"])\n        elif domain == \"multi_agent\":\n            tags.update([\"delegation\", \"handoff\", \"reporting\"])\n        elif domain == \"model\":\n            tags.update([\"api\", \"reasoning\", \"configuration\"])\n\n[366 more lines in file. Use offset=130 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772733812253}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d9568eb","parentId":"62843699","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:04:17.941Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Veo que el problema es que `add_meaningful` divide por '_' y añade cada palabra, pero \"handoff_contract_not_enforced\" se divide en [\"handoff\", \"contract\", \"not\", \"enforced\"]. Luego \"not\" se añade porque no está en la lista `generic`. Necesito agregar \"not\" a la lista genérica. También \"enforced\" tal vez debería estar en la lista (ya está). \"contract\" ya está. \"handoff\" ya está.\n\nAgregaré más stop words: \"not\", \"and\", \"or\", \"but\", \"for\", \"with\", \"without\", \"from\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"at\", \"by\", \"as\", \"if\", \"then\", \"else\", \"when\", \"where\", \"how\", \"why\", \"what\", \"which\", \"who\", \"whom\", \"whose\", \"this\", \"that\", \"these\", \"those\", \"there\", \"here\".\n\nTambién podría excluir palabras con menos de 3 letras, pero \"not\" tiene 3. Mejor usar una lista extensa.\n\nAdemás, noto que \"multi_agent\" se añade como tag porque la función `add_meaningful` para la segunda parte (type) no se ejecuta porque `typ` está en el type_map y se añade \"multi-agent\". Sin embargo, luego también se añade \"multi_agent\" porque el dominio es \"multi_agent\" (primera parte). Eso es redundante. Podríamos evitar añadir el dominio si ya tenemos un tag similar. Pero quizás está bien tener \"multi_agent\" y \"multi-agent\". Podemos normalizar: convertir guiones bajos a guiones. O simplemente permitir ambos.\n\nSin embargo, prefiero tener tags únicos y consistentes. Modificaré la función para que el dominio se añada solo si no es redundante con tags ya existentes.\n\nPero primero, enfoquémonos en eliminar palabras genéricas. Voy a actualizar la lista `generic` en la función `add_meaningful`. También cambiaré la lógica para excluir palabras de menos de 3 caracteres (excepto si son acrónimos importantes como \"api\", pero eso se maneja aparte). Agregaré \"api\" a la lista de excepciones.\n\nVoy a editar la función. Primero, necesito reemplazar todo el bloque de `add_meaningful`. También ajustaré la lógica de añadir dominio. Pero primero hagamos la lista genérica más amplia.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_GjK1IkuYiOIYrco3zKzipglZ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py","oldText":"    # Helper to split snake_case into words and add meaningful ones\n    def add_meaningful(text, exclude_generic=True):\n        words = text.lower().split('_')\n        generic = {\"error\", \"failure\", \"handoff\", \"missing\", \"required\", \"content\", \n                   \"field\", \"report\", \"contract\", \"enforced\", \"excessive\", \"workload\",\n                   \"timeout\", \"unknown\", \"none\", \"openclaw\"}\n        for w in words:\n            if not w or len(w) < 2:\n                continue\n            if exclude_generic and w in generic:\n                continue\n            tags.add(w)","newText":"    # Helper to split snake_case into words and add meaningful ones\n    def add_meaningful(text, exclude_generic=True):\n        words = text.lower().split('_')\n        generic = {\"error\", \"failure\", \"handoff\", \"missing\", \"required\", \"content\", \n                   \"field\", \"report\", \"contract\", \"enforced\", \"excessive\", \"workload\",\n                   \"timeout\", \"unknown\", \"none\", \"openclaw\", \"not\", \"and\", \"or\", \"but\",\n                   \"for\", \"with\", \"without\", \"from\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"at\", \"by\", \"as\",\n                   \"if\", \"then\", \"else\", \"when\", \"where\", \"how\", \"why\", \"what\", \"which\",\n                   \"who\", \"whom\", \"whose\", \"this\", \"that\", \"these\", \"those\", \"there\", \"here\",\n                   \"been\", \"being\", \"have\", \"has\", \"had\", \"do\", \"does\", \"did\", \"will\", \"would\",\n              