":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"## ✅ Refinements Applied\n\n### 1. Normalized Section Headings\nUpdated `update_index.py` to use exact lowercase headings as specified:\n- `## tools`\n- `## requirements`\n- `## planning`\n- `## multi-agent`\n- `## validation`\n- `## other`\n\n### 2. Contextual, Searchable Tags\nCompletely rewrote `generate_tags()` function to:\n- Remove generic filler tags (`incident`, `learning`, `guardrail`)\n- Focus on tool/domain/action keywords\n- Normalize underscores to hyphens for consistency\n- Filter out stop words and very short words\n- Extract meaningful terms from Pattern‑Key parts\n- Add contextual keywords from prevention rules when needed\n\n### 3. Rebuilt INDEX.md from Scratch\nFirst 30 lines of the regenerated index:\n\n```markdown\n# INDEX.md – Lightweight Retrieval Index\n\n*Generated by error‑learning‑loop. Updated: 2026-03-05 13:05:47*\n\n---\n\n## tools\n\n- Pattern-Key: model|ERROR|deepseek_reasoner|missing_field|reasoning_content_required\n  Tags: deepseek, model, model-error, reasoning\n  Rule: For long multi‑step tasks, avoid DeepSeek reasoning mode; use standard completion mode or a different model.\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n\n## multi-agent\n\n- Pattern-Key: multi_agent|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF|openclaw_subagent|missing_report|handoff_contract_not_enforced\n  Tags: handoff, multi-agent, report, subagent\n  Rule: Every sub‑agent must end its final response with a structured Handoff Report (Outcome + Incidents).\n  Promoted: AGENTS.md\n\n## validation\n\n- Pattern-Key: validation|TOOL_FAILURE|openclaw_validator|timeout|excessive_workload\n  Tags: items, tool-failure, validation, validator\n  Rule: Never assign more than 5 items to a single validator agent. If more items need validation, spawn multiple validators each with a subset.\n  Promoted: AGENTS.md\n```\n\n### 4. Global Deduplication Confirmed\n✅ **Each Pattern‑Key appears exactly once** (3 total entries). The index generator enforces:\n- Keep highest count when duplicates exist\n- Keep newest `last_seen` timestamp\n- Merge metadata from all sources\n- Write analytics to separate `REPORT.md`\n\nThe Learning Retrieval Layer now provides:\n- **Lightweight scanning** – minimal entries (3–4 lines each)\n- **Contextual tags** – focused on tool/domain/action\n- **Fixed domain sections** – consistent navigation\n- **Separation of concerns** – analytics in `REPORT.md`, retrieval in `INDEX.md`"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":481,"output":1541,"cacheRead":67200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69222,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772733956113}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed1108d9","parentId":"51f9b574","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:20:21.537Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 13:20 EST] Implement automatic Contextual Learning Retrieval in AGENTS.md so the agent consults the Learning Retrieval Layer before executing complex tasks. \n\nThe system already has a working learning store: \n\n/.learnings/ ERRORS.md LEARNINGS.md INDEX.md REPORT.md \n\nINDEX.md is the lightweight retrieval layer and must be used before complex operations. \n\n \n\n Modify AGENTS.md \n\nInside the section: \n\nEvery Session \n\nAdd a new step after the existing session preparation steps. \n\nThe new step must implement Contextual Learning Retrieval using the learning index. \n\nInsert the following block: \n\nContextual Learning Retrieval \n\nBefore executing any complex task, perform a quick learning retrieval using the learning index. \n\nSteps: \n\n Scan <workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md. \n\n Identify Pattern-Keys relevant to the current task context. \n\n Select the top 3–7 relevant Pattern-Keys. \n\n Apply their Rules or Preflight constraints before executing the task. \n\n Only consult .learnings/LEARNINGS.md if a rule requires additional detail. \n\nThis retrieval step must be lightweight and should avoid loading large logs unnecessarily. \n\n \n\n Add Trigger Heuristics \n\nDefine what qualifies as a complex task to avoid unnecessary index scans. \n\nAdd the following rules under the retrieval block: \n\nRun Contextual Learning Retrieval when any of the following conditions apply: \n\n Using external tools (bash, python, shell scripts) \n\n Delegating work to sub-agents \n\n Running validator agents or batch operations \n\n Producing multi-file outputs (skills, scripts, documentation, codebases) \n\n Tasks expected to require multiple reasoning steps (>3 steps) \n\nSkip retrieval for trivial or conversational responses. \n\n \n\n Confirm Integration \n\nAfter editing AGENTS.md: \n\n• Show the updated ## Every Session section \n\n• Confirm the retrieval step appears in the correct order \n\n• Confirm the retrieval logic references <workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md"}],"timestamp":1772734821516}}
{"type":"message","id":"ceae8081","parentId":"ed1108d9","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:21:33.564Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to modify AGENTS.md to add the Contextual Learning Retrieval step. First, let me read the current \"Every Session\" section to see the existing steps and where to insert the new one.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_uj4jPNHvqAUzYG2cTZwRqNbm","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md","offset":1,"limit":100}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":68878,"output":170,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69048,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772734821533}}
{"type":"message","id":"68817cb7","parentId":"ceae8081","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:21:33.581Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_uj4jPNHvqAUzYG2cTZwRqNbm","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Every Session\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n5. If `.learnings/INDEX.md` exists, scan it for relevant Pattern-Keys based on the current task context, then consult `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` / `.learnings/ERRORS.md` only for those keys.\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n\n### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n\n### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n\n- **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝\n\n## Safety\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n## External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n## Group Chats\n\nYou have access to your human's stuff. That doesn't mean you _share_ their stuff. In groups, you're a participant — not their voice, not their proxy. Think before you speak.\n\n### 💬 Know When to Speak!\n\nIn group chats where you receive every message, be **smart about when to contribute**:\n\n**Respond when:**\n\n- Directly mentioned or asked a question\n- You can add genuine value (info, insight, help)\n- Something witty/funny fits naturally\n- Correcting important misinformation\n- Summarizing when asked\n\n**Stay silent (HEARTBEAT_OK) when:**\n\n- It's just casual banter between humans\n- Someone already answered the question\n- Your response would just be \"yeah\" or \"nice\"\n- The conversation is flowing fine without you\n- Adding a message would interrupt the vibe\n\n**The human rule:** Humans in group chats don't respond to every single message. Neither should you. Quality > quantity. If you wouldn't send it in a real group chat with friends, don't send it.\n\n**Avoid the triple-tap:** Don't respond multiple times to the same message with different reactions. One thoughtful response beats three fragments.\n\nParticipate, don't dominate.\n\n### 😊 React Like a Human!\n\n[132 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772734893573}}
