{"type":"message","id":"cc6e204b","parentId":"9c8bbd20","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:32:45.073Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_z8R5MZa0Cjw1w8gN0XFgtUC6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Every Session\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n5. **Contextual Learning Retrieval** – Before executing any complex task, perform a quick learning retrieval using the learning index:\n   - Scan `<workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md`\n   - Identify Pattern‑Keys relevant to the current task context\n   - Select the top 3–7 relevant Pattern‑Keys\n   - Apply their Rules or Preflight constraints before executing the task\n   - Only consult `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` if a rule requires additional detail\n   \n   This retrieval step must be lightweight and should avoid loading large logs unnecessarily.\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n### Trigger Heuristics\n\nRun Contextual Learning Retrieval when any of the following conditions apply:\n\n- Using external tools (bash, python, shell scripts)\n- Delegating work to sub-agents\n- Running validator agents or batch operations\n- Producing multi-file outputs (skills, scripts, documentation, codebases)\n- Tasks expected to require multiple reasoning steps (>3 steps)\n\nSkip retrieval for trivial or conversational responses.\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n\n\n[203 more lines in file. Use offset=49 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772735565062}}
