Run Contextual Learning Retrieval when any of the following conditions apply:\n\n- Using external tools (bash, python, shell scripts)\n- Delegating work to sub-agents\n- Running validator agents or batch operations\n- Producing multi-file outputs (skills, scripts, documentation, codebases)\n- Tasks expected to require multiple reasoning steps (>3 steps)\n\nSkip retrieval for trivial or conversational responses.\n```\n\n### **Integration Confirmed:**\n\n✅ **Correct Order**: Contextual Learning Retrieval appears as step 5, after session initialization and before task execution.\n\n✅ **References `<workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md`**: Both the retrieval step and trigger heuristics reference the canonical lightweight index.\n\n✅ **Lightweight Design**: Retrieval focuses on `INDEX.md` (minimal, 3–4 line entries) and only consults `LEARNINGS.md` when additional detail is needed.\n\n✅ **Trigger Heuristics Defined**: Clear criteria for when to run retrieval, preventing unnecessary scans for trivial tasks.\n\n### **Learning Store Status:**\n- **`INDEX.md`**: Contains 3 Pattern‑Keys, each appearing exactly once (global deduplication enforced)\n- **Tags**: Contextual and searchable (e.g., `deepseek`, `model-error`, `handoff`, `validation`, `batching`)\n- **Sections**: Fixed domain grouping (`tools`, `multi-agent`, `validation`, etc.)\n\nThe agent now has an automated mechanism to consult learned guardrails before complex operations, reducing repeat errors while maintaining low overhead."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":143,"output":889,"cacheRead":69760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70792,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772735592322}}
