{"type":"message","id":"1ac72a7a","parentId":"a890498a","timestamp":"2026-03-05T18:54:30.244Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_1yKehYbOFZbHmIjlHvy8OjDM","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n- Read and organize memory files\n- Check on projects (git status, etc.)\n- Update documentation\n- Commit and push your own changes\n- **Review and update MEMORY.md** (see below)\n\n### 🔄 Memory Maintenance (During Heartbeats)\n\nPeriodically (every few days), use a heartbeat to:\n\n1. Read through recent `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` files\n2. Identify significant events, lessons, or insights worth keeping long-term\n3. Update `MEMORY.md` with distilled learnings\n4. Remove outdated info from MEMORY.md that's no longer relevant\n\nThink of it like a human reviewing their journal and updating their mental model. Daily files are raw notes; MEMORY.md is curated wisdom.\n\nThe goal: Be helpful without being annoying. Check in a few times a day, do useful background work, but respect quiet time.\n\n## Guardrails (Auto-learnings)\n\n*Automatically promoted from error‑learning‑loop.*\n\n### Validator Batch Size\n- **Pattern‑Key**: validation|TOOL_FAILURE|openclaw_validator|timeout|excessive_workload\n- **Date**: 2026‑03‑04\n- **Rule**: Never assign more than 5 items to a single validator agent. Split validation tasks into batches of ≤5 items.\n- **Rationale**: Validators with 6+ items tend to timeout within the 10‑minute execution window.\n- **Preflight**: Count items before launching validator; estimate time (allow ~2 minutes per item). If total >8 minutes, split batch.\n\n### Handoff Report Enforcement\n- **Pattern‑Key**: multi_agent|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF|openclaw_subagent|missing_report|handoff_contract_not_enforced\n- **Date**: 2026‑03‑04\n- **Rule**: Every sub‑agent must end its final response with a structured Handoff Report (Outcome + Incidents).\n- **Rationale**: Without enforced reporting, incidents from sub‑agents are lost, breaking the error‑learning loop.\n- **Preflight**: Include Handoff Report requirement in sub‑agent instructions; verify output contains the report.\n\n## Make It Yours\n\nThis is a starting point. Add your own conventions, style, and rules as you figure out what works.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772736870235}}
