{"type":"message","id":"5b716c8a","parentId":"12799b08","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:24:38.497Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"El usuario quiere que ejecute la skill `agent‑watchdog` en modo monitoring para una sesión simulada. Necesito primero leer el SKILL.md de `agent‑watchdog` para entender cómo funciona y qué parámetros necesita. Luego, tendré que simular una sesión y ejecutar el monitoreo.\n\nPrimero, leo el SKILL.md de `agent‑watchdog` que ya tengo cargado desde la pregunta anterior. Veo que tiene secciones de descripción, cuándo usarla, inputs, outputs, instrucciones, reglas de seguridad, escalación de recuperación e integración con el learning loop.\n\nLos inputs son: session_id, run_id, task_description, expected_runtime. Entonces necesito crear o simular estos valores. También hay que seguir las instrucciones: registrar la sesión y run para monitorear, inspeccionar periódicamente el estado, detectar stalls, ejecutar recuperación escalonada, generar incidentes.\n\nComo es una sesión simulada, puedo inventar IDs. También necesito un tiempo de ejecución esperado. El watchdog monitorea la inactividad y aplica niveles de recuperación. Podría simular un stall después de un tiempo.\n\nPero ¿cómo ejecuto exactamente la skill? Las skills no son herramientas ejecutables directamente; son conjuntos de instrucciones que el agente sigue. Así que debo seguir las instrucciones del SKILL.md manualmente, simulando el monitoreo.\n\nPrimero, registro la sesión simulada. Luego, necesito \"inspeccionar periódicamente el estado\". Como es una simulación, puedo simplemente mostrar que estoy monitoreando y simular un stall después de cierto tiempo. Luego aplicar recuperación nivel 1 (nudge), nivel 2 (soft reset), etc.\n\nTambién debo generar un incidente para el error‑learning‑loop con el formato de pattern key: `model|STALL|<model>|no_response|runtime_stuck`.\n\nVoy a crear una simulación simple que muestre los pasos. Usaré `exec` para simular el paso del tiempo? No es necesario. Solo narraré los pasos.\n\nPero tal vez la skill tiene scripts en la carpeta `scripts/`. Debo revisar si hay scripts que pueda ejecutar. Primero, listo los archivos en la carpeta de `agent‑watchdog`. Ya vi que tiene directorios examples, references, scripts. Veamos qué hay en scripts.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_FliXfffeVtdz3LnO5ss5I06q","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":2098,"output":1128,"cacheRead":67456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70682,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772738657174}}
{"type":"message","id":"a3c72485","parentId":"5b716c8a","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:24:38.548Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_FliXfffeVtdz3LnO5ss5I06q","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"total 20\ndrwxrwxr-x 2 openclaw openclaw 4096 Mar  5 14:16 .\ndrwxrwxr-x 5 openclaw openclaw 4096 Mar  5 14:16 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  358 Mar  5  2026 watchdog_learning_adapter.py\n-rw-r--r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  607 Mar  5  2026 watchdog_monitor.py\n-rw-r--r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  230 Mar  5  2026 watchdog_recovery.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":21,"aggregated":"total 20\ndrwxrwxr-x 2 openclaw openclaw 4096 Mar  5 14:16 .\ndrwxrwxr-x 5 openclaw openclaw 4096 Mar  5 14:16 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  358 Mar  5  2026 watchdog_learning_adapter.py\n-rw-r--r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  607 Mar  5  2026 watchdog_monitor.py\n-rw-r--r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  230 Mar  5  2026 watchdog_recovery.py","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772738678535}}
{"type":"message","id":"bdf6ca7e","parentId":"a3c72485","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:24:43.979Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hay scripts Python. Voy a leerlos para ver si puedo ejecutarlos. Primero, `watchdog_monitor.py`.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_V5isvEUEDCegmSYAzn9w07OL","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":799,"output":119,"cacheRead":69504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70422,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772738678548}}
{"type":"message","id":"d461263c","parentId":"bdf6ca7e","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:24:43.996Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_V5isvEUEDCegmSYAzn9w07OL","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nimport time\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nSTALL_TIMEOUT = 120\nMONITOR_INTERVAL = 30\n\nclass Session:\n    def __init__(self, session_id):\n        self.session_id = session_id\n        self.last_activity = datetime.utcnow()\n        self.state = \"running\"\n\ndef detect_stall(session):\n    inactivity = (datetime.utcnow() - session.last_activity).total_seconds()\n    if session.state == \"running\" and inactivity > STALL_TIMEOUT:\n        return True\n    return False\n\ndef monitor(session):\n    while True:\n        if detect_stall(session):\n            return \"stall_detected\"\n        time.sleep(MONITOR_INTERVAL)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772738683989}}
{"type":"message","id":"370901a5","parentId":"d461263c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:24:49.487Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, es un script simple que define una clase Session y funciones de detección de stall. No es un script ejecutable completo. Probablemente sea un ejemplo. También hay `watchdog_recovery.py`.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_YGBkuri1v15Q1fvuiplI0xOk","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":294,"output":153,"cacheRead":70272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70719,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772738683997}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4b89822","parentId":"370901a5","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:24:49.499Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_YGBkuri1v15Q1fvuiplI0xOk","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\ndef recovery_action(attempt):\n    if attempt == 1:\n        return \"nudge_continue\"\n    elif attempt == 2:\n        return \"cancel_and_resume\"\n    elif attempt == 3:\n        return \"relaunch_agent\"\n    else:\n        return \"abort\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772738689493}}
{"type":"message","id":"785ae347","parentId":"b4b89822","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:24:55.132Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Y `watchdog_learning_adapter.py`.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_wt4ioZcmvfiMtW5mOsfl144r","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_learning_adapter.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":225,"output":87,"cacheRead":70528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70840,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772738689499}}
{"type":"message","id":"68cd5bdb","parentId":"785ae347","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:24:55.176Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_wt4ioZcmvfiMtW5mOsfl144r","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\ndef generate_incident(model, stall_duration, recovery_level, success):\n    return {\n        \"pattern_key\": f\"model|STALL|{model}|no_response|runtime_stuck\",\n        \"timestamp\": datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        \"stall_duration\": stall_duration,\n        \"recovery_level\": recovery_level,\n        \"success\": success\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772738695152}}
{"type":"message","id":"649f2f3d","parentId":"68cd5bdb","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:25:43.230Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Estos scripts son módulos de ejemplo, no programas completos. La skill parece ser más bien un conjunto de instrucciones para que el agente implemente manualmente. Entonces, debo seguir las instrucciones del SKILL.md y simular el monitoreo.\n\nVoy a crear una sesión simulada con IDs ficticios. Luego, simularé que paso el tiempo y detecto un stall. Aplicaré recuperación nivel 1 (nudge), nivel 2 (soft reset), etc. Finalmente, generaré un incidente para el error‑learning‑loop.\n\nPero también debo considerar que el watchdog debe integrarse con el error‑learning‑loop. El incidente generado debe ser registrado en ERRORS.md/LEARNINGS.md. Podría simplemente mostrar el formato del incidente, sin realmente escribirlo (para no ensuciar los logs reales). O puedo escribirlo en un archivo temporal.\n\nEl usuario dijo \"ejecuta agent‑watchdog skill en modo monitoring para una session simulada\". Asumo que quiere ver una demostración de cómo funciona el watchdog.\n\nProcederé así:\n\n1. Crear variables de sesión simulada.\n2. Mostrar que inicio monitoreo.\n3. Simular que después de 2 minutos (STALL_TIMEOUT) detecto stall.\n4. Aplicar recuperación nivel 1: enviar \"continue\".\n5. Simular que no responde, aplicar nivel 2: cancel run y resume task.\n6. Simular que aún no responde, aplicar nivel 3: close session y relaunch agent.\n7. Generar incidente con pattern key.\n8. Mostrar telemetría.\n\nTambién debo respetar las reglas de seguridad: máximo 3 intentos, nunca reiniciar indefinidamente, siempre emitir incidente.\n\nVoy a hacerlo narrativamente, con mensajes detallados. También puedo usar `exec` para simular el paso del tiempo con `sleep`, pero no es necesario.\n\nComenzaré.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"## 🐕 agent‑watchdog – Monitoring Simulated Session\n\n**Skill invoked**: `agent‑watchdog`  \n**Mode**: Monitoring (simulated session)  \n**Goal**: Detect stalls, attempt recovery, generate incident for error‑learning‑loop.\n\n---\n\n### 📋 Session Registration\n\n```python\nsession_id = \"sim-session-001\"\nrun_id = \"sim-run-2026-03-05-14-24\"\ntask_description = \"Validate 8 items with Contextual Learning Retrieval\"\nexpected_runtime = 16  # minutes (3 validators, parallel)\nmodel = \"custom-api-deepseek-com/deepseek-reasoner\"\n```\n\n**Monitoring started**: 2026‑03‑05 14:24 EST  \n**Stall timeout**: 120 seconds (2 minutes)  \n**Monitor interval**: 30 seconds\n\n---\n\n### 🔍 Period 1: Normal Activity (0‑90 seconds)\n\n```\n[00:30] Session state: running ✅\n[01:00] Last activity: 60 seconds ago ✅\n[01:30] All validators reporting progress ✅\n```\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Period 2: Stall Detection (120 seconds)\n\n```\n[02:00] ❌ STALL DETECTED\n- Session: sim‑session‑001\n- Run: sim‑run‑2026‑03‑05‑14‑24\n- Inactivity: 120 seconds (exceeds stall timeout)\n- State: running (no response)\n```\n\n**Stall classification**: Model hang (no response within timeout window)\n\n---\n\n### 🚨 Recovery Escalation\n\n#### **Level 1 – Nudge (send \"continue\")**\n```\n[02:05] Recovery attempt 1/3\nAction: send nudge message \"continue\"\nTarget: session sim‑session‑001\nResult: no response after 30 seconds\nStatus: failed\n```\n\n#### **Level 2 – Soft Reset (cancel run and resume task)**\n```\n[02:35] Recovery attempt 2/3\nAction: cancel run sim‑run‑2026‑03‑05‑14‑24\nAction: resume task from last checkpoint\nResult: session still unresponsive\nStatus: failed\n```\n\n#### **Level 3 – Relaunch (close session and start new agent)**\n```\n[03:05] Recovery attempt 3/3\nAction: close session sim‑session‑001\nAction: launch new agent with same task\nResult: new session active, task resumed\nStatus: success\n```\n\n**Recovery outcome**: Success after 3 attempts (relaunch required)\n\n---\n\n### 📊 Telemetry & Incident Generation\n\n**Pattern‑Key**: `model|STALL|custom-api-deepseek-com/deepseek-reasoner|no_response|runtime_stuck`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"pattern_key\": \"model|STALL|custom-api-deepseek-com/deepseek-reasoner|no_response|runtime_stuck\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026‑03‑05T19:27:00Z\",\n  \"stall_duration\": 120,\n  \"recovery_level\": 3,\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"model\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com/deepseek-reasoner\",\n  \"task_type\": \"validator_batch\",\n  \"items_count\": 8,\n  \"batch_strategy\": \"3+3+2\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🔄 Learning‑Loop Integration\n\n**Incident ready for error‑learning‑loop** with:\n\n1. **Pattern‑Key** following schema: `model|STALL|<model>|no_response|runtime_stuck`\n2. **Telemetry fields** required for learning extraction:\n   - `model`: identifies which model stalled\n   - `stall_duration`: quantifies severity\n   - `recovery_level`: documents what worked\n   - `success`: outcome flag\n3. **Context**: Validator batch operation (8 items, split 3+3+2)\n\n**Next step**: Feed this incident to `error‑learning‑loop` skill for:\n- Deduplication against existing incidents\n- Learning statement extraction\n- Prevention rule formulation\n- Potential guardrail promotion\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Monitoring Complete\n\n**Summary**:\n- ✅ Session registered and monitored\n- ✅ Stall detected at 120 seconds\n- ✅ Recovery escalation followed (nudge → soft reset → relaunch)\n- ✅ Incident generated with full telemetry\n- ✅ Safety rules respected (max 3 attempts, always emit report)\n\n**Recommendation from watchdog**:\n- Consider reducing validator batch size further if stalls persist\n- Monitor model‑specific timeout patterns\n- Track recovery success rate per model/task type\n\nThe `agent‑watchdog` skill has successfully simulated monitoring, stall detection, staged recovery, and incident generation – ready for integration with the error‑learning‑loop."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":214,"output":1884,"cacheRead":70720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72818,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772738695177}}
