{"type":"message","id":"e4c411a6","parentId":"0d7119a4","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:28:34.488Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_G4cQEtCZhAwJYarmOtMwW8mO","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n## Delegation Template\nWhen spawning sub‑agents, ALWAYS include the following Handoff Report requirement (non‑optional):\n\n```\n### Mandatory Final Block\nYour final response must end with a structured Handoff Report using this exact format:\n\n### Handoff Report\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**:\n  - [TYPE=ERROR|NEAR_MISS|MISUNDERSTANDING|TOOL_FAILURE|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF; SEV=S1|S2|S3|S4] <brief symptom> (evidence: <1‑line concrete detail, no secrets>)\n  - Pattern hint: <optional>\n  - Prevention rule: <optional>\n- **Files touched**: <list or \"none\">\n- **Next action**: <1‑line suggestion>\n\nIf no incidents occurred, write \"Incidents: none\".\nDo NOT include secrets, tokens, or credentials in evidence.\n```\n\nThis template must be included verbatim in all sub‑agent delegation prompts.\n\n**Watchdog Registration**: Whenever sub‑agents are spawned for long‑running tasks (expected runtime >5 minutes), automatically register them with the `agent‑watchdog` for stall monitoring and recovery.\n\n## Make It Yours\n\nThis is a starting point. Add your own conventions, style, and rules as you figure out what works.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772738914467}}
{"type":"message","id":"bbf71ebd","parentId":"e4c411a6","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:29:00.448Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfecto. La adición está en el lugar correcto. Ahora mostraré la sección actualizada al usuario y confirmaré la integración. También notaré que se agregó después de la plantilla y antes de \"Make It Yours\". El texto define \"long-running tasks\" como expected runtime >5 minutos, lo que parece razonable. Ahora responderé.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"## ✅ Instrucción Agregada a AGENTS.md\n\nHe agregado la siguiente política en la sección **## Delegation Template**:\n\n```markdown\n**Watchdog Registration**: Whenever sub‑agents are spawned for long‑running tasks (expected runtime >5 minutes), automatically register them with the `agent‑watchdog` for stall monitoring and recovery.\n```\n\n### 📋 Ubicación y Contexto\n\n**Sección**: Delegation Template (justo después del template de Handoff Report, antes de \"Make It Yours\")\n\n**Integración con flujo existente**:\n1. **Trigger Heuristics** ya define cuándo ejecutar Contextual Learning Retrieval (delegación a sub‑agents, tareas multi‑paso)\n2. **Delegation Template** ahora incluye dos requisitos:\n   - Handoff Report obligatorio\n   - Registro automático con `agent‑watchdog` para tareas largas (>5 minutos)\n3. **Guardrails** mantienen las reglas de seguridad (batch size, reportes)\n\n### 🚀 Comportamiento Automático Resultante\n\nCuando se spawnean sub‑agents para:\n\n- Validación de batches grandes\n- Tareas de múltiples pasos (>3 reasoning steps)\n- Ejecución prolongada (>5 minutos estimados)\n\nEl sistema ahora hará:\n\n1. **Registro en watchdog** → monitoreo de stalls (timeout 2 minutos)\n2. **Recuperación escalonada** → nudge → soft reset → relaunch\n3. **Reporte de incidentes** → integración con error‑learning‑loop\n4. **Handoff Report** → captura de incidentes para aprendizaje\n\n### 🔄 Conexión con Skills\n\n- **agent‑watchdog**: Detección de stalls, recuperación automática\n- **error‑learning‑loop**: Captura de incidentes, promoción de guardrails\n- **Contextual Learning Retrieval**: Consulta de INDEX.md antes de tareas complejas\n\nLa política ahora está documentada y lista para implementación automática en futuras delegaciones."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":43932,"output":603,"cacheRead":27328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71863,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772738914489}}
{"type":"message","id":"03d0f87c","parentId":"bbf71ebd","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:40:41.467Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 14:40 EST] You must perform a structured correction and upgrade of the current agent orchestration system. \n\n \n\nThis update must modify AGENTS.md and the agent-watchdog skill to ensure correct watchdog registration, session monitoring, deadlock detection, and learning integration. \n\n \n\nThe goal is to fix the current policy-only watchdog registration and turn it into an operational mechanism. \n\n \n\nAdditionally, you must implement multi-agent deadlock detection and ACP runtime monitoring. \n\n \n\nDo NOT create a new skill. You must update the existing system. \n\n \n\nFollow the instructions carefully. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\nSTEP 1 — VERIFY CURRENT ARCHITECTURE \n\n \n\nInspect the workspace and confirm the following components exist: \n\n \n\nskills/ \n\n error-learning-loop/ \n\n agent-watchdog/ \n\n \n\n.learnings/ \n\n ERRORS.md \n\n LEARNINGS.md \n\n INDEX.md \n\n REPORT.md \n\n \n\nAGENTS.md \n\n \n\nThe architecture must already support: \n\n \n\n- error-learning-loop \n\n- contextual learning retrieval \n\n- watchdog monitoring \n\n- learning index \n\n \n\nIf any of these are missing, report them. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\nSTEP 2 — FIX WATCHDOG REGISTRATION POLICY \n\n \n\nCurrently AGENTS.md only contains a policy statement: \n\n \n\n\"Whenever sub-agents are spawned for long-running tasks (>5 minutes), automatically register them with the agent-watchdog.\" \n\n \n\nThis is insufficient. \n\n \n\nYou must convert this policy into an operational delegation procedure. \n\n \n\nUpdate AGENTS.md in the section: \n\n \n\n## Delegation Template \n\n \n\nAdd the following subsection AFTER the Handoff Report template. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\n### Watchdog Registration Procedure \n\n \n\nWhenever a sub-agent is spawned for a long-running task (expected runtime >5 minutes), the main agent must immediately register the sub-agent with the agent-watchdog. \n\n \n\nThe registration must include the following parameters: \n\n \n\nsession_id \n\nrun_id \n\ntask_description \n\nexpected_runtime \n\nmodel \n\nruntime_type (subagent | acp) \n\n \n\nProcedure: \n\n \n\n1. Spawn the sub-agent. \n\n2. Capture the returned session_id and run_id. \n\n3. Register the sub-agent with the watchdog. \n\n4. Start watchdog monitoring. \n\n5. Allow the watchdog to perform stall recovery if needed. \n\n \n\nExample flow: \n\n \n\nspawn validator_agent_A \n\nspawn validator_agent_B \n\n \n\nregister_watchdog( \n\n session_id=\"validator_A_session\", \n\n run_id=\"validator_A_run\", \n\n task_description=\"validate batch items\", \n\n expected_runtime=8, \n\n model=\"deepseek-reasoner\", \n\n runtime_type=\"subagent\" \n\n) \n\n \n\nThe watchdog will then: \n\n \n\nmonitor session activity \n\ndetect inactivity \n\nperform recovery escalation \n\n \n\nRecovery escalation levels: \n\n \n\nLevel 1: send \"continue\" \n\nLevel 2: cancel run and resume task \n\nLevel 3: close session and relaunch agent \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\nSTEP 3 — ENSURE WATCHDOG INCIDENT REPORTING \n\n \n\nModify the agent-watchdog skill so that after recovery attempts it must emit incidents to the learning system. \n\n \n\nAdd a final step in the watchdog flow: \n\n \n\nStep — Emit Incident to Learning Store \n\n \n\nActions: \n\n \n\n1. Generate incident telemetry. \n\n2. Append incident to: \n\n \n\n<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md \n\n \n\n3. Invoke the error-learning-loop skill. \n\n \n\nThe incident schema must follow the pattern: \n\n \n\nmodel|STALL|<model>|no_response|runtime_stuck \n\n \n\nTelemetry fields: \n\n \n\npattern_key \n\ntimestamp \n\nmodel \n\nstall_duration \n\nrecovery_level \n\nsuccess \n\ntask_type \n\nitems_count \n\n \n\nThis ensures the learning loop can deduplicate, extract rules, and promote guardrails. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\nSTEP 4 — VERIFY LEARNING LOOP INTEGRATION \n\n \n\nAfter emitting an incident the watchdog must trigger the learning loop. \n\n \n\nSequence must be: \n\n \n\nwatchdog detects stall \n\n→ recovery escalation \n\n→ incident generated \n\n→ incident appended to ERRORS.md \n\n→ error-learning-loop executed \n\n→ deduplication \n\n→ learning extraction \n\n→ guardrail promotion \n\n→ INDEX.md updated \n\n \n\nVerify that this pipeline works end-to-end. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\nSTEP 5 — VERIFY ACP SUBAGENT SUPPORT \n\n \n\nCheck OpenClaw version features. \n\n \n\nRecent OpenClaw versions introduced ACP dispatch enabled by default. \n\n \n\nACP stands for Agent Communication Protocol. \n\n \n\nACP agents run as independent processes that communicate with OpenClaw. \n\n \n\nBecause ACP agents run outside the parent runtime they may stall without reporting completion. \n\n \n\nUpdate the watchdog logic to support both runtimes: \n\n \n\nruntime_type = \"subagent\" \n\nruntime_type = \"acp\" \n\n \n\nThe watchdog must monitor: \n\n \n\n- subagent sessions \n\n- ACP sessions \n\n \n\nACP monitoring must detect: \n\n \n\nACP process running but no output \n\nno session updates \n\nsession stalled without completion callback \n\n \n\nIf ACP sessions stall, the watchdog must emit: \n\n \n\nruntime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\nSTEP 6 — IMPLEMENT MULTI-AGENT DEADLOCK DETECTION \n\n \n\nAdd a deadlock detection subsystem to the agent-watchdog skill. \n\n \n\nThis subsystem must detect dependency cycles between agents. \n\n \n\nDeadlocks occur when agents wait on each other indefinitely. \n\n \n\nExample scenario: \n\n \n\nAgent A waiting for B \n\nAgent B waiting for C \n\nAgent C waiting for A \n\n \n\nAll agents remain in state \"running\" but no progress occurs. \n\n \n\nThe watchdog must detect: \n\n \n\ndependency cycles \n\nblocked resource chains \n\nagents waiting on unresolved tasks \n\n \n\nImplementation requirements: \n\n \n\n1. Track active agents and their dependency relationships. \n\n \n\nEach monitored agent must include metadata: \n\n \n\nagent_id \n\nwaiting_for_agent_id \n\ntask_state \n\n \n\n2. Build a dependency graph of agents. \n\n \n\n3. Periodically check for cycles in the dependency graph. \n\n \n\nIf a cycle is detected, classify it as a deadlock. \n\n \n\nDeadlock pattern key: \n\n \n\nmulti_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting \n\n \n\n4. When a deadlock is detected the watchdog must attempt resolution. \n\n \n\nDeadlock recovery strategy: \n\n \n\nLevel 1 — Request progress update from all agents \n\nLevel 2 — Force resolution of one dependency edge \n\nLevel 3 — Restart one agent in the cycle \n\n \n\n5. Emit deadlock incidents to the learning system. \n\n \n\nTelemetry fields: \n\n \n\npattern_key \n\ntimestamp \n\ncycle_size \n\nagents_involved \n\nrecovery_strategy \n\nsuccess \n\n \n\nDeadlock incidents must be appended to: \n\n \n\n<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md \n\n \n\nExample pattern key: \n\n \n\nmulti_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\nSTEP 7 — VALIDATE FINAL SYSTEM \n\n \n\nAfter completing the update verify: \n\n \n\nAGENTS.md contains operational watchdog registration instructions. \n\n \n\nagent-watchdog emits incidents to the learning system. \n\n \n\nerror-learning-loop processes those incidents. \n\n \n\n.learnings/INDEX.md updates automatically. \n\n \n\nACP sessions are supported by the watchdog. \n\n \n\nMulti-agent deadlocks are detectable and recoverable. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------ \n\n \n\nOUTPUT \n\n \n\nReturn a structured report including: \n\n \n\n1. AGENTS.md modifications \n\n2. agent-watchdog updates \n\n3. learning-loop integration confirmation \n\n4. ACP monitoring capability \n\n5. deadlock detection capability \n\n6. final system architecture diagram \n\n \n\nDo not generate unnecessary explanations. \n\n \n\nOnly implement the required modifications."}],"timestamp":1772739641461}}
