cancel run and resume task\n+325 - **Level 3**: close session and relaunch agent\n+326 \n 280 ## Make It Yours\n 281 \n 282 This is a starting point. Add your own conventions, style, and rules as you figure out what works.","firstChangedLine":278},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772739709311}}
{"type":"message","id":"7aac55e3","parentId":"b01c146b","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:42:06.407Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ahora STEP 3: ENSURE WATCHDOG INCIDENT REPORTING. Necesito modificar la skill agent-watchdog para que emita incidentes al sistema de aprendizaje. Voy a inspeccionar los archivos de la skill. Primero, verificar qué scripts tiene. Ya los vi antes: watchdog_monitor.py, watchdog_recovery.py, watchdog_learning_adapter.py. Necesito actualizar estos scripts o crear un nuevo script que integre el flujo completo. Sin embargo, las skills en OpenClaw generalmente se implementan como scripts Python o simplemente instrucciones en SKILL.md. El usuario dice \"Do NOT create a new skill. You must update the existing system.\" Así que debo modificar los scripts existentes.\n\nVoy a revisar los scripts actuales más detalladamente.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_SG6eT9xLeUbkHUJpt3k8vnsD","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":43749,"output":411,"cacheRead":28416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772739709330}}
{"type":"message","id":"051c203e","parentId":"7aac55e3","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:42:06.433Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_SG6eT9xLeUbkHUJpt3k8vnsD","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nimport time\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nSTALL_TIMEOUT = 120\nMONITOR_INTERVAL = 30\n\nclass Session:\n    def __init__(self, session_id):\n        self.session_id = session_id\n        self.last_activity = datetime.utcnow()\n        self.state = \"running\"\n\ndef detect_stall(session):\n    inactivity = (datetime.utcnow() - session.last_activity).total_seconds()\n    if session.state == \"running\" and inactivity > STALL_TIMEOUT:\n        return True\n    return False\n\ndef monitor(session):\n    while True:\n        if detect_stall(session):\n            return \"stall_detected\"\n        time.sleep(MONITOR_INTERVAL)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772739726417}}
