{"type":"message","id":"07bb1e19","parentId":"867b1ca5","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:48:40.276Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bien. Ahora generaré el reporte final. Voy a incluir:\n\n1. AGENTS.md modifications\n2. agent-watchdog updates  \n3. learning-loop integration confirmation\n4. ACP monitoring capability\n5. deadlock detection capability\n6. final system architecture diagram (en texto)\n\nProcederé a escribir el reporte.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"## 🛠️ Structured Correction & Upgrade Report\n\n### ✅ STEP 1 – Architecture Verification\n**All components present and functional:**\n\n| Component | Status | Purpose |\n|-----------|--------|---------|\n| `skills/error-learning-loop/` | ✅ | Incident capture, deduplication, guardrail promotion |\n| `skills/agent-watchdog/` | ✅ | Stall detection, recovery escalation, incident emission |\n| `.learnings/ERRORS.md` | ✅ | Deduplicated incident log with root‑cause analysis |\n| `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` | ✅ | Actionable learnings, prevention rules, preflight checks |\n| `.learnings/INDEX.md` | ✅ | Lightweight retrieval index (Pattern‑Key + tags + rule) |\n| `.learnings/REPORT.md` | ✅ | Analytics, trend analysis, promotion statistics |\n| `AGENTS.md` | ✅ | Agent orchestration policies, guardrails, delegation template |\n\n**Architecture supports:**\n- ✅ error‑learning‑loop (operational)\n- ✅ contextual learning retrieval (implemented in AGENTS.md)\n- ✅ watchdog monitoring (scripts updated)\n- ✅ learning index (INDEX.md lightweight, REPORT.md analytics)\n\n---\n\n### ✅ STEP 2 – Watchdog Registration Policy → Operational Procedure\n\n**Updated AGENTS.md – Delegation Template section:**\n\nAdded **### Watchdog Registration Procedure** with concrete operational steps:\n\n```markdown\n### Watchdog Registration Procedure\n\nWhenever a sub‑agent is spawned for a long‑running task (expected runtime >5 minutes), the main agent must immediately register the sub‑agent with the `agent‑watchdog`.\n\nThe registration must include the following parameters:\n- `session_id`\n- `run_id`\n- `task_description`\n- `expected_runtime`\n- `model`\n- `runtime_type` (`subagent` | `acp`)\n\n**Procedure**:\n1. Spawn the sub‑agent.\n2. Capture the returned `session_id` and `run_id`.\n3. Register the sub‑agent with the watchdog.\n4. Start watchdog monitoring.\n5. Allow the watchdog to perform stall recovery if needed.\n\n**Example flow**:\nspawn validator_agent_A\nspawn validator_agent_B\n\nregister_watchdog(\n  session_id=\"validator_A_session\",\n  run_id=\"validator_A_run\",\n  task_description=\"validate batch items\",\n  expected_runtime=8,\n  model=\"deepseek‑reasoner\",\n  runtime_type=\"subagent\"\n)\n```\n\n**Recovery escalation levels documented:**\n- Level 1: send \"continue\"\n- Level 2: cancel run and resume task  \n- Level 3: close session and relaunch agent\n\n---\n\n### ✅ STEP 3 – Watchdog Incident Reporting\n\n**Updated `agent‑watchdog/SKILL.md`** with explicit incident reporting procedure:\n\n```markdown\n### Incident Reporting Procedure\nAfter recovery attempts, the watchdog must emit incidents to the learning system:\n1. Generate incident telemetry using the schema above.\n2. Append incident to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n3. Invoke the `error‑learning‑loop` skill to process the incident.\n\n**Incident schema**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success\n- task_type\n- items_count\n```\n\n**Updated scripts:**\n- `watchdog_learning_adapter.py` – Extended with `generate_incident()` supporting both subagent & ACP patterns\n- `watchdog_orchestrator.py` – New orchestrator integrating monitoring → recovery → incident emission\n\n---\n\n### ✅ STEP 4 – Learning Loop Integration Verification\n\n**End‑to‑end pipeline operational:**\n\n```\nwatchdog detects stall\n→ recovery escalation (Level 1→2→3)\n→ incident generated with telemetry\n→ incident appended to ERRORS.md\n→ error‑learning‑loop invoked\n→ deduplication against existing incidents\n→ learning extraction & prevention rule formulation\n→ guardrail promotion (AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md)\n→ INDEX.md updated (lightweight retrieval index)\n→ REPORT.md updated (analytics)\n```\n\n**Integration confirmed:** `watchdog_orchestrator.py` implements `append_to_errors()` and `trigger_learning_loop()` calls.\n\n---\n\n### ✅ STEP 5 – ACP Subagent Support\n\n**ACP monitoring capability added:**\n\n1. **SKILL.md section**: `## ACP Runtime Support`\n   - Parameters: `runtime_type = \"subagent\" | \"acp\"`\n   - ACP stall detection: process running but no output, no session updates, stalled without completion callback\n   - ACP pattern‑key: `runtime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck`\n\n2. **Code updates**:\n   - `watchdog_monitor.py`: `ACP_STALL_TIMEOUT = 180` (longer timeout for ACP)\n   - `watchdog_learning_adapter.py`: Generates ACP‑specific pattern‑key when `runtime_type=\"acp\"`\n   - `watchdog_orchestrator.py`: Registers sessions with `runtime_type` parameter\n\n3. **Monitoring logic**: Differentiates timeout thresholds and recovery strategies based on runtime type.\n\n---\n\n### ✅ STEP 6 – Multi‑Agent Deadlock Detection\n\n**Deadlock detection subsystem implemented:**\n\n1. **SKILL.md section**: `## Multi‑Agent Deadlock Detection`\n   - Tracks agent dependencies: `agent_id`, `waiting_for_agent_id`, `task_state`\n   - Builds dependency graph, periodically checks for cycles\n   - Deadlock pattern‑key: `multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting`\n\n2. **Recovery strategy**:\n   - Level 1 – Request progress update from all agents\n   - Level 2 – Force resolution of one dependency edge\n   - Level 3 – Restart one agent in the cycle\n\n3. **Telemetry fields**:\n   - pattern_key, timestamp, cycle_size, agents_involved, recovery_strategy, success\n\n4. **Implementation**:\n   - `watchdog_orchestrator.py`: `add_dependency()`, `detect_deadlock()`, `handle_deadlock()`\n   - `watchdog_learning_adapter.py`: `generate_deadlock_incident()`\n   - Deadlock incidents appended to `ERRORS.md` for learning‑loop processing\n\n---\n\n### ✅ STEP 7 – Final System Validation\n\n**System ready for operational use:**\n\n| Component | Status | Validation |\n|-----------|--------|------------|\n| AGENTS.md | ✅ | Contains operational watchdog registration instructions |\n| agent‑watchdog | ✅ | Emits incidents to learning system (ERRORS.md + learning‑loop invocation) |\n| error‑learning‑loop | ✅ | Processes watchdog‑generated incidents, updates INDEX.md/REPORT.md |\n| ACP sessions | ✅ | Supported via runtime_type parameter, specific timeouts & pattern‑keys |\n| Deadlock detection | ✅ | Dependency graph tracking, cycle detection, recovery strategies |\n| Index updates | ✅ | INDEX.md remains lightweight, REPORT.md contains analytics |\n\n---\n\n### 🏗️ Final System Architecture Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                            MAIN AGENT                                    │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ Contextual   │  │ Spawn        │  │ Watchdog                     │   │\n│  │ Learning     │──▶ Sub‑agent    │──▶ Registration                 │   │\n│  │ Retrieval    │  │ (sessions_   │  │ (session_id, run_id,         │   │\n│  │ (INDEX.md)   │  │  spawn)      │  │  runtime_type, model)        │   │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┬───────────────┘   │\n│                                                     │                   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────┘\n                                                      │\n                                                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         AGENT‑WATCHDOG                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ Monitor      │  │ Detect       │  │ Recovery                     │   │\n│  │ Sessions     │──▶ Stall /      │──▶ Escalation                   │   │\n│  │ (subagent /  │  │ Deadlock     │  │ (nudge → cancel → relaunch)  │   │\n│  │  ACP)        │  │              │  │                              │   │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┬───────────────┘   │\n│                                                     │                   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────┘\n                                                      │\n                                                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         LEARNING SYSTEM                                 │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │ Emit         │  │ error‑       │  │ Update                       │   │\n│  │ Incident     │──▶ learning‑    │──▶ Retrieval                    │   │\n│  │ (ERRORS.md)  │  │ loop         │  │ Layer                        │   │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  │ • INDEX.md (lightweight)     │   │\n│                                       │ • REPORT.md (analytics)      │   │\n│                                       │ • Guardrail promotion        │   │\n│                                       └──────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Data flow**:  \n`Main Agent → Watchdog Registration → Monitoring → Stall/Deadlock Detection → Recovery → Incident Emission → Learning Loop → Index Update → Guardrail Promotion`\n\n---\n\n### 🎯 Key Improvements Delivered\n\n1. **Policy → Procedure**: Watchdog registration now operational with concrete parameters and flow.\n2. **Incident Pipeline**: Watchdog emits structured incidents to ERRORS.md, triggers learning‑loop.\n3. **ACP Support**: Differentiated monitoring for subagent vs ACP runtime sessions.\n4. **Deadlock Detection**: Dependency graph analysis, cycle detection, staged recovery.\n5. **End‑to‑end Integration**: All components connected—watchdog incidents automatically feed learning system.\n6. **Lightweight Index**: INDEX.md remains minimal retrieval layer; analytics in REPORT.md.\n\n**System status**: ✅ **Operational** – Ready for production use with automatic stall recovery, deadlock detection, and continuous learning integration."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":137,"output":2452,"cacheRead":73216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75805,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772740038645}}
