{"type":"message","id":"efdb3077","parentId":"f7261a31","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:54:38.135Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_HJByPkBEOdl6LSKflXPQIEKs","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### Watchdog Registration Procedure\n\nWhenever a sub‑agent is spawned for a long‑running task (expected runtime >5 minutes), the main agent must immediately register the sub‑agent with the `agent‑watchdog`.\n\nThe registration must include the following parameters:\n\n- `session_id`\n- `run_id`\n- `task_description`\n- `expected_runtime`\n- `model`\n- `runtime_type` (`subagent` | `acp`)\n\n**Procedure**:\n\n1. Spawn the sub‑agent.\n2. Capture the returned `session_id` and `run_id`.\n3. Register the sub‑agent with the watchdog.\n4. Start watchdog monitoring.\n5. Allow the watchdog to perform stall recovery if needed.\n\n**Example flow**:\n\n```\nspawn validator_agent_A\nspawn validator_agent_B\n\nregister_watchdog(\n  session_id=\"validator_A_session\",\n  run_id=\"validator_A_run\",\n  task_description=\"validate batch items\",\n  expected_runtime=8,\n  model=\"deepseek‑reasoner\",\n  runtime_type=\"subagent\"\n)\n```\n\nThe watchdog will then:\n\n- Monitor session activity\n- Detect inactivity\n- Perform recovery escalation\n\n**Recovery escalation levels**:\n\n- **Level 1**: send \"continue\"\n- **Level 2**: cancel run and resume task\n- **Level 3**: close session and relaunch agent\n\n## Make It Yours\n\n[3 more lines in file. Use offset=328 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772740478117}}
{"type":"message","id":"aa16e560","parentId":"efdb3077","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:54:44.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to check if the watchdog script actually accepts these parameters. Let me look at the register_session function in watchdog_orchestrator.py again.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Ww46H9dls956GlCoQuEcRMig","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py","offset":30,"limit":40}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":432,"output":161,"cacheRead":75712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76305,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772740478140}}
{"type":"message","id":"5466945b","parentId":"aa16e560","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:54:44.669Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_Ww46H9dls956GlCoQuEcRMig","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    \n    def register_session(self, session_id, run_id, task_description,\n                         expected_runtime, model, runtime_type='subagent'):\n        \"\"\"Register a session for monitoring.\"\"\"\n        session = Session(session_id)\n        session.run_id = run_id\n        session.task_description = task_description\n        session.expected_runtime = expected_runtime\n        session.model = model\n        session.runtime_type = runtime_type\n        session.start_time = datetime.utcnow()\n        session.last_activity = datetime.utcnow()\n        session.state = 'running'\n        \n        self.sessions[session_id] = session\n        print(f\"[Watchdog] Registered session {session_id} ({runtime_type})\")\n        return session\n    \n    def update_activity(self, session_id):\n        \"\"\"Update last activity timestamp for a session.\"\"\"\n        if session_id in self.sessions:\n            self.sessions[session_id].last_activity = datetime.utcnow()\n    \n    def detect_stalls(self):\n        \"\"\"Check all registered sessions for stalls.\"\"\"\n        stalls = []\n        for session_id, session in self.sessions.items():\n            if detect_stall(session):\n                stalls.append(session)\n        return stalls\n    \n    def perform_recovery(self, session, attempt):\n        \"\"\"Execute recovery escalation.\"\"\"\n        action = recovery_action(attempt)\n        print(f\"[Recovery] Attempt {attempt}: {action} on session {session.session_id}\")\n        # Simulate action\n        if action == 'nudge_continue':\n            # Send continue signal\n            pass\n        elif action == 'cancel_and_resume':\n\n[184 more lines in file. Use offset=70 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772740484647}}
