{"type":"message","id":"25ac10e7","parentId":"27ff1c6c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:56:16.419Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So it's manual or wrap-up. Not automatically triggered by watchdog.\n\nNow I need to verify the index update pipeline. The update_index.py can rebuild INDEX.md and REPORT.md, but there's no automatic trigger. The watchdog doesn't actually call it.\n\nNow let me create the audit report. I need to provide evidence for each verification.\n\nLet me also check if there's any mechanism for agents to report waiting_for_agent_id. I don't see any. The deadlock detection assumes this information is available but there's no collection mechanism.\n\nNow let me compile the audit report. First, let me create a summary table. I'll go through each verification systematically.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"## 🔍 Technical Audit Report: Agent Orchestration System\n\n**Audit Date**: 2026‑03‑05 14:52 EST  \n**Scope**: Verification of operational capabilities in `agent‑watchdog` and learning‑loop integration.\n\n---\n\n### Verification 1 — Watchdog Incident Emission  \n**Status**: PASS  \n**Evidence**: \n```python\ndef append_to_errors(self, incident):\n    \"\"\"Append incident to ERRORS.md following the pattern-key format.\"\"\"\n    if not ERRORS_PATH.exists():\n        return\n    \n    with open(ERRORS_PATH, 'a', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        f.write(f\"\\n### Pattern-Key: {incident['pattern_key']}\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **First Occurrence**: {incident['timestamp'][:10]}\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Latest Occurrence**: {incident['timestamp'][:10]}\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Count**: 1\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Type**: stall\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Severity**: S2\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Model**: {incident.get('model', 'unknown')}\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Stall Duration**: {incident.get('stall_duration', 0)} seconds\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Recovery Level**: {incident.get('recovery_level', 0)}\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Success**: {incident.get('success', False)}\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Runtime Type**: {incident.get('runtime_type', 'subagent')}\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Task Type**: {incident.get('task_type', 'unknown')}\\n\")\n        f.write(f\"- **Items Count**: {incident.get('items_count', 0)}\\n\")\n        f.write(\"\\n\")\n    print(f\"[Watchdog] Incident appended to {ERRORS_PATH}\")\n```\n**Explanation**: The watchdog correctly writes structured incidents to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md` with all required telemetry fields.\n\n---\n\n### Verification 2 — Learning Loop Trigger  \n**Status**: PARTIAL  \n**Evidence**:\n```python\ndef trigger_learning_loop(self, incident):\n    \"\"\"Invoke the error-learning-loop skill.\"\"\"\n    # In production, this would spawn the skill via sessions_spawn\n    print(f\"[Watchdog] Triggering error-learning-loop for {incident['pattern_key']}\")\n    # Simulate call to error-learning-loop\n    # subprocess.run([...])\n```\n**Explanation**: The watchdog logs intent to trigger the learning loop but does **not** actually invoke `error-learning-loop`. This is a simulation stub; production integration would require `sessions_spawn` or direct skill execution.\n\n---\n\n### Verification 3 — Index Update Pipeline  \n**Status**: FAIL  \n**Evidence**:  \n1. **Learning loop modifies LEARNINGS.md** → Manual only (no automatic update after watchdog incidents).  \n2. **Learning loop updates INDEX.md** → Script exists (`update_index.py`) but is not called automatically.  \n3. **Learning loop updates REPORT.md** → Same script updates REPORT.md, but no automatic trigger.  \n\n**Pipeline gap**:  \n```\nincident emitted → ERRORS.md updated → ❌ error-learning-loop NOT executed → ❌ deduplication NOT performed → ❌ learning NOT extracted → ❌ guardrail NOT promoted → ❌ INDEX.md NOT rebuilt\n```\n\n**Explanation**: The `update_index.py` script can rebuild INDEX.md and REPORT.md, but there is **no automatic trigger** from watchdog incidents. The pipeline is broken after ERRORS.md append.\n\n---\n\n### Verification 4 — Deadlock Detection Capability  \n**Status**: PARTIAL  \n**Evidence**:\n```python\ndef add_dependency(self, agent_id, waiting_for_agent_id):\n    \"\"\"Record that agent_id is waiting for waiting_for_agent_id.\"\"\"\n    self.agent_graph[agent_id] = waiting_for_agent_id\n\ndef detect_deadlock(self):\n    \"\"\"Check dependency graph for cycles.\"\"\"\n    visited = set()\n    for agent in self.agent_graph:\n        if agent not in visited:\n            cycle = self._find_cycle(agent, set(), visited)\n            if cycle:\n                return cycle\n    return None\n```\n**Explanation**: Deadlock detection **logic exists** (dependency graph, cycle detection), but **dependency information collection is missing**. The system has no mechanism for agents to report `waiting_for_agent_id`. The example in `main()` uses hardcoded dependencies (`agent_A → agent_B → agent_C → agent_A`), not real agent telemetry.\n\n---\n\n### Verification 5 — ACP Runtime Monitoring  \n**Status**: PASS  \n**Evidence**:\n```python\n# watchdog_monitor.py\nSTALL_TIMEOUT = 120\nACP_STALL_TIMEOUT = 180  # Longer timeout for ACP sessions\n\ndef detect_stall(session):\n    inactivity = (datetime.utcnow() - session.last_activity).total_seconds()\n    timeout = ACP_STALL_TIMEOUT if session.runtime_type == 'acp' else STALL_TIMEOUT\n    if session.state == \"running\" and inactivity > timeout:\n        return True\n    return False\n```\n```python\n# watchdog_learning_adapter.py\nif runtime_type == 'acp':\n    pattern_key = f\"runtime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck\"\n```\n**Explanation**: ACP monitoring is **fully implemented** with distinct timeouts (180s vs 120s) and correct pattern‑key emission.\n\n---\n\n### Verification 6 — Watchdog Registration Flow  \n**Status**: PARTIAL  \n**Evidence**:  \n**AGENTS.md** defines:\n```markdown\nregister_watchdog(\n  session_id=\"validator_A_session\",\n  run_id=\"validator_A_run\",\n  task_description=\"validate batch items\",\n  expected_runtime=8,\n  model=\"deepseek‑reasoner\",\n  runtime_type=\"subagent\"\n)\n```\n**Watchdog interface matches**:\n```python\ndef register_session(self, session_id, run_id, task_description,\n                     expected_runtime, model, runtime_type='subagent'):\n```\n**Mismatch**: The registration procedure in AGENTS.md is **documentation only**. There is **no automatic capture** of `session_id` and `run_id` from spawned sub‑agents. The watchdog is a standalone Python script, not integrated with OpenClaw’s session‑spawning mechanism.\n\n---\n\n### 📊 Final Summary Table\n\n| Capability | Status | Notes |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| Watchdog incident emission | PASS | Correctly writes to ERRORS.md with full telemetry |\n| Learning loop trigger | PARTIAL | Simulation stub only; no actual skill invocation |\n| Index update pipeline | FAIL | Pipeline breaks after ERRORS.md; no automatic rebuild |\n| Deadlock detection | PARTIAL | Logic exists but dependency collection missing |\n| ACP runtime monitoring | PASS | Different timeouts, correct pattern‑keys |\n| Watchdog registration flow | PARTIAL | Interface matches but no integration with session spawning |\n\n---\n\n### 🚨 SYSTEM STATUS: REQUIRES FIXES\n\n**Critical gaps identified**:\n\n1. **Learning‑loop automation broken** – Incidents are logged but never processed for learning extraction or guardrail promotion.\n2. **Deadlock detection non‑operational** – No mechanism for agents to report dependencies (`waiting_for_agent_id`).\n3. **Watchdog‑session integration missing** – Registration procedure exists only on paper; no automatic capture of `session_id`/`run_id`.\n4. **Index/REPORT.md not auto‑updated** – Learning store remains stale after incidents.\n\n**Operational readiness**: ❌ **Not production‑ready**. The system has correct architectural components but critical integration points are unimplemented or simulated.\n\n**Recommendation**: Before production use, implement:\n- Actual `sessions_spawn` call to `error-learning-loop` from watchdog\n- Agent dependency reporting mechanism\n- Integration with OpenClaw’s session spawning to capture `session_id`/`run_id`\n- Automatic INDEX.md/REPORT.md rebuild after incidents"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":28282,"output":1984,"cacheRead":48512,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78778,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772740510216}}
{"type":"message","id":"4990551d","parentId":"25ac10e7","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:58:42.884Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 14:58 EST] Apply critical fixes to make the watchdog + learning system production-ready. \n\n \n\nDo NOT create new skills. Modify existing files only. \n\n \n\nTarget gaps from audit: \n\n- V2 Learning loop trigger is a stub \n\n- V3 Index update pipeline is broken \n\n- V6 Registration is documentation-only \n\n- V4 Deadlock has no real dependency intake \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nFIX 1 — Make the pipeline automatic (BLOCKER) \n\nGoal: After watchdog appends an incident, the learning store must update automatically. \n\n \n\nImplement in skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py: \n\n \n\nA) After append_to_errors(incident), do BOTH: \n\n 1) Try to invoke error-learning-loop (preferred) \n\n 2) Always run a fallback index rebuild (guaranteed) \n\n \n\nPreferred invocation: \n\n- If OpenClaw provides sessions_spawn / skill execution, implement it. \n\n- If not available, clearly mark it as optional. \n\n \n\nFallback (MUST IMPLEMENT): \n\n- Execute: python3 <workspace>/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py <workspace> \n\n so that <workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md and REPORT.md are always rebuilt. \n\n \n\nThis guarantees the retrieval layer stays fresh even if skill invocation is unavailable. \n\n \n\nAdd guardrails: \n\n- Do not rebuild index more than once per incident. \n\n- If multiple incidents arrive quickly, debounce rebuild (e.g., 30–60s). \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nFIX 2 — Implement a real “learning-loop trigger” when possible \n\nReplace trigger_learning_loop() stub with an actual action. \n\n \n\nMinimum requirement: \n\n- If direct skill invocation is not possible, trigger_learning_loop() must call the fallback update_index.py (and return status). \n\n \n\nReturn a status object: \n\n{ triggered: true/false, method: \"skill\"|\"fallback\", error: <optional> } \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nFIX 3 — Make Watchdog Registration operational (MVP) \n\nUpdate AGENTS.md \"Watchdog Registration Procedure\" so it is executable, not just policy. \n\n \n\nAdd this requirement to the sub-agent instructions (delegation template): \n\n- Every delegated sub-agent must include in its Handoff Report: \n\n - session_id (or runtime session name) \n\n - run_id (or equivalent run identifier) \n\n - lastActivityAt if available \n\n - progress marker (what step it reached) \n\n \n\nThen update the procedure: \n\n- After spawning, parse the Handoff Report to extract session_id/run_id \n\n- Register the sub-agent with agent-watchdog using those values \n\n- Start monitoring \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nFIX 4 — Make deadlock detection operational without explicit dependencies (MVP) \n\nKeep the existing dependency-graph cycle detection, but add a second detection mode: \n\n \n\nDEADLOCK_STARVATION: \n\n- If N agents are running and \n\n- No heartbeat / no output / no lastActivity change for > DEADLOCK_TIMEOUT (e.g., 180s) \n\n- AND main is blocked waiting on their completion \n\n→ classify as deadlock starvation \n\n \n\nEmit incident: \n\nmulti_agent|DEADLOCK|progress_starvation|agents_no_progress \n\n \n\nTelemetry: \n\nagents_involved, deadlock_timeout, recovery_strategy, success \n\n \n\nRecovery: \n\nLevel 1: request progress update from all agents \n\nLevel 2: nudge \"continue\" to each \n\nLevel 3: restart the smallest-risk agent or relaunch one validator batch \n\n \n\nAppend this incident to <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md and run the same learning trigger + fallback rebuild. \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nVALIDATION REQUIRED (must perform and show results) \n\nAfter implementing: \n\n \n\n1) Simulate a watchdog incident and show: \n\n- ERRORS.md got a new entry \n\n- update_index.py was executed (or skill invoked) \n\n- INDEX.md timestamp updated \n\n \n\n2) Simulate deadlock starvation for 2–3 agents and show: \n\n- incident appended \n\n- INDEX.md updated \n\n \n\nOutput a concise report with: \n\n- Files changed + what changed \n\n- Proof that INDEX.md updates automatically after a watchdog incident \n\n- Proof that deadlock starvation emits incidents and updates index"}],"timestamp":1772740722867}}
