{"type":"message","id":"89b52eba","parentId":"fcc54894","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:59:23.806Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ahora necesito modificar `trigger_learning_loop` para que realmente ejecute algo. Primero verificaré si hay algún mecanismo disponible para invocar skills en OpenClaw. Según la documentación, podría usar `sessions_spawn` con `runtime=\"subagent\"` y `agentId` correspondiente. Pero necesito ver qué agents están disponibles. Sin embargo, para el MVP, implementaré el fallback: ejecutar el script `update_index.py`. Eso garantizará que INDEX.md y REPORT.md se actualicen.\n\nTambién necesito agregar lógica de debouncing para no reconstruir el índice repetidamente. Añadiré un timestamp de última reconstrucción.\n\nPrimero, voy a modificar `watchdog_orchestrator.py`. Necesito agregar imports para subprocess y time, y luego implementar el fallback. También necesito agregar el modo de detección de deadlock por starvation.\n\nVoy a crear una función `_rebuild_index_fallback()` que ejecute el script de Python. También modificaré `append_to_errors` para que llame al trigger, y el trigger intentará invocar el skill y si no puede, usará el fallback.\n\nAdemás, necesito agregar el deadlock starvation detection. Agregaré un método `detect_starvation_deadlock` que verifique si múltiples agentes no han tenido actividad por más de DEADLOCK_TIMEOUT.\n\nAhora, también necesito actualizar AGENTS.md para hacer la registración operativa. Agregaré instrucciones de que los sub-agentes deben incluir session_id y run_id en su Handoff Report, y que el main agent debe parsearlos y registrar con el watchdog.\n\nSin embargo, dado que el watchdog es un script Python independiente, necesito pensar cómo se integraría con el main agent. Tal vez el main agent pueda llamar al script de watchdog con los parámetros. Pero para el MVP, puedo hacer que el watchdog monitoree sesiones activas a través de la lista de sesiones de OpenClaw. Pero eso es más complejo. Para el MVP, puedo mantener el stub de registración pero al menos hacer que el procedimiento sea más concreto: \"Después de spawn, ejecutar script de watchdog con parámetros\".\n\nVoy a enfocarme primero en las correcciones de código del watchdog.\n\nComencemos modificando `watchdog_orchestrator.py`. Primero, leeré el archivo completo para entender la estructura.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_xTM8KW5B1hHO35FPsGGBdqIq","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":27048,"output":1141,"cacheRead":50560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78749,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772740736094}}
{"type":"message","id":"39b7ace7","parentId":"89b52eba","timestamp":"2026-03-05T19:59:23.865Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_xTM8KW5B1hHO35FPsGGBdqIq","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nagent‑watchdog orchestrator – Integrates stall detection, recovery escalation,\ndeadlock detection, ACP monitoring, and learning‑loop incident reporting.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport sys\nimport time\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Import local modules\nsys.path.append(str(Path(__file__).parent))\nfrom watchdog_monitor import Session, detect_stall, monitor\nfrom watchdog_recovery import recovery_action\nfrom watchdog_learning_adapter import generate_incident\n\n# Constants\nWORKSPACE = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'\nERRORS_PATH = WORKSPACE / '.learnings' / 'ERRORS.md'\nLEARNING_LOOP_SKILL = WORKSPACE / 'skills' / 'error-learning-loop' / 'SKILL.md'\n\nclass AgentWatchdog:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.sessions = {}  # session_id -> Session\n        self.agent_graph = {}  # agent_id -> waiting_for_agent_id\n        self.stall_timeout = 120  # seconds\n        self.monitor_interval = 30\n    \n    def register_session(self, session_id, run_id, task_description,\n                         expected_runtime, model, runtime_type='subagent'):\n        \"\"\"Register a session for monitoring.\"\"\"\n        session = Session(session_id)\n        session.run_id = run_id\n        session.task_description = task_description\n        session.expected_runtime = expected_runtime\n        session.model = model\n        session.runtime_type = runtime_type\n        session.start_time = datetime.utcnow()\n        session.last_activity = datetime.utcnow()\n        session.state = 'running'\n        \n        self.sessions[session_id] = session\n        print(f\"[Watchdog] Registered session {session_id} ({runtime_type})\")\n        return session\n    \n    def update_activity(self, session_id):\n        \"\"\"Update last activity timestamp for a session.\"\"\"\n        if session_id in self.sessions:\n            self.sessions[session_id].last_activity = datetime.utcnow()\n    \n    def detect_stalls(self):\n        \"\"\"Check all registered sessions for stalls.\"\"\"\n        stalls = []\n        for session_id, session in self.sessions.items():\n            if detect_stall(session):\n                stalls.append(session)\n        return stalls\n    \n    def perform_recovery(self, session, attempt):\n        \"\"\"Execute recovery escalation.\"\"\"\n        action = recovery_action(attempt)\n        print(f\"[Recovery] Attempt {attempt}: {action} on session {session.session_id}\")\n        # Simulate action\n        if action == 'nudge_continue':\n            # Send continue signal\n            pass\n        elif action == 'cancel_and_resume':\n            # Cancel run and resume\n            pass\n        elif action == 'relaunch_agent':\n            # Close session and relaunch\n            pass\n        return action\n    \n    def emit_incident(self, session, stall_duration, recovery_level, success):\n        \"\"\"Generate incident and append to ERRORS.md.\"\"\"\n        incident = generate_incident(\n            session.model,\n            stall_duration,\n            recovery_level,\n            success\n        )\n        # Add extra telemetry fields\n        incident['task_type'] = session.task_description\n        incident['items_count'] = getattr(session, 'items_count', 0)\n        incident['runtime_type'] = session.runtime_type\n        \n        # Append to ERRORS.md\n        self.append_to_errors(incident)\n        \n        # Trigger error-learning-loop (simulated)\n        self.trigger_learning_loop(incident)\n        \n        return incident\n    \n    def append_to_errors(self, incident):\n        \"\"\"Append incident to ERRORS.md following the pattern-key format.\"\"\"\n        if not ERRORS_PATH.exists():\n            return\n        \n        with open(ERRORS_PATH, 'a', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            f.write(f\"\\n### Pattern-Key: {incident['pattern_key']}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **First Occurrence**: {incident['timestamp'][:10]}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Latest Occurrence**: {incident['timestamp'][:10]}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Count**: 1\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Type**: stall\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Severity**: S2\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Model**: {incident.get('model', 'unknown')}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Stall Duration**: {incident.get('stall_duration', 0)} seconds\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Recovery Level**: {incident.get('recovery_level', 0)}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Success**: {incident.get('success', False)}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Runtime Type**: {incident.get('runtime_type', 'subagent')}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Task Type**: {incident.get('task_type', 'unknown')}\\n\")\n            f.write(f\"- **Items Count**: {incident.get('items_count', 0)}\\n\")\n            f.write(\"\\n\")\n        print(f\"[Watchdog] Incident appended to {ERRORS_PATH}\")\n    \n    def trigger_learning_loop(self, incident):\n        \"\"\"Invoke the error-learning-loop skill.\"\"\"\n        # In production, this would spawn the skill via sessions_spawn\n        print(f\"[Watchdog] Triggering error-learning-loop for {incident['pattern_key']}\")\n        # Simulate call to error-learning-loop\n        # subprocess.run([...])\n    \n    # Deadlock detection methods\n    def add_dependency(self, agent_id, waiting_for_agent_id):\n        \"\"\"Record that agent_id is waiting for waiting_for_agent_id.\"\"\"\n        self.agent_graph[agent_id] = waiting_for_agent_id\n    \n    def detect_deadlock(self):\n        \"\"\"Check dependency graph for cycles.\"\"\"\n        visited = set()\n        for agent in self.agent_graph:\n            if agent not in visited:\n                cycle = self._find_cycle(agent, set(), visited)\n                if cycle:\n                    return cycle\n        return None\n    \n    def _find_cycle(self, agent, path, visited):\n        \"\"\"DFS to find cycle.\"\"\"\n        if agent in path:\n            # Cycle detected\n            cycle_start = path.index(agent)\n            return list(path[cycle_start:]) + [agent]\n        if agent in visited:\n            return None\n        \n        path.add(agent)\n        visited.add(agent)\n        \n        next_agent = self.agent_graph.get(agent)\n        if next_agent:\n            cycle = self._find_cycle(next_agent, path, visited)\n            if cycle:\n                return cycle\n        \n        path.remove(agent)\n        return None\n    \n    def handle_deadlock(self, cycle):\n        \"\"\"Attempt deadlock recovery.\"\"\"\n        print(f\"[Deadlock] Cycle detected: {cycle}\")\n        # Level 1: request progress update\n        for agent in cycle:\n            print(f\"[Deadlock] Requesting progress update from {agent}\")\n        \n        # Level 2: force resolution of one edge\n        if len(cycle) > 1:\n            broken_edge = (cycle[0], cycle[1])\n            print(f\"[Deadlock] Breaking dependency {broken_edge}\")\n            self.agent_graph[broken_edge[0]] = None\n        \n        # Level 3: restart one agent\n        agent_to_restart = cycle[0]\n        print(f\"[Deadlock] Restarting agent {agent_to_restart}\")\n        \n        # Emit deadlock incident\n        incident = {\n            'pattern_key': 'multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting',\n            'timestamp': datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n            'cycle_size': len(cycle),\n            'agents_involved': cycle,\n            'recovery_strategy': 'edge_break_and_restart',\n            'success': True\n        }\n        self.append_to_errors(incident)\n        self.trigger_learning_loop(incident)\n        \n        return incident\n    \n    def run_monitoring_cycle(self):\n        \"\"\"Main monitoring loop.\"\"\"\n        print(\"[Watchdog] Starting monitoring cycle\")\n        # Detect stalls\n        stalls = self.detect_stalls()\n        for session in stalls:\n            stall_duration = (datetime.utcnow() - session.last_activity).total_seconds()\n            print(f\"[Watchdog] Stall detected in session {session.session_id} ({stall_duration}s)\")\n            \n            # Recovery escalation\n            for attempt in range(1, 4):\n                action = self.perform_recovery(session, attempt)\n                # Simulate recovery success after third attempt\n                success = (attempt == 3)\n                if success:\n                    incident = self.emit_incident(session, stall_duration, attempt, success)\n                    print(f\"[Watchdog] Recovery successful, incident {incident['pattern_key']}\")\n                    break\n                time.sleep(1)  # Simulate delay between attempts\n        \n        # Deadlock detection\n        cycle = self.detect_deadlock()\n        if cycle:\n            self.handle_deadlock(cycle)\n        \n        print(\"[Watchdog] Monitoring cycle complete\")\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Example usage.\"\"\"\n    watchdog = AgentWatchdog()\n    \n    # Register example sessions\n    watchdog.register_session(\n        session_id=\"validator_A_session\",\n        run_id=\"validator_A_run\",\n        task_description=\"validate batch items\",\n        expected_runtime=8,\n        model=\"deepseek-reasoner\",\n        runtime_type=\"subagent\"\n    )\n    \n    watchdog.register_session(\n        session_id=\"acp_agent_1\",\n        run_id=\"acp_run_1\",\n        task_description=\"ACP processing task\",\n        expected_runtime=10,\n        model=\"gpt-4\",\n        runtime_type=\"acp\"\n    )\n    \n    # Simulate a dependency (deadlock scenario)\n    watchdog.add_dependency(\"agent_A\", \"agent_B\")\n    watchdog.add_dependency(\"agent_B\", \"agent_C\")\n    watchdog.add_dependency(\"agent_C\", \"agent_A\")\n    \n    # Run one monitoring cycle\n    watchdog.run_monitoring_cycle()\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772740763831}}
