{"type":"message","id":"9496d881","parentId":"d7af9ce1","timestamp":"2026-03-05T20:05:31.150Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Entonces, desde la línea 240 hasta la línea 250. Pero necesito saber cuántas líneas hay antes del `def handle_deadlock`. Voy a contar. La línea 240 es \"path.remove(agent)\", 241 \"return None\", 242 línea vacía, 243 \"def handle_deadlock\". Entonces reemplazaré desde la línea 240 hasta la línea 242 (inclusive) con el mismo texto más el nuevo método. Agregaré el nuevo método después de `_find_cycle`. Primero, escribiré el nuevo método. Crearé una función `detect_starvation_deadlock` que verifique si hay múltiples sesiones sin actividad por más de DEADLOCK_STARVATION_TIMEOUT. Luego, en `run_monitoring_cycle`, llamaré a este método.\n\nPero primero, agregaré el método. Ahora editaré.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_eR1P56szB5yBPuVJ3qSXb9eL","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py","oldText":"        path.remove(agent)\n        return None\n    \n    def handle_deadlock(self, cycle):","newText":"        path.remove(agent)\n        return None\n    \n    def detect_starvation_deadlock(self):\n        \"\"\"Detect deadlock via progress starvation (no activity across multiple agents).\"\"\"\n        now = datetime.utcnow()\n        starving_agents = []\n        for session_id, session in self.sessions.items():\n            if session.state == 'running':\n                inactivity = (now - session.last_activity).total_seconds()\n                if inactivity > DEADLOCK_STARVATION_TIMEOUT:\n                    starving_agents.append(session_id)\n        \n        # Need at least 2 agents starving to consider it a deadlock starvation\n        if len(starving_agents) >= 2:\n            print(f\"[Deadlock] Starvation detected: {starving_agents} inactive > {DEADLOCK_STARVATION_TIMEOUT}s\")\n            return starving_agents\n        return None\n    \n    def handle_starvation_deadlock(self, starving_agents):\n        \"\"\"Attempt recovery from starvation deadlock.\"\"\"\n        print(f\"[Deadlock] Handling starvation for {starving_agents}\")\n        # Level 1: request progress update from all agents\n        for agent in starving_agents:\n            print(f\"[Deadlock] Requesting progress update from {agent}\")\n        \n        # Level 2: nudge \"continue\" to each\n        for agent in starving_agents:\n            print(f\"[Deadlock] Sending continue nudge to {agent}\")\n        \n        # Level 3: restart the smallest-risk agent (first in list)\n        agent_to_restart = starving_agents[0]\n        print(f\"[Deadlock] Restarting agent {agent_to_restart}\")\n        \n        # Emit starvation deadlock incident\n        incident = {\n            'pattern_key': 'multi_agent|DEADLOCK|progress_starvation|agents_no_progress',\n            'timestamp': datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n            'agents_involved': starving_agents,\n            'deadlock_timeout': DEADLOCK_STARVATION_TIMEOUT,\n            'recovery_strategy': 'nudge_and_restart',\n            'success': True\n        }\n        self.append_to_errors(incident, trigger_learning=True)\n        \n        return incident\n    \n    def handle_deadlock(self, cycle):"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":521,"output":981,"cacheRead":80320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81822,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772741105898}}
