de incidente a ERRORS.md con un pattern-key de prueba.\n2. Ejecutaré `update_index.py` y mostraré que INDEX.md se actualiza.\n3. Luego ejecutaré un script de prueba para deadlock starvation.\n\nPero también debo demostrar que el watchdog puede emitir incidentes automáticamente. Para eso, modificaré el script `watchdog_orchestrator.py` para agregar una bandera `--test-incident` que genere un incidente de prueba y salga. Luego ejecutaré ese comando.\n\nVoy a crear una función `test_incident` en el script. Pero para no complicar, simplemente puedo usar el script existente y modificar las fechas de sesiones para que parezcan stalled. Cambiaré `last_activity` a hace 300 segundos. Eso activará detección de stall. Lo haré modificando el script temporalmente. O puedo escribir un pequeño script aparte. Lo haré ahora.\n\nPrimero, crearé un script de prueba en el workspace temporal. Usaré `exec` para escribir un script Python que importe `AgentWatchdog`, cree una sesión con `last_activity` vieja, y ejecute `run_monitoring_cycle`. Luego mostrará si se agregó un incidente.\n\nPero necesito asegurarme de que el watchdog escriba en ERRORS.md. Dado que ERRORS.md ya existe, agregará una entrada. Luego verificaremos que INDEX.md se actualizó comparando timestamps.\n\nAhora, voy a crear el script de prueba. Primero, necesito importar desde el directorio correcto. Lo haré en el directorio de skills. Vamos a escribir el script. Usaré `write` para crear un archivo temporal.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ftRG6k8dRb4131UzS2Lc0pnB","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/test_watchdog.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTest watchdog incident emission and index auto‑rebuild.\n\"\"\"\nimport sys\nimport time\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nsys.path.append(str(Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace' / 'skills' / 'agent-watchdog' / 'scripts'))\n\nfrom watchdog_orchestrator import AgentWatchdog\nfrom watchdog_monitor import Session\n\ndef main():\n    workspace = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'\n    errors_path = workspace / '.learnings' / 'ERRORS.md'\n    index_path = workspace / '.learnings' / 'INDEX.md'\n    \n    print(\"=== Watchdog Incident Emission Test ===\")\n    print(f\"ERRORS.md exists: {errors_path.exists()}\")\n    print(f\"INDEX.md exists: {index_path.exists()}\")\n    \n    # Record current index timestamp\n    if index_path.exists():\n        index_mtime_before = index_path.stat().st_mtime\n        print(f\"INDEX.md mtime before: {datetime.fromtimestamp(index_mtime_before)}\")\n    \n    # Create watchdog instance\n    watchdog = AgentWatchdog()\n    \n    # Register a session with last_activity far in the past (definitely stalled)\n    session = watchdog.register_session(\n        session_id=\"test_stalled_session\",\n        run_id=\"test_run_001\",\n        task_description=\"test watchdog stall detection\",\n        expected_runtime=5,\n        model=\"test-model\",\n        runtime_type=\"subagent\"\n    )\n    # Manually set last_activity to 5 minutes ago\n    session.last_activity = datetime.utcnow() - timedelta(seconds=500)\n    print(f\"Registered stalled session, last_activity: {session.last_activity}\")\n    \n    # Run one monitoring cycle\n    print(\"\\n--- Running monitoring cycle ---\")\n    watchdog.run_monitoring_cycle()\n    \n    # Check if ERRORS.md was updated\n    print(\"\\n--- Checking results ---\")\n    if errors_path.exists():\n        with open(errors_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            content = f.read()\n            if 'test_stalled_session' in content:\n                print(\"✅ Incident appended to ERRORS.md\")\n            else:\n                print(\"❌ Incident NOT found in ERRORS.md\")\n    \n    # Check if INDEX.md was rebuilt\n    if index_path.exists():\n        index_mtime_after = index_path.stat().st_mtime\n        print(f\"INDEX.md mtime after: {datetime.fromtimestamp(index_mtime_after)}\")\n        if index_mtime_after > index_mtime_before:\n            print(\"✅ INDEX.md was rebuilt (timestamp updated)\")\n        else:\n            print(\"⚠️  INDEX.md timestamp unchanged (may be debounced)\")\n    \n    # Test deadlock starvation detection\n    print(\"\\n=== Deadlock Starvation Test ===\")\n    watchdog2 = AgentWatchdog()\n    # Register two sessions with old activity\n    s1 = watchdog2.register_session(\"agent1\", \"run1\", \"task1\", 10, \"model\", \"subagent\")\n    s2 = watchdog2.register_session(\"agent2\", \"run2\", \"task2\", 10, \"model\", \"subagent\")\n    s1.last_activity"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1772741271527,"errorMessage":"Request was aborted"}}
