{"type":"message","id":"2b7114e5","parentId":"8b0bbbd0","timestamp":"2026-03-05T20:08:43.164Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 14:58 EST] Apply critical fixes to make the watchdog + learning system production-ready. \n\n \n\nDo NOT create new skills. Modify existing files only. \n\n \n\nTarget gaps from audit: \n\n- V2 Learning loop trigger is a stub \n\n- V3 Index update pipeline is broken \n\n- V6 Registration is documentation-only \n\n- V4 Deadlock has no real dependency intake \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nFIX 1 — Make the pipeline automatic (BLOCKER) \n\nGoal: After watchdog appends an incident, the learning store must update automatically. \n\n \n\nImplement in skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py: \n\n \n\nA) After append_to_errors(incident), do BOTH: \n\n 1) Try to invoke error-learning-loop (preferred) \n\n 2) Always run a fallback index rebuild (guaranteed) \n\n \n\nPreferred invocation: \n\n- If OpenClaw provides sessions_spawn / skill execution, implement it. \n\n- If not available, clearly mark it as optional. \n\n \n\nFallback (MUST IMPLEMENT): \n\n- Execute: python3 <workspace>/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py <workspace> \n\n so that <workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md and REPORT.md are always rebuilt. \n\n \n\nThis guarantees the retrieval layer stays fresh even if skill invocation is unavailable. \n\n \n\nAdd guardrails: \n\n- Do not rebuild index more than once per incident. \n\n- If multiple incidents arrive quickly, debounce rebuild (e.g., 30–60s). \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nFIX 2 — Implement a real “learning-loop trigger” when possible \n\nReplace trigger_learning_loop() stub with an actual action. \n\n \n\nMinimum requirement: \n\n- If direct skill invocation is not possible, trigger_learning_loop() must call the fallback update_index.py (and return status). \n\n \n\nReturn a status object: \n\n{ triggered: true/false, method: \"skill\"|\"fallback\", error: <optional> } \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nFIX 3 — Make Watchdog Registration operational (MVP) \n\nUpdate AGENTS.md \"Watchdog Registration Procedure\" so it is executable, not just policy. \n\n \n\nAdd this requirement to the sub-agent instructions (delegation template): \n\n- Every delegated sub-agent must include in its Handoff Report: \n\n - session_id (or runtime session name) \n\n - run_id (or equivalent run identifier) \n\n - lastActivityAt if available \n\n - progress marker (what step it reached) \n\n \n\nThen update the procedure: \n\n- After spawning, parse the Handoff Report to extract session_id/run_id \n\n- Register the sub-agent with agent-watchdog using those values \n\n- Start monitoring \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nFIX 4 — Make deadlock detection operational without explicit dependencies (MVP) \n\nKeep the existing dependency-graph cycle detection, but add a second detection mode: \n\n \n\nDEADLOCK_STARVATION: \n\n- If N agents are running and \n\n- No heartbeat / no output / no lastActivity change for > DEADLOCK_TIMEOUT (e.g., 180s) \n\n- AND main is blocked waiting on their completion \n\n→ classify as deadlock starvation \n\n \n\nEmit incident: \n\nmulti_agent|DEADLOCK|progress_starvation|agents_no_progress \n\n \n\nTelemetry: \n\nagents_involved, deadlock_timeout, recovery_strategy, success \n\n \n\nRecovery: \n\nLevel 1: request progress update from all agents \n\nLevel 2: nudge \"continue\" to each \n\nLevel 3: restart the smallest-risk agent or relaunch one validator batch \n\n \n\nAppend this incident to <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md and run the same learning trigger + fallback rebuild. \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nVALIDATION REQUIRED (must perform and show results) \n\nAfter implementing: \n\n \n\n1) Simulate a watchdog incident and show: \n\n- ERRORS.md got a new entry \n\n- update_index.py was executed (or skill invoked) \n\n- INDEX.md timestamp updated \n\n \n\n2) Simulate deadlock starvation for 2–3 agents and show: \n\n- incident appended \n\n- INDEX.md updated \n\n \n\nOutput a concise report with: \n\n- Files changed + what changed \n\n- Proof that INDEX.md updates automatically after a watchdog incident \n\n- Proof that deadlock starvation emits incidents and updates index"}],"timestamp":1772741323154}}
