{"type":"message","id":"a2fce756","parentId":"2336783f","timestamp":"2026-03-05T20:11:13.822Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"El timestamp actual es \"2026-03-05 13:05:47\". Ahora crearé el script de prueba. Primero, necesito saber la estructura exacta de las clases para importarlas correctamente. Reviso los imports en watchdog_orchestrator.py. Veo que importa desde watchdog_monitor, watchdog_recovery, watchdog_learning_adapter. También define la clase AgentWatchdog. Para simplificar, puedo ejecutar el script principal modificando algunos parámetros. Podría modificar temporalmente el archivo watchdog_orchestrator.py para forzar condiciones de prueba, pero prefiero no modificar el archivo de producción. Crearé un script de prueba que importe las clases necesarias.\n\nPero el archivo watchdog_orchestrator.py define la clase AgentWatchdog dentro del mismo archivo, así que puedo importarla desde ahí. Sin embargo, si ejecuto el script directamente, ejecutará su función main() que registra sesiones de ejemplo. Esa función main() ya registra sesiones y ejecuta un ciclo de monitoreo. Pero las sesiones tienen last_activity reciente, así que no detectará stalls. Necesito modificar las sesiones después de registrarlas.\n\nHaré lo siguiente: crearé un script test_validation.py que importe AgentWatchdog desde watchdog_orchestrator, registre sesiones, manipule last_activity, y ejecute run_monitoring_cycle. Luego capturaré los cambios.\n\nPrimero, creo el script.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_3bCl6M31giREgWb0Yy45eHXV","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/test_validation.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTest validation for watchdog + learning system.\nSimulates:\n1. Watchdog stall incident\n2. Deadlock starvation incident\n\"\"\"\n\nimport sys\nimport os\nimport time\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Add parent directory to path\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).parent))\n\n# Import the watchdog orchestrator\nfrom watchdog_orchestrator import AgentWatchdog\nfrom watchdog_monitor import Session\nfrom watchdog_learning_adapter import generate_incident, generate_deadlock_incident\n\ndef backup_file(path):\n    \"\"\"Create backup of a file.\"\"\"\n    if path.exists():\n        backup = path.with_suffix('.bak')\n        import shutil\n        shutil.copy2(path, backup)\n        return backup\n    return None\n\ndef restore_file(path, backup):\n    \"\"\"Restore file from backup.\"\"\"\n    if backup and backup.exists():\n        import shutil\n        shutil.copy2(backup, path)\n        backup.unlink()\n        return True\n    return False\n\ndef get_file_timestamp(path):\n    \"\"\"Get the last modified time of a file.\"\"\"\n    if path.exists():\n        return datetime.fromtimestamp(path.stat().st_mtime)\n    return None\n\ndef test_watchdog_stall():\n    \"\"\"Test 1: Simulate watchdog stall incident.\"\"\"\n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n    print(\"TEST 1: Watchdog Stall Incident\")\n    print(\"=\"*60)\n    \n    # Backup files\n    workspace = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'\n    errors_path = workspace / '.learnings' / 'ERRORS.md'\n    index_path = workspace / '.learnings' / 'INDEX.md'\n    \n    errors_backup = backup_file(errors_path)\n    index_backup = backup_file(index_path)\n    \n    try:\n        # Get initial state\n        initial_index_time = get_file_timestamp(index_path)\n        print(f\"Initial INDEX.md timestamp: {initial_index_time}\")\n        \n        # Create watchdog instance\n        watchdog = AgentWatchdog()\n        \n        # Register a session and manually set last_activity to be stale\n        session = watchdog.register_session(\n            session_id=\"test_stall_session\",\n            run_id=\"test_stall_run\",\n            task_description=\"test validation stall\",\n            expected_runtime=5,\n            model=\"deepseek-reasoner\",\n            runtime_type=\"subagent\"\n        )\n        \n        # Force stale activity (2.5 minutes ago, exceeding 120s timeout)\n        stale_time = datetime.utcnow() - timedelta(seconds=150)\n        session.last_activity = stale_time\n        \n        print(f\"Registered session with stale last_activity: {stale_time}\")\n        \n        # Run monitoring cycle (should detect stall and emit incident)\n        print(\"Running monitoring cycle...\")\n        watchdog.run_monitoring_cycle()\n        \n        # Check if ERRORS.md was updated\n        if errors_path.exists():\n            with open(errors_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                content = f.read()\n                if 'model|STALL|deepseek-reasoner|no_response|runtime_stuck' in content:\n                    print(\"✅ Stall incident appended to ERRORS.md\")\n                    # Find the new entry\n                    lines = content.split('\\n')\n                    for i, line in enumerate(lines[-20:]):\n                        if 'Pattern-Key:' in line and 'deepseek-reasoner' in line:\n                            print(f\"   Found: {line.strip()}\")\n                else:\n                    print(\"❌ Stall incident NOT found in ERRORS.md\")\n        \n        # Check if INDEX.md was rebuilt (timestamp should be newer)\n        time.sleep(1)  # Small delay for file system\n        final_index_time = get_file_timestamp(index_path)\n        print(f\"Final INDEX.md timestamp: {final_index_time}\")\n        \n        if final_index_time and initial_index_time:\n            if final_index_time > initial_index_time:\n                print(\"✅ INDEX.md timestamp updated (automatic rebuild)\")\n            else:\n                print(\"⚠️  INDEX.md timestamp NOT updated\")\n        else:\n            print(\"⚠️  Could not compare timestamps\")\n        \n        return True\n        \n    finally:\n        # Restore backups (optional for test, but keep changes for verification)\n        # restore_file(errors_path, errors_backup)\n        # restore_file(index_path, index_backup)\n        pass\n\ndef test_deadlock_starvation():\n    \"\"\"Test 2: Simulate deadlock starvation incident.\"\"\"\n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n    print(\"TEST 2: Deadlock Starvation Incident\")\n    print(\"=\"*60)\n    \n    workspace = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'\n    errors_path = workspace / '.learnings' / 'ERRORS.md'\n    index_path = workspace / '.learnings' / 'INDEX.md'\n    \n    # Get initial state (after first test)\n    initial_index_time = get_file_timestamp(index_path)\n    print(f\"Initial INDEX.md timestamp: {initial_index_time}\")\n    \n    # Create watchdog instance\n    watchdog = AgentWatchdog()\n    \n    # Register multiple sessions and make them all stale\n    sessions = []\n    for i in range(3):\n        session = watchdog.register_session(\n            session_id=f\"test_starvation_{i}\",\n            run_id=f\"test_starvation_run_{i}\",\n            task_description=f\"starvation test {i}\",\n            expected_runtime=10,\n            model=\"gpt-4\",\n            runtime_type=\"subagent\"\n        )\n        # Force very stale activity (3.5 minutes ago, exceeding 180s starvation timeout)\n        stale_time = datetime.utcnow() - timedelta(seconds=190)\n        session.last_activity = stale_time\n        sessions.append(session)\n        print(f\"Registered session {session.session_id} with stale activity\")\n    \n    # Run monitoring cycle (should detect starvation deadlock)\n    print(\"Running monitoring cycle...\")\n    watchdog.run_monitoring_cycle()\n    \n    # Check if ERRORS.md was updated with starvation incident\n    if errors_path.exists():\n        with open(errors_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            content = f.read()\n            if 'multi_agent|DEADLOCK|progress_starvation|agents_no_progress' in content:\n                print(\"✅ Starvation deadlock incident a