{"type":"message","id":"a95a33db","parentId":"036b50f6","timestamp":"2026-03-05T20:58:20.634Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 15:48 EST] Apply the final hardening improvements to the existing system (agent-watchdog + error-learning-loop integration). \n\n \n\nThis is the LAST change set. Keep it minimal, surgical, and production-focused. \n\n \n\nDo NOT create new skills. Modify existing files only. \n\nDo NOT refactor unrelated code. \n\nAfter implementing, run the validation steps and report results with evidence. \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nIMPROVEMENT 1 — Incident Rate Limiting (Prevent log explosion) \n\n \n\nProblem: \n\nIf a model stalls repeatedly, watchdog may append too many near-duplicate incidents, bloating .learnings/ERRORS.md and degrading learning signal quality. \n\n \n\nGoal: \n\nAdd a rate limiter so that the watchdog will not append more than N incidents per Pattern-Key per time window. \n\n \n\nRequirements: \n\n1) Implement rate limiting in: \n\nskills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py \n\n \n\n2) Policy: \n\n- MAX_INCIDENTS_PER_PATTERN_PER_HOUR = 5 (default) \n\n- WINDOW_SECONDS = 3600 \n\n \n\n3) Behavior: \n\n- Before append_to_errors(incident), check if incident['pattern_key'] has already been logged >= MAX within the last hour. \n\n- If over limit: \n\n - Do NOT append a new entry. \n\n - Instead, update a lightweight counter in memory (or a small local cache) and emit a console log: \n\n \"[Watchdog] Rate limit hit for <pattern_key> — skipped append.\" \n\n - Still allow index rebuild debouncing logic to proceed only if there was a real append (avoid churn). \n\n \n\n4) Implementation details: \n\n- Add a small local cache file (allowed) under: \n\n<workspace>/.learnings/.watchdog_rate_limit.json \n\nStructure example: \n\n{ \n\n \"pattern_key\": [ \n\n \"2026-03-05T19:10:00Z\", \n\n \"2026-03-05T19:15:00Z\" \n\n ] \n\n} \n\n- Purge timestamps older than WINDOW_SECONDS on each check. \n\n- Ensure concurrency safety using the existing rebuild_lock or a dedicated lock. \n\n \n\n5) Validation: \n\n- Simulate 6 incidents with same pattern_key within 1 hour. \n\n- Confirm only 5 appended to ERRORS.md and the 6th was skipped with log evidence. \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nIMPROVEMENT 2 — Watchdog Self-Protection (Detect watchdog failure) \n\n \n\nProblem: \n\nIf the watchdog orchestrator itself crashes or errors, no one reports it, and monitoring silently stops. \n\n \n\nGoal: \n\nAdd a self-protection mechanism so that watchdog failures produce learnable incidents and keep monitoring resilient. \n\n \n\nRequirements: \n\n1) Wrap the main watchdog loop (monitor → detect → recover → emit) with try/except: \n\n- On exception, create a watchdog failure incident: \n\npattern_key: watchdog|FAILURE|orchestrator|runtime_error \n\n \n\nTelemetry fields: \n\npattern_key \n\ntimestamp \n\nerror_type \n\nerror_message (trim to <= 200 chars) \n\nstack_hint (optional, short) \n\nruntime_type (if known) \n\nsessions_tracked_count \n\nsuccess=false \n\n \n\n2) Persist this incident: \n\n- Append to <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md (rate limiting should also apply here) \n\n- Trigger learning pipeline (trigger_learning_loop → fallback rebuild) \n\n \n\n3) Recovery: \n\n- After logging the watchdog failure incident, restart the monitoring loop once (single retry). \n\n- Prevent infinite loops: \n\n - MAX_WATCHDOG_SELF_RESTARTS = 1 per process run \n\n - If exceeded, exit gracefully with a clear log message. \n\n \n\n4) Validation: \n\n- Force an exception intentionally (e.g., pass invalid session object or simulate missing file) in a test harness. \n\n- Confirm: \n\n - incident written with pattern_key watchdog|FAILURE|orchestrator|runtime_error \n\n - INDEX.md updated (via fallback) \n\n - watchdog attempts exactly one self-restart \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nPOST-IMPLEMENTATION VALIDATION (Must perform) \n\n \n\nAfter implementing both improvements, run and show evidence for: \n\n \n\nTest A — Rate limiting \n\n- Generate 6 incidents for same pattern_key within 1 hour \n\n- Evidence: \n\n - ERRORS.md only has 5 new entries \n\n - console log shows rate limit skip for the 6th \n\n - rate limit cache file updated \n\n \n\nTest B — Self-protection \n\n- Trigger a controlled watchdog exception \n\n- Evidence: \n\n - ERRORS.md includes watchdog|FAILURE|orchestrator|runtime_error \n\n - INDEX.md timestamp updates (fallback rebuild) \n\n - watchdog restart count is exactly 1 \n\n \n\n================================================ \n\nOUTPUT FORMAT \n\n \n\nReturn a concise structured report: \n\n \n\n1) Files changed (with brief description) \n\n2) New constants / config added \n\n3) Evidence for Test A (snippets + timestamps) \n\n4) Evidence for Test B (snippets + timestamps) \n\n5) Confirm no other unrelated changes were made"}],"timestamp":1772744300624}}
