{"type":"message","id":"77804caf","parentId":"99609c29","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:17:13.354Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll spawn a sub-agent using main agent. I'll provide detailed task instructions. Let me craft the delegation with Handoff Report requirement. I'll also include watchdog registration? Actually the sub-agent should include incident emission and learning integration, but I don't need to force watchdog registration for this skill creation task. I'll just ensure they follow the spec and end with Handoff Report. Let me spawn.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_tmAcGrZ0jbU3w78IMAaJ5SJU","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"Create a brand-new OpenClaw skill \"long-prompt-orchestrator\" in the workspace under /skills/ with production-ready implementation.\n\nSKILL PURPOSE:\nA production-ready \"Long Prompt Optimizer\" that automatically:\n1) detects overly long prompts / complex tasks\n2) decomposes them into smaller dependent mini-prompts executed sequentially\n3) maintains a persistent ToDo checklist with states (initial / in_progress / complete)\n4) manages token budgets per API call and optimizes context to reduce hallucinations\n5) validates final output against the original prompt objective\n6) supports recovery: if interrupted/stalled, resumes from checklist state and last checkpoint\n\nHARD REQUIREMENTS:\n- Create new skill folder at: <workspace>/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\n- Include SKILL.md (complete, precise, step-by-step)\n- Include scripts (Python preferred) implementing workflow and file persistence\n- Include examples/ and references/\n- Must integrate with existing learning system:\n  - Emit incidents to <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md for:\n    - decomposition fails\n    - token budget exceeded\n    - checklist corruption\n    - validation fails\n    - resume fails\n  - Pattern-Keys must be consistent and dedup-friendly\n  - After incident emission, trigger same pipeline style used by watchdog:\n    - prefer calling error-learning-loop if possible\n    - must include fallback to run update_index.py to keep INDEX.md fresh\n- Must be production-ready NOW: include all optimizations and guardrails from v1\n- Do NOT \"suggest future improvements\" unless included in v1 implementation\n\nDIRECTORY STRUCTURE REQUIRED:\nskills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\n  SKILL.md\n  scripts/\n    orchestrate.py\n    decompose.py\n    todo.py\n    token_budget.py\n    validate.py\n    recovery.py\n    learning_emit.py\n  references/\n    design.md\n    pattern_keys.md\n  examples/\n    example_basic.md\n    example_complex.md\n\nIMPLEMENTATION SPECS:\n\n1) CORE BEHAVIOR — prompt decomposition + dependency execution\n- Detect \"too long/complex\" requests using heuristics:\n  - estimated tokens > MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS (config, default 4000)\n  - expected steps > 5\n  - multi-file outputs or multi-agent operations\n  - long tool execution sequences\n- Decompose into mini-prompts each with:\n  - id, objective, inputs, outputs, dependencies (DAG edges), acceptance criteria, max token budget\n- Execution in topological order\n- After each step: write checkpoint to disk, update ToDo state, compress context (distill outputs into compact \"facts\")\n- Final validation: compare final result against original objective and acceptance criteria\n  - If fails: create incident + attempt one repair pass using checklist + deltas\n  - If still fails: stop and emit incident\n\n2) PERSISTENT TODO CHECKLIST (3 states) + RECOVERY\n- Persistent checklist file at: <workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>.md (or .json)\n- Must contain: task_id, original_prompt (shortened/hashed), created_at, status: initial|in_progress|complete\n- List of items with: item_id, description, dependencies, state: initial|in_progress|complete, started_at/completed_at, artifacts produced, notes\n- Recovery rules:\n  - On restart: load checklist + last checkpoint, find in_progress items, infer where stopped, resume minimal next step\n  - If checklist corrupted: emit incident, attempt rebuild from checkpoints once\n\n3) TOKEN MANAGEMENT + CONTEXT OPTIMIZATION\n- Implement strict token budget layer: global budget, per-step max output/input tokens\n- Maintain compact \"Context Ledger\" file: <workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md with key facts, decisions, file paths, open questions, constraints\n- For each mini-step: assemble only objective + dependencies outputs + relevant ledger facts\n- Guardrails:\n  - max number of mini-tasks (e.g., 20) to prevent infinite decomposition\n  - stop if decomposition doesn't reduce token estimate\n  - hard stop if token budget exceeded: emit incident\n\n4) LEARNING INTEGRATION (IMPLEMENTED, NOT THEORETICAL)\n- Implement learning_emit.py to append incident blocks to <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md\n- Pattern keys (examples, implement in references/pattern_keys.md):\n  - planning|OVERLOAD|prompt_too_long|decompose|required\n  - planning|FAILURE|decompose|no_progress|loop\n  - tokens|BUDGET|exceeded|input_overflow|truncate_required\n  - tokens|BUDGET|exceeded|output_overflow|reduce_required\n  - checklist|FAILURE|state_corrupt|rebuild_failed|manual_needed\n  - validation|FAILURE|final_output|criteria_not_met|repair_failed\n  - recovery|FAILURE|resume|checkpoint_missing|cannot_continue\n- After emitting: prefer triggering error-learning-loop skill; include fallback to run update_index.py with debouncing\n\n5) VALIDATION HARNESS (MUST RUN QUICK DEMO)\n- examples/example_basic.md: simple long prompt split into 4-6 tasks\n- examples/example_complex.md: multi-file output style request split + ToDo\n- Provide quick CLI demo in orchestrate.py:\n  - `python3 orchestrate.py --demo basic`\n  - `python3 orchestrate.py --demo complex`\n- Demo must demonstrate: decomposition result, todo creation + state transitions, checkpoint files written, recovery path simulated, incident emission path at least once\n\n6) SKILL.MD MUST BE COMPLETE AND UNAMBIGUOUS\n- Include: name, description, when-to-use/not, inputs/outputs, step-by-step instructions, safety rules/guardrails, file layout, ToDo+checkpoints, token budgeting, recovery, incident emission, example usage\n\nDELIVERY REQUIREMENTS:\n- MUST write files to disk in the workspace\n- MUST provide short validation run (dry-run) demonstrating scripts work\n- MUST end with Handoff Report including: Outcome + Incidents + Files created/changed\n- Use existing workspace components (AGENTS.md, skills, .learnings/) as needed\n- Do NOT refactor existing skills\n- Do NOT change watchdog or error-learning-loop\n\nSTART WORK NOW.","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"main","label":"long-prompt-orchestrator-creator"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":437,"output":1647,"cacheRead":39232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41316,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772745390123}}
