et an idea of the format.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_oT9ICWog872MyZqe1uvxlq2K\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772745447622\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"toolResult\",\n      \"toolCallId\": \"call_00_oT9ICWog872MyZqe1uvxlq2K\",\n      \"toolName\": \"read\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"---\\nname: error-learning-loop\\ndescription: Capture errors and near-misses from the current task and from sub-agent handoff reports, perform semantic deduplication of incidents, convert them into actionable learnings, and promote guardrails into AGENTS.md and TOOLS.md so the main agent avoids repeating mistakes. Supports manual invocation and end-of-task wrap-up.\\nmetadata: {\\\"openclaw\\\":{\\\"category\\\":\\\"meta\\\",\\\"user-invocable\\\":true,\\\"command-dispatch\\\":\\\"model\\\",\\\"requires\\\":[\\\"workspace_write\\\"],\\\"optional_requires\\\":[\\\"sessions_history\\\",\\\"python\\\",\\\"bash\\\"],\\\"safety_level\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"wrap_up_enabled\\\":true}}\\n---\\n\\n# error-learning-loop\\n\\n## Purpose\\nCreate a structured feedback loop where the **main agent** learns from:\\n- its own errors/near-misses, and\\n- **sub-agent handoff reports** (Option 1: chat-based reporting),\\nso repeated mistakes become guardrails in the workspace.\\n\\nThis skill is designed to be installed **only in the main agent workspace**.\\n\\n## Operating Modes\\n### Manual Mode\\nTriggered explicitly by the user.\\n\\nExample:\\n\\\"Run the learning loop.\\\"\\n\\n### Wrap-Up Mode\\nExecuted at the end of a task **ONLY IF** at least one incident occurred:\\n- tool failure / exception / non-zero exit\\n- user correction or new requirement that invalidates prior work\\n- near-miss detected\\n- sub-agent handoff indicates failure/partial or an incident\\n\\nIf no incident occurred, wrap-up should not execute.\\n\\n## Multi-agent data source (Option 1 — REQUIRED)\\nThe main agent must collect incidents from sub-agents via a mandatory **Handoff Report** appended to every sub-agent’s final response.\\n\\n### Handoff Report (required format)\\nSub-agents must end with:\\n\\nOutcome: success|partial|failure\\nIncidents:\\n- [TYPE=ERROR|NEAR_MISS|MISUNDERSTANDING|TOOL_FAILURE|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF; SEV=S1|S2|S3|S4] <symptom in 1 line> (evidence: <1 line, no secrets>)\\nPattern hint: <optional, 1 line>\\nPrevention rule: <optional, 1 line>\\nFiles touched: <list or \\\"none\\\">\\nNext action: <1 line>\\n\\n### Rules for sub-agents\\n- Do NOT include secrets/tokens/credentials.\\n- Keep evidence brief and concrete.\\n- If there were no incidents: set Outcome=success and Incidents: none.\\n\\n## Core Concept: Semantic Dedupe\\nTraditional dedupe compares exact strings.\\nSemantic dedupe groups incidents by **meaning** into stable Pattern-Keys.\\n\\nExample (all same semantic class):\\n- \\\"rg command not found\\\"\\n- \\\"ripgrep missing\\\"\\n- \\\"bash failed because rg not installed\\\"\\n→ Pattern-Key: tools|…path\\n\\n## Pattern-Key\\nFormat:\\n<domain>|<type>|<tool>|<failure_class>|<root_cause_signature>\\n\\n## Hard Safety Rules (non-negotiable)\\n1) Only read/write inside the current workspace and {baseDir}. Never edit outside.\\n2) Never store secrets, tokens, passwords, keys, or private identifiers in learnings/logs.\\n3) Do NOT install dependencies; do NOT auto-refactor code; do NOT change global OpenClaw config.\\n4) Session/history access (if available) is allowed only when invoked and only for relevant sessions.\\n5) Prefer minimal, auditable edits: small diffs, clear headings, and dated entries.\\n6) If unsure whether something is sensitive: redact it.\\n\\n## Mitigations (to prevent common failure modes)\\n### M1 — Prevent overfitting (bad generalizations)\\nPromote a learning to AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md only if it is generalizable AND:\\n- repeated Pattern-Key occurrences >= 2, OR\\n- Severity is S1/S2 structural issue.\\n\\nOtherwise keep it in .learnings only.\\n\\n### M2 — Prevent logging noise\\nKeep entries concise:\\n- Symptoms: max 6 bullets\\n- Root Cause: max 4 bullets\\n- 1 learning sentence\\n- 1 prevention rule\\n- Preflight: 2–6 checks max\\n\\n### M3 — Prevent sensitive-data leakage\\nBefore writing:\\n- redact tokens/keys/passwords\\n- replace emails/phones with placeholders\\n- avoid customer names unless explicitly required\\n\\n### M4 — Prevent uncontrolled scope creep\\nIf the fix requires new capability:\\n- log as FEATURE_REQUEST\\n- do not implement automatically\\n\\n## Inputs\\nFrom current context:\\n- Task goal (1–2 sentences)\\n- Evidence: tool outputs, user corrections\\n- Tags (mandatory):\\n  - agent=<name>\\n  - session\\n…(truncated)…\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"isError\": false,\n      \"timestamp\": 1772745452841\n    }\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": true,\n  \"droppedMessages\": false,\n  \"contentTruncated\": true,\n  \"contentRedacted\": true,\n  \"bytes\": 12773\n}"}],"details":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:8f487c35-0aec-488b-bd3d-fb8efe3c085c","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Create a brand-new OpenClaw skill \"long-prompt-orchestrator\" in the workspace under /skills/ with production-ready implementation.\n\nSKILL PURPOSE:\nA production-ready \"Long Prompt Optimizer\" that automatically:\n1) detects overly long prompts / complex tasks\n2) decomposes them into smaller dependent mini-prompts executed sequentially\n3) maintains a persistent ToDo checklist with states (initial / in_progress / complete)\n4) manages token budgets per API call and optimizes context to reduce hallucinations\n5) validates final output against the original prompt objective\n6) supports recovery: if interrupted/stalled, resumes from checklist state and last checkpoint\n\nHARD REQUIREMENTS:\n- Create new skill folder at: <workspace>/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\n- Include SKILL.md (complete, precise, step-by-step)\n- Include scripts (Python preferred) implementing workflow and file persistence\n- Include examples/ and references/\n- Must integrate with existing learning system:\n  - Emit incidents to <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md for:\n    - decomposition fails\n    - token budget exceeded\n    - checklist corruption\n    - validation fails\n    - resume fails\n  - Pattern-Keys must be consistent and dedup-friendly\n  - After incident emission, trigger same pipeline style used by watchdog:\n    - prefer calling error-learning-loop if possible\n    - must include fallback to run update_index.py to keep INDEX.md fresh\n- Must be production-ready NOW: include all optimizations and guardrails from v1\n- Do NOT \"suggest future improvements\" unless included in v1 implementation\n\nDIRECTORY STRUCTURE REQUIRED:\nskills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\n  SKILL.md\n  scripts/\n    orchestrate.py\n    decompose.py\n    todo.py\n    token_budget.py\n    validate.py\n    recovery.py\n    learning_emit.py\n  references/\n    design.md\n    pattern_keys.md\n  examples/\n    example_basic.md\n    example_complex.md\n\nIMPLEMENTATION SPECS:\n\n1) CORE BEHAVIOR — prompt decomposition + dependency execution\n- Detect \"too long/complex\" requests using heuristics:\n  - estimated tokens > MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS (config, default 4000)\n  - expected steps > 5\n  - multi-file outputs or multi-agent operations\n  - long tool execution sequences\n- Decompose into mini-prompts each with:\n  - id, objective, inputs, outputs, dependencies (DAG edges), acceptance criteria, max token budget\n- Execution in topological order\n- After each step: write checkpoint to disk, update ToDo state, compress context (distill outputs into compact \"facts\")\n- Final validation: compare final result against original objective and acceptance criteria\n  - If fails: create incident + attempt one repair pass using checklist + deltas\n  - If still fails: stop and emit incident\n\n2) PERSISTENT TODO CHECKLIST (3 states) + RECOVERY\n- Persistent checklist file at: <workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>.md (or .json)\n- Must contain: task_id, original_prompt (shortened/hashed), created_at, status: initial|in_progress|complete\n- List of items with: item_id, description, dependencies, state: initial|in_progress|complete, started_at/completed_at, artifacts produced, notes\n- Recovery rules:\n  - On restart: load checklist + last checkpoint, find in_progress items, infer where stopped, resume minimal next step\n  - If checklist corrupted: emit incident, attempt rebuild from checkpoints once\n\n3) TOKEN MANAGEMENT + CONTEXT OPTIMIZATION\n- Implement strict token budget layer: global budget, per-step max output/input tokens\n- Maintain compact \"Context Ledger\" file: <workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md with key facts, decisions, file paths, open questions, constraints\n- For each mini-step: assemble only objective + dependencies outputs + relevant ledger facts\n- Guardrails:\n  - max number of mini-tasks (e.g., 20) to prevent infinite decomposition\n  - stop if decomposition doesn't reduce token estimate\n  - hard stop \n…(truncated)…"}],"timestamp":1772745433733},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'll start by creating the skill directory structure and then implement each component. First, let me check the workspace root and see what's already there."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_kBND8Gt2UsedYvVMgLvMfKDx","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace -type f -name \"*.md\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772745433736},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_kBND8Gt2UsedYvVMgLvMfKDx","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/references/incident_schema.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/references/pattern_key_guidelines.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/references/subagent_handoff_contract.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/references/promotion_policy.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/examples/example_errors.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/examples/example_learnings.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/examples/example_tools_guardrails.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/references/watchdog_patterns.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/examples/example_watchdog_usage.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/IDENTITY.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/temp_proceso24.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/temp_proceso27.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/PROPUESTAS_semantico.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/temp_proceso28.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772745440015},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll create the skill directory. Let's first see if there's already a skills folder:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_TOfwOlMHCuT8mQActd0OcPyi"