{"type":"message","id":"f910fc3e","parentId":"7fcd9f4c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:19:03.298Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Not yet. Let me check if there's any activity in the workspace directory (new files). Let me check if there are any .py files in the scripts directory. Let me wait 2 minutes and check again. Let me also prepare acceptance test script. Let me write a Python script that will test the skill once it's ready. But I'll wait for Handoff Report first. Let me check sessions_list again to see if sub-agent is still active (updatedAt). Let me get current time in milliseconds: use date +%s%3N. Let me do exec. Let me also check if the sub-agent has any recent messages. Let me check sessions_history with limit 50. Let me do that now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_L64LoKVBwDh6tUUc3tv97TJG","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:8f487c35-0aec-488b-bd3d-fb8efe3c085c","limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":310,"output":386,"cacheRead":50560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51256,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772745533912}}
{"type":"message","id":"960e3c5f","parentId":"f910fc3e","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:19:03.393Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_L64LoKVBwDh6tUUc3tv97TJG","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:8f487c35-0aec-488b-bd3d-fb8efe3c085c\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"[Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\\n\\n[Subagent Task]: Create a brand-new OpenClaw skill \\\"long-prompt-orchestrator\\\" in the workspace under /skills/ with production-ready implementation.\\n\\nSKILL PURPOSE:\\nA production-ready \\\"Long Prompt Optimizer\\\" that automatically:\\n1) detects overly long prompts / complex tasks\\n2) decomposes them into smaller dependent mini-prompts executed sequentially\\n3) maintains a persistent ToDo checklist with states (initial / in_progress / complete)\\n4) manages token budgets per API call and optimizes context to reduce hallucinations\\n5) validates final output against the original prompt objective\\n6) supports recovery: if interrupted/stalled, resumes from checklist state and last checkpoint\\n\\nHARD REQUIREMENTS:\\n- Create new skill folder at: <workspace>/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\\n- Include SKILL.md (complete, precise, step-by-step)\\n- Include scripts (Python preferred) implementing workflow and file persistence\\n- Include examples/ and references/\\n- Must integrate with existing learning system:\\n  - Emit incidents to <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md for:\\n    - decomposition fails\\n    - token budget exceeded\\n    - checklist corruption\\n    - validation fails\\n    - resume fails\\n  - Pattern-Keys must be consistent and dedup-friendly\\n  - After incident emission, trigger same pipeline style used by watchdog:\\n    - prefer calling error-learning-loop if possible\\n    - must include fallback to run update_index.py to keep INDEX.md fresh\\n- Must be production-ready NOW: include all optimizations and guardrails from v1\\n- Do NOT \\\"suggest future improvements\\\" unless included in v1 implementation\\n\\nDIRECTORY STRUCTURE REQUIRED:\\nskills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\\n  SKILL.md\\n  scripts/\\n    orchestrate.py\\n    decompose.py\\n    todo.py\\n    token_budget.py\\n    validate.py\\n    recovery.py\\n    learning_emit.py\\n  references/\\n    design.md\\n    pattern_keys.md\\n  examples/\\n    example_basic.md\\n    example_complex.md\\n\\nIMPLEMENTATION SPECS:\\n\\n1) CORE BEHAVIOR — prompt decomposition + dependency execution\\n- Detect \\\"too long/complex\\\" requests using heuristics:\\n  - estimated tokens > MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS (config, default 4000)\\n  - expected steps > 5\\n  - multi-file outputs or multi-agent operations\\n  - long tool execution sequences\\n- Decompose into mini-prompts each with:\\n  - id, objective, inputs, outputs, dependencies (DAG edges), acceptance criteria, max token budget\\n- Execution in topological order\\n- After each step: write checkpoint to disk, update ToDo state, compress context (distill outputs into compact \\\"facts\\\")\\n- Final validation: compare final result against original objective and acceptance criteria\\n  - If fails: create incident + attempt one repair pass using checklist + deltas\\n  - If still fails: stop and emit incident\\n\\n2) PERSISTENT TODO CHECKLIST (3 states) + RECOVERY\\n- Persistent checklist file at: <workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>.md (or .json)\\n- Must contain: task_id, original_prompt (shortened/hashed), created_at, status: initial|in_progress|complete\\n- List of items with: item_id, description, dependencies, state: initial|in_progress|complete, started_at/completed_at, artifacts produced, notes\\n- Recovery rules:\\n  - On restart: load checklist + last checkpoint, find in_progress items, infer where stopped, resume minimal next step\\n  - If checklist corrupted: emit incident, attempt rebuild from checkpoints once\\n\\n3) TOKEN MANAGEMENT + CONTEXT OPTIMIZATION\\n- Implement strict token budget layer: global budget, per-step max output/input tokens\\n- Maintain compact \\\"Context Ledger\\\" file: <workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md with key facts, decisions, file paths, open questions, constraints\\n- For each mini-step: assemble only objective + dependencies outputs + relevant ledger facts\\n- Guardrails:\\n  - max number of mini-tasks (e.g., 20) to prevent infinite decomposition\\n  - stop if decomposition doesn't reduce token estimate\\n  - hard stop \\n…(truncated)…\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"timestamp\": 1772745433733\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"I'll start by creating the skill directory structure and then implement each component. First, let me check the workspace root and see what's already there.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_kBND8Gt2UsedYvVMgLvMfKDx\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace -type f -name \\\"*.md\\\" | head -20\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772745433736\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now I'll create the skill directory. Let's first see if there's already a skills folder:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_TOfwOlMHCuT8mQActd0OcPyi\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"ls -la /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772745440018\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Good. Now create the new skill directory:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_SdQqsTbfFGvw7nCrSrMyY1UJ\",\n          \"name\": \"exec\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"command\": \"mkdir -p /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/{scripts,references,examples}\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772745443847\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now I'll start creating the files. First, let's create SKILL.md. I'll write the content step by step. Let's first read the existing skill template from error-learning-loop to get an idea of the format.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_oT9ICWog872MyZqe1uvxlq2K\",\n          \"name\": \"read\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772745447622\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"thinking\",\n          \"thinking\": \"Now I'll create SKILL.md for long-prompt-orchestrator. I'll follow similar structure but tailored to the skill's purpose. Let's write it.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_WfMj327h01LPAP2RUOcsJPL4\",\n          \"name\": \"write\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md\",\n            \"content\": \"---\\nname: long-prompt-orchestrator\\ndescription: A production-ready Long Prompt Optimizer that automatically decomposes overly long/complex tasks into smaller dependent mini-prompts executed sequentially, manages token budgets, maintains persistent ToDo checklists, validates final output, and supports recovery from interruptions.\\nmetadata: {\\\"openclaw\\\":{\\\"category\\\":\\\"planning\\\",\\\"user-invocable\\\":true,\\\"command-dispatch\\\":\\\"model\\\",\\\"requires\\\":[\\\"python\\\",\\\"workspace_write\\\"],\\\"optional_requires\\\":[\\\"bash\\\"],\\\"safety_level\\\":\\\"high\\\",\\\"wrap_up_enabled\\\":false}}\\n---\\n\\n# long-prompt-orchestrator\\n\\n## Purpose\\nAutomatically detect overly long prompts or complex tasks, decompose them into smaller dependent mini-prompts, execute them sequentially, maintain a persistent ToDo checklist with state tracking, manage token budgets per API call, optimize context to reduce hallucinations, validate final output against original objective, and support recovery from interruptions.\\n\\n## When to Use\\n- When the main agent receives a prompt that is too long (estimated tokens > 4000)\\n- When a task appears complex: expected steps > 5, multi‑file outputs, multi‑agent operations, long tool execution sequences\\n- When you need to split a large task into manageable sub‑tasks with dependencies\\n- When you need to maintain a persistent checklist and resume after interruption\\n\\n## When NOT to Use\\n- For simple, short prompts (estimated tokens < 1000)\\n- For tasks that require atomic, non‑decomposable execution\\n- When the user explicitly wants a single‑step response\\n- When the task is already being handled by another planning/orchestration skill\\n\\n## Inputs\\n- Original prompt (string)\\n- Optional configuration (MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS, MAX_MINI_TASKS, etc.)\\n- Optional checkpoint/task_id for recovery\\n\\n## Outputs\\n- Final result (if successful)\\n- Persistent checklist file at `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>.md`\\n- Context ledger file at `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md`\\n- Checkpoint files for each completed mini‑task\\n- Incidents logged to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md` (if failures)\\n- Handoff Report for integration with main agent\\n\\n## Step-by-step Instructions\\n\\n### Step 0 — Setup\\nEnsure the skill directory exists and scripts are executable. Create `.taskboards/` directory if missing.\\n\\n### Step 1 — Detection\\nUse `scripts/decompose.py` to analyze the original prompt:\\n- Estimate token count (rough heuristic)\\n- Detect complexity heuristics (steps >5, multi‑file outputs, etc.)\\n- If prompt is within limits, return original prompt (skip decomposition)\\n\\n### Step 2 — Decomposition\\nIf decomposition required:\\n- Generate a DAG of mini‑tasks each with:\\n  - `id`\\n  - `objective`\\n  - `inputs` (files, data from previous tasks)\\n  - `outputs` (expected artifacts)\\n  - `dependencies` (list of task ids)\\n  - `acceptance_criteria`\\n  - `max_token_budget`\\n- Ensure total mini‑tasks ≤ MAX_MINI_TASKS (default 20)\\n- If decomposition doesn't reduce token estimate, stop and emit incident\\n\\n### Step 3 — Create Persistent ToDo Checklist\\nUse `scripts/todo.py` to create `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>.md` (or .json) containing:\\n- `task_id`\\n- `original_prompt` (shortened/hashed)\\n- `created_at`\\n- `status` (initial|in_progress|complete)\\n- List of items with `item_id`, `description`, `dependencies`, `state` (initial|in_progress|complete), `started_at`/`completed_at`, `artifacts`, `notes`\\n\\n### Step 4 — Token Management & Context Ledger\\nUse `scripts/token_budget.py` to allocate global token budget and per‑step max tokens.\\nCreate `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md` with key facts, decisions, file paths, open questions, constraints.\\nBefore each mini‑task, assemble context: objective + dependencies outputs + relevant ledger facts.\\n\\n### Step 5 — Execution Loop\\nUse `scripts/orchestrate.py` to iterate through mini‑tasks in topological order:\\n- Update checklist state to `in_progress`\\n- Execute the mini‑prompt (call model API via OpenClaw tooling)\\n- Capture output\\n- Update checklist state to `complete`\\n- Write checkpoint file\\n- Distill outputs into compact facts and update ledger\\n- If token budget exceeded, emit incident and stop\\n\\n### Step 6 — Validation\\nAfter all mini‑tasks complete, use `scripts/validate.py` to compare final result against original objective and acceptance criteria.\\nIf validation fails:\\n- Attempt one repair pass using checklist + deltas\\n- If still fails, emit incident and stop\\n\\n### Step 7 — Recovery\\nIf interruption/stall detected:\\n- Load checklist + last checkpoint\\n- Find `in_progress` items, infer where stopped\\n- Resume minimal next step using `scripts/recovery.py`\\n- If checklist corrupted, emit incident and attempt rebuild from checkpoints once\\n\\n### Step 8 — Learning Integration\\nWhenever an incident occurs (decomposition fails, token budget exceeded, checklist corruption, validation fails, resume fails):\\n- Use `scripts/learning_emit.py` to append incident block to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`\\n- Use Pattern‑Keys from `references/pattern_keys.md`\\n- After emitting, prefer triggering `error-learning-loop` skill; fallback to run `update_index.py` with debouncing\\n\\n### Step 9 — Cleanup (Optional)\\nAfter successful completion, optionally archive or delete checkpoint files.\\n\\n## Safety Rules / Guardrails\\n- Never delete user files without explicit confirmation.\\n- Never exceed global token budget; hard‑stop and emit incident.\\n- Limit mini‑tasks to 20 to prevent infinite decomposition.\\n- Do not store secrets/tokens/credentials in ledger or checklist.\\n- Recovery must not overwrite valid completed work.\\n- All incidents must be logged with proper Pattern‑Keys.\\n\\n## File Layout\\n```\\nskills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\\n  SKILL.md                           (this file)\\n  scripts/\\n    orchestrate.py                   (main orchestration loop)\\n    decompose.py                     (detect & decompose)\\n    todo.py                          (persistent checklist)\\n    token_budget.py                  (token management)\\n    validate.py                      (final validation)\\n    recovery.py                      (recovery logic)\\n    learning_emit.py                 (incident emission)\\n  references/\\n    design.md                        (design decisions)\\n    pattern_keys.md                  (Pattern‑Key definitions)\\n  examples/\\n    example_basic.md                 (simple long prompt example)\\n    example_complex.md               (complex multi‑file example)\\n```\\n\\n## ToDo + Checkpoints\\n- Checklist files are stored in `<workspace>/.taskboards/`\\n- Each checklist is named `<task_id>.md` (or `.json`)\\n- Checkpoints are stored as `<workspace>/.taskboards/checkpoints/<task_id>_<step>.json`\\n- Context ledger is `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md`\\n\\n## Token Budgeting\\n- Global budget configurable (default 16000 tokens)\\n- Per‑step input max tokens (default 4000)\\n- Per‑step output max tokens (default 2000)\\n- Token estimation uses rough heuristic (4 chars per token)\\n\\n## Recovery\\n- On restart, load checklist and last checkpoint.\\n- If checklist missing or corrupted, attempt rebuild from checkpoints.\\n- If rebuild fails, emit incident and stop.\\n\\n## Incident Emission\\n- All incidents must be emitted via `learning_emit.py`\\n- Pattern‑Keys must follow domain|type|tool|failure_class|root_cause_signature\\n- After emission, call `error-learning-loop` if available, else run `update_index.py`\\n\\n## Example Usage\\n### Via CLI demo\\n```bash\\ncd /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator\\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo basic\\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo complex\\n```\\n\\n### Integration with main agent\\nWhen the main agent detects a long prompt, invoke this skill:\\n1. Spawn a sub‑agent with this skill's orchestration script.\\n2. Pass the original prompt as argument.\\n3. Wait for Handoff Report.\\n\\n### Manual invocation\\n```bash\\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --prompt \\\"Very long prompt...\\\"\\n```\\n\\n## Configuration\\nEnvironment variables or config file can override:\\n- `MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS` (default 4000)\\n- `MAX_MINI_TASKS` (default 20)\\n- `GLOBAL_TOKEN_BUDGET` (default 16000)\\n- `INPUT_TOKEN_LIMIT` (default 4000)\\n- `OUTPUT_TOKEN_LIMIT` (default 2000)\\n\\n## Quick Validation\\nRun the demo to verify the skill works:\\n```bash\\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo basic\\n```\\nCheck that:\\n- Decomposition result printed\\n- ToDo checklist created\\n- State transitions visible\\n- Checkpoint files written\\n- Recovery path simulated\\n- Incident emission triggered at least once\\n\\n## Notes\\nThis is a production‑ready v1 implementation. All optimizations and guardrails are included.\\nDo NOT suggest future improvements unless they are part of v1.\\n\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-reasoner\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1772745452843\n    }\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": true,\n  \"droppedMessages\": false,\n  \"contentTruncated\": true,\n  \"contentRedacted\": false,\n  \"bytes\": 15607\n}"}],"details":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:8f487c35-0aec-488b-bd3d-fb8efe3c085c","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Create a brand-new OpenClaw skill \"long-prompt-orchestrator\" in the workspace under /skills/ with production-ready implementation.\n\nSKILL PURPOSE:\nA production-ready \"Long Prompt Optimizer\" that automatically:\n1) detects overly long prompts / complex tasks\n2) decomposes them into smaller dependent mini-prompts executed sequentially\n3) maintains a persistent ToDo checklist with states (initial / in_progress / complete)\n4) manages token budgets per API call and optimizes context to reduce hallucinations\n5) validates final output against the original prompt objective\n6) supports recovery: if interrupted/stalled, resumes from checklist state and last checkpoint\n\nHARD REQUIREMENTS:\n- Create new skill folder at: <workspace>/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\n- Include SKILL.md (complete, precise, step-by-step)\n- Include scripts (Python preferred) implementing workflow and file persistence\n- Include examples/ and references/\n- Must integrate with existing learning system:\n  - Emit incidents to <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md for:\n    - decomposition fails\n    - token budget exceeded\n    - checklist corruption\n    - validation fails\n    - resume fails\n  - Pattern-Keys must be consistent and dedup-friendly\n  - After incident emission, trigger same pipeline style used by watchdog:\n    - prefer calling error-learning-loop if possible\n    - must include fallback to run update_index.py to keep INDEX.md fresh\n- Must be production-ready NOW: include all optimizations and guardrails from v1\n- Do NOT \"suggest future improvements\" unless included in v1 implementation\n\nDIRECTORY STRUCTURE REQUIRED:\nskills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\n  SKILL.md\n  scripts/\n    orchestrate.py\n    decompose.py\n    todo.py\n    token_budget.py\n    validate.py\n    recovery.py\n    learning_emit.py\n  references/\n    design.md\n    pattern_keys.md\n  examples/\n    example_basic.md\n    example_complex.md\n\nIMPLEMENTATION SPECS:\n\n1) CORE BEHAVIOR — prompt decomposition + dependency execution\n- Detect \"too long/complex\" requests using heuristics:\n  - estimated tokens > MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS (config, default 4000)\n  - expected steps > 5\n  - multi-file outputs or multi-agent operations\n  - long tool execution sequences\n- Decompose into mini-prompts each with:\n  - id, objective, inputs, outputs, dependencies (DAG edges), acceptance criteria, max token budget\n- Execution in topological order\n- After each step: write checkpoint to disk, update ToDo state, compress context (distill outputs into compact \"facts\")\n- Final validation: compare final result against original objective and acceptance criteria\n  - If fails: create incident + attempt one repair pass using checklist + deltas\n  - If still fails: stop and emit incident\n\n2) PERSISTENT TODO CHECKLIST (3 states) + RECOVERY\n- Persistent checklist file at: <workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>.md (or .json)\n- Must contain: task_id, original_prompt (shortened/hashed), created_at, status: initial|in_progress|complete\n- List of items with: item_id, description, dependencies, state: initial|in_progress|complete, started_at/completed_at, artifacts produced, notes\n- Recovery rules:\n  - On restart: load checklist + last checkpoint, find in_progress items, infer where stopped, resume minimal next step\n  - If checklist corrupted: emit incident, attempt rebuild from checkpoints once\n\n3) TOKEN MANAGEMENT + CONTEXT OPTIMIZATION\n- Implement strict token budget layer: global budget, per-step max output/input tokens\n- Maintain compact \"Context Ledger\" file: <workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md with key facts, decisions, file paths, open questions, constraints\n- For each mini-step: assemble only objective + dependencies outputs + relevant ledger facts\n- Guardrails:\n  - max number of mini-tasks (e.g., 20) to prevent infinite decomposition\n  - stop if decomposition doesn't reduce token estimate\n  - hard stop \n…(truncated)…"}],"timestamp":1772745433733},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'll start by creating the skill directory structure and then implement each component. First, let me check the workspace root and see what's already there."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_kBND8Gt2UsedYvVMgLvMfKDx","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace -type f -name \"*.md\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772745433736},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll create the skill directory. Let's first see if there's already a skills folder:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_TOfwOlMHCuT8mQActd0OcPyi","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772745440018},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now create the new skill directory:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_SdQqsTbfFGvw7nCrSrMyY1UJ","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/{scripts,references,examples}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772745443847},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll start creating the files. First, let's create SKILL.md. I'll write the content step by step. Let's first read the existing skill template from error-learning-loop to get an idea of the format."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_oT9ICWog872MyZqe1uvxlq2K","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772745447622},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll create SKILL.md for long-prompt-orchestrator. I'll follow similar structure but tailored to the skill's purpose. Let's write it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_WfMj327h01LPAP2RUOcsJPL4","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md","content":"---\nname: long-prompt-orchestrator\ndescription: A production-ready Long Prompt Optimizer that automatically decomposes overly long/complex tasks into smaller dependent mini-prompts executed sequentially, manages token budgets, maintains persistent ToDo checklists, validates final output, and supports recovery from interruptions.\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"category\":\"planning\",\"user-invocable\":true,\"command-dispatch\":\"model\",\"requires\":[\"python\",\"workspace_write\"],\"optional_requires\":[\"bash\"],\"safety_level\":\"high\",\"wrap_up_enabled\":false}}\n---\n\n# long-prompt-orchestrator\n\n## Purpose\nAutomatically detect overly long prompts or complex tasks, decompose them into smaller dependent mini-prompts, execute them sequentially, maintain a persistent ToDo checklist with state tracking, manage token budgets per API call, optimize context to reduce hallucinations, validate final output against original objective, and support recovery from interruptions.\n\n## When to Use\n- When the main agent receives a prompt that is too long (estimated tokens > 4000)\n- When a task appears complex: expected steps > 5, multi‑file outputs, multi‑agent operations, long tool execution sequences\n- When you need to split a large task into manageable sub‑tasks with dependencies\n- When you need to maintain a persistent checklist and resume after interruption\n\n## When NOT to Use\n- For simple, short prompts (estimated tokens < 1000)\n- For tasks that require atomic, non‑decomposable execution\n- When the user explicitly wants a single‑step response\n- When the task is already being handled by another planning/orchestration skill\n\n## Inputs\n- Original prompt (string)\n- Optional configuration (MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS, MAX_MINI_TASKS, etc.)\n- Optional checkpoint/task_id for recovery\n\n## Outputs\n- Final result (if successful)\n- Persistent checklist file at `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>.md`\n- Context ledger file at `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md`\n- Checkpoint files for each completed mini‑task\n- Incidents logged to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md` (if failures)\n- Handoff Report for integration with main agent\n\n## Step-by-step Instructions\n\n### Step 0 — Setup\nEnsure the skill directory exists and scripts are executable. Create `.taskboards/` directory if missing.\n\n### Step 1 — Detection\nUse `scripts/decompose.py` to analyze the original prompt:\n- Estimate token count (rough heuristic)\n- Detect complexity heuristics (steps >5, multi‑file outputs, etc.)\n- If prompt is within limits, return original prompt (skip decomposition)\n\n### Step 2 — Decomposition\nIf decomposition required:\n- Generate a DAG of mini‑tasks each with:\n  - `id`\n  - `objective`\n  - `inputs` (files, data from previous tasks)\n  - `outputs` (expected artifacts)\n  - `dependencies` (list of task ids)\n  - `acceptance_criteria`\n  - `max_token_budget`\n- Ensure total mini‑tasks ≤ MAX_MINI_TASKS (default 20)\n- If decomposition doesn't reduce token estimate, stop and emit incident\n\n### Step 3 — Create Persistent ToDo Checklist\nUse `scripts/todo.py` to create `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>.md` (or .json) containing:\n- `task_id`\n- `original_prompt` (shortened/hashed)\n- `created_at`\n- `status` (initial|in_progress|complete)\n- List of items with `item_id`, `description`, `dependencies`, `state` (initial|in_progress|complete), `started_at`/`completed_at`, `artifacts`, `notes`\n\n### Step 4 — Token Management & Context Ledger\nUse `scripts/token_budget.py` to allocate global token budget and per‑step max tokens.\nCreate `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md` with key facts, decisions, file paths, open questions, constraints.\nBefore each mini‑task, assemble context: objective + dependencies outputs + relevant ledger facts.\n\n### Step 5 — Execution Loop\nUse `scripts/orchestrate.py` to iterate through mini‑tasks in topological order:\n- Update checklist state to `in_progress`\n- Execute the mini‑prompt (call model API via OpenClaw tooling)\n- Capture output\n- Update checklist state to `complete`\n- Write checkpoint file\n- Distill outputs into compact facts and update ledger\n- If token budget exceeded, emit incident and stop\n\n### Step 6 — Validation\nAfter all mini‑tasks complete, use `scripts/validate.py` to compare final result against original objective and acceptance criteria.\nIf validation fails:\n- Attempt one repair pass using checklist + deltas\n- If still fails, emit incident and stop\n\n### Step 7 — Recovery\nIf interruption/stall detected:\n- Load checklist + last checkpoint\n- Find `in_progress` items, infer where stopped\n- Resume minimal next step using `scripts/recovery.py`\n- If checklist corrupted, emit incident and attempt rebuild from checkpoints once\n\n### Step 8 — Learning Integration\nWhenever an incident occurs (decomposition fails, token budget exceeded, checklist corruption, validation fails, resume fails):\n- Use `scripts/learning_emit.py` to append incident block to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n- Use Pattern‑Keys from `references/pattern_keys.md`\n- After emitting, prefer triggering `error-learning-loop` skill; fallback to run `update_index.py` with debouncing\n\n### Step 9 — Cleanup (Optional)\nAfter successful completion, optionally archive or delete checkpoint files.\n\n## Safety Rules / Guardrails\n- Never delete user files without explicit confirmation.\n- Never exceed global token budget; hard‑stop and emit incident.\n- Limit mini‑tasks to 20 to prevent infinite decomposition.\n- Do not store secrets/tokens/credentials in ledger or checklist.\n- Recovery must not overwrite valid completed work.\n- All incidents must be logged with proper Pattern‑Keys.\n\n## File Layout\n```\nskills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\n  SKILL.md                           (this file)\n  scripts/\n    orchestrate.py                   (main orchestration loop)\n    decompose.py                     (detect & decompose)\n    todo.py                          (persistent checklist)\n    token_budget.py                  (token management)\n    validate.py                      (final validation)\n    recovery.py                      (recovery logic)\n    learning_emit.py                 (incident emission)\n  references/\n    design.md                        (design decisions)\n    pattern_keys.md                  (Pattern‑Key definitions)\n  examples/\n    example_basic.md                 (simple long prompt example)\n    example_complex.md               (complex multi‑file example)\n```\n\n## ToDo + Checkpoints\n- Checklist files are stored in `<workspace>/.taskboards/`\n- Each checklist is named `<task_id>.md` (or `.json`)\n- Checkpoints are stored as `<workspace>/.taskboards/checkpoints/<task_id>_<step>.json`\n- Context ledger is `<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md`\n\n## Token Budgeting\n- Global budget configurable (default 16000 tokens)\n- Per‑step input max tokens (default 4000)\n- Per‑step output max tokens (default 2000)\n- Token estimation uses rough heuristic (4 chars per token)\n\n## Recovery\n- On restart, load checklist and last checkpoint.\n- If checklist missing or corrupted, attempt rebuild from checkpoints.\n- If rebuild fails, emit incident and stop.\n\n## Incident Emission\n- All incidents must be emitted via `learning_emit.py`\n- Pattern‑Keys must follow domain|type|tool|failure_class|root_cause_signature\n- After emission, call `error-learning-loop` if available, else run `update_index.py`\n\n## Example Usage\n### Via CLI demo\n```bash\ncd /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo basic\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo complex\n```\n\n### Integration with main agent\nWhen the main agent detects a long prompt, invoke this skill:\n1. Spawn a sub‑agent with this skill's orchestration script.\n2. Pass the original prompt as argument.\n3. Wait for Handoff Report.\n\n### Manual invocation\n```bash\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --prompt \"Very long prompt...\"\n```\n\n## Configuration\nEnvironment variables or config file can override:\n- `MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS` (default 4000)\n- `MAX_MINI_TASKS` (default 20)\n- `GLOBAL_TOKEN_BUDGET` (default 16000)\n- `INPUT_TOKEN_LIMIT` (default 4000)\n- `OUTPUT_TOKEN_LIMIT` (default 2000)\n\n## Quick Validation\nRun the demo to verify the skill works:\n```bash\npython3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo basic\n```\nCheck that:\n- Decomposition result printed\n- ToDo checklist created\n- State transitions visible\n- Checkpoint files written\n- Recovery path simulated\n- Incident emission triggered at least once\n\n## Notes\nThis is a production‑ready v1 implementation. All optimizations and guardrails are included.\nDo NOT suggest future improvements unless they are part of v1.\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772745452843}],"truncated":true,"droppedMessages":false,"contentTruncated":true,"contentRedacted":false,"bytes":15607},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772745543385}}
