{"type":"message","id":"9a31bf95","parentId":"c016d04e","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:22:49.241Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"example_complex.md added. Still no scripts. Let me check if scripts directory has any files now. Let me list scripts. Let me also check if there are any .py files in the parent directory maybe. Let me check. Let me also check if the sub-agent is still active. Let me check sessions_list. Let me see if updatedAt changed. Let me get updatedAt. Let me do exec with python to parse. Let me do: python3 -c \"import json, subprocess, time; out = subprocess.check_output(['openclaw', 'sessions', 'list', '--json'], text=True); data = json.loads(out); for s in data['sessions']: if 'long-prompt' in s.get('label',''): print(s['updatedAt']); print('Diff:', int(time.time()*1000)-s['updatedAt'])\". But openclaw command may not be available. Let me use sessions_list tool again. Let me just check manually. Let me do sessions_list and look at the timestamp. Let me compute diff using python. Let me do exec with python using current time. Let me do: python3 -c \"import time; print(int(time.time()*1000))\". Let me get current time. Let me also get updatedAt from sessions_list output. Let me look at the sessions_list output I got earlier. The updatedAt was 1772745433649. That's March 5, 2026 4:17:13? Let me convert. That's about 4:17 PM. Current time is about 4:28 PM. That's 11 minutes ago. That suggests the sub-agent hasn't updated in 11 minutes, meaning it might be stuck or finished. But it should auto-announce if finished. Maybe it's still running but not making tool calls? Could be thinking. Let me check sessions_history with limit 100 to see if there are more recent messages beyond truncation. Let me do sessions_history with limit 100 and includeTools. Let me do that now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_dOrFjUbl0sTMnJfEzteH4gOf","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey"