{"type":"message","id":"538934f5","parentId":"bb808bf8","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:26:14.415Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 16:15 EST] You are the MAIN agent. Run a fire-test of our multi-agent system. \n\n \n\nGOAL: \n\nSpawn ONE independent sub-agent (you choose which) and instruct it to CREATE a brand-new OpenClaw skill inside this workspace under /skills/. \n\n \n\nSkill purpose: \n\nA production-ready “Long Prompt Optimizer” skill that automatically: \n\n1) detects overly long prompts / complex tasks, \n\n2) decomposes them into smaller dependent mini-prompts executed sequentially, \n\n3) maintains a persistent ToDo checklist with states (initial / in_progress / complete), \n\n4) manages token budgets per API call and optimizes context to reduce hallucinations, \n\n5) validates final output against the original prompt objective, \n\n6) supports recovery: if interrupted/stalled, it resumes from checklist state and last checkpoint. \n\n \n\nHARD REQUIREMENTS: \n\n- Create a new skill folder under: <workspace>/skills/<skill-name>/ \n\n- Include SKILL.md (complete, precise, step-by-step) \n\n- Include scripts (Python preferred) that implement the workflow and file persistence \n\n- Include examples/ and references/ \n\n- Must integrate with our existing learning system: \n\n - Emit incidents to <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md when: \n\n - decomposition fails \n\n - token budget exceeded \n\n - checklist corruption \n\n - validation fails \n\n - resume fails \n\n - Pattern-Keys must be consistent and dedup-friendly \n\n - After incident emission, trigger the same pipeline style used by watchdog: \n\n - prefer calling error-learning-loop if possible \n\n - must include fallback to run update_index.py to keep INDEX.md fresh \n\n- Must be designed production-ready NOW: include all optimizations and guardrails from v1. \n\n- Do NOT “suggest future improvements” unless they are included in v1. Implement them now. \n\n \n\nNON-GOALS: \n\n- Do not refactor existing skills. \n\n- Do not change watchdog or error-learning-loop. \n\n- Do not add optional “maybe later” features; implement only what is essential and production-grade. \n\n \n\n============================================================ \n\nSTEP A — SPAWN SUB-AGENT \n\n \n\nSpawn a sub-agent you consider best for building a robust skill (implementation + docs). \n\nIn the delegation instructions require: \n\n- It must end with a Handoff Report including: Outcome + Incidents + Files created/changed. \n\n- It must actually write files to disk in the workspace. \n\n- It must provide a short validation run (dry-run) demonstrating the scripts work. \n\n \n\n============================================================ \n\nSTEP B — SUB-AGENT IMPLEMENTATION SPEC (give to sub-agent) \n\n \n\nCreate a skill named (choose a clean name): \n\n- prompt-load-balancer \n\nOR \n\n- long-prompt-orchestrator \n\nOR \n\n- prompt-decomposition-engine \n\n \n\nDirectory structure REQUIRED: \n\n \n\nskills/<skill-name>/ \n\n SKILL.md \n\n scripts/ \n\n orchestrate.py \n\n decompose.py \n\n todo.py \n\n token_budget.py \n\n validate.py \n\n recovery.py \n\n learning_emit.py \n\n references/ \n\n design.md \n\n pattern_keys.md \n\n examples/ \n\n example_basic.md \n\n example_complex.md \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------------------ \n\n1) Core behavior — prompt decomposition + dependency execution \n\n \n\n- Detect “too long / too complex” requests using heuristics: \n\n - estimated tokens > MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS (config) \n\n - expected steps > 5 \n\n - multi-file outputs or multi-agent operations \n\n - long tool execution sequences \n\n \n\n- Decompose into mini-prompts: \n\n - each mini-prompt must have: \n\n - id \n\n - objective \n\n - inputs \n\n - outputs \n\n - dependencies (DAG edges) \n\n - acceptance criteria \n\n - max token budget \n\n \n\n- Execution: \n\n - run tasks in topological order \n\n - after each step: \n\n - write checkpoint to disk \n\n - update ToDo state \n\n - compress context (distill outputs into compact “facts” list) \n\n \n\n- Final validation: \n\n - compare final result against original objective and acceptance criteria \n\n - if fails: \n\n - create incident + attempt one repair pass using the checklist + deltas \n\n - if still fails: stop and emit incident \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------------------ \n\n2) Persistent ToDo checklist (3 states) + recovery \n\n \n\nCreate persistent checklist file at: \n\n \n\n<workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>.md (or .json if better) \n\n \n\nMust contain: \n\n- task_id \n\n- original_prompt (shortened/hashed reference) \n\n- created_at \n\n- status: initial|in_progress|complete \n\n- list of items with: \n\n - item_id \n\n - description \n\n - dependencies \n\n - state: initial|in_progress|complete \n\n - started_at / completed_at \n\n - artifacts produced (file paths) \n\n - notes \n\n \n\nRecovery rules: \n\n- On restart: \n\n - load checklist + last checkpoint \n\n - find any in_progress items \n\n - infer “where it stopped” using checkpoint + last outputs \n\n - resume only the minimal next step \n\n- If checklist is corrupted: \n\n - emit incident \n\n - attempt rebuild from checkpoints once \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------------------ \n\n3) Token management + context optimization \n\n \n\nImplement a strict token budget layer: \n\n- global budget for the entire run \n\n- per-step max output tokens \n\n- per-step max input tokens \n\n \n\nContext strategy: \n\n- Never carry full raw prompt forward after decomposition. \n\n- Maintain a compact “Context Ledger” file: \n\n <workspace>/.taskboards/<task_id>_ledger.md \n\n containing: \n\n - key facts (bulleted) \n\n - decisions made \n\n - file paths created \n\n - remaining open questions \n\n - constraints / guardrails to enforce \n\n- For each mini-step: \n\n - assemble only: objective + dependencies outputs + relevant ledger facts \n\n - keep it minimal and deterministic \n\n \n\nGuardrails: \n\n- max number of mini-tasks (e.g., 20) to prevent infinite decomposition \n\n- stop condition if decomposition doesn’t reduce token estimate \n\n- hard stop if token budget exceeded: emit incident \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------------------ \n\n4) Learning integration (must be implemented, not theoretical) \n\n \n\nImplement learning_emit.py: \n\n- append incident blocks into <workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md \n\n- pattern keys (examples, implement in references/pattern_keys.md): \n\n - planning|OVERLOAD|prompt_too_long|decompose|required \n\n - planning|FAILURE|decompose|no_progress|loop \n\n - tokens|BUDGET|exceeded|input_overflow|truncate_required \n\n - tokens|BUDGET|exceeded|output_overflow|reduce_required \n\n - checklist|FAILURE|state_corrupt|rebuild_failed|manual_needed \n\n - validation|FAILURE|final_output|criteria_not_met|repair_failed \n\n - recovery|FAILURE|resume|checkpoint_missing|cannot_continue \n\n \n\nAfter emitting: \n\n- Prefer triggering error-learning-loop skill if OpenClaw supports it \n\n- Must include fallback: \n\n python3 <workspace>/skills/error-learning-loop/scripts/update_index.py <workspace> \n\n- Debounce rebuild to avoid churn. \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------------------ \n\n5) Validation harness (must run a quick demo) \n\n \n\nProvide in examples/: \n\n- example_basic.md: simple long prompt split into 4-6 tasks \n\n- example_complex.md: multi-file output style request split + ToDo \n\n \n\nProvide a quick CLI demo in orchestrate.py: \n\n- `python3 orchestrate.py --demo basic` \n\n- `python3 orchestrate.py --demo complex` \n\nThe demo may simulate “LLM calls” if needed, but must demonstrate: \n\n- decomposition result \n\n- todo creation + state transitions \n\n- checkpoint files written \n\n- recovery path simulated (stop mid-way then resume) \n\n- incident emission path at least once (intentional small failure) \n\n \n\n------------------------------------------------------------ \n\n6) SKILL.md must be complete and unambiguous \n\n \n\nSKILL.md must include: \n\n- name \n\n- description \n\n- when-to-use / when-not-to-use \n\n- inputs / outputs \n\n- step-by-step instructions \n\n- safety rules / guardrails \n\n- file layout \n\n- how ToDo + checkpoints work \n\n- token budgeting rules \n\n- recovery procedure \n\n- how incidents are emitted + pattern keys \n\n- example usage commands \n\n \n\n============================================================ \n\nSTEP C — MAIN AGENT ACCEPTANCE CHECK \n\n \n\nAfter sub-agent completes, as MAIN agent you must: \n\n1) Confirm the folder exists and files were created. \n\n2) Run the demo command(s) once. \n\n3) Confirm .taskboards files are created. \n\n4) Confirm ERRORS.md receives an incident and INDEX.md is refreshed (fallback rebuild). \n\n5) Summarize pass/fail for: \n\n - decomposition \n\n - todo tracking \n\n - recovery \n\n - token budgeting \n\n - learning emission \n\n \n\n============================================================ \n\nOUTPUT REQUIREMENTS \n\n \n\nReturn: \n\n- Sub-agent Handoff Report (must include file list) \n\n- Your own acceptance check results \n\n- A short “ready to install/use” instruction: where it lives, how to invoke it. \n\n \n\nNo fluff. No future suggestions unless implemented."}],"timestamp":1772745974411}}
