{"type":"message","id":"5a75452f","parentId":"bf339e05","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:30:00.940Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"El demo dice \"No decomposition needed\". Eso significa que la detección no está funcionando correctamente, probablemente porque el prompt no es suficientemente largo según el umbral. El umbral es MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS = 4000, pero el prompt tiene solo 858 caracteres. La estimación de tokens es caracteres/4 ~ 214 tokens, muy por debajo del límite. El demo debería forzar la descomposición para mostrar la funcionalidad. El sub-agent estaba editando para arreglar esto. Necesito modificar el demo para que funcione. Dado que el sub-agent no completó el Handoff Report, como MAIN agent puedo ajustar el demo para que muestre la funcionalidad, pero debo ser transparente.\n\nPrimero, voy a verificar los otros scripts (decompose.py) para ver si implementa la detección y descomposición. Si está vacío o no funciona, puedo arreglarlo. Pero primero, veamos decompose.py:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_MugBA2NB109p773dEoa9tc4O","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/scripts/decompose.py","offset":1,"limit":80}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":252,"output":541,"cacheRead":74816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75609,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772746188981}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ee47fc6","parentId":"5a75452f","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:30:00.983Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_MugBA2NB109p773dEoa9tc4O","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nDetect overly long/complex prompts and decompose into mini‑tasks.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport re\nimport math\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any, Tuple\n\ndef estimate_tokens(text: str) -> int:\n    \"\"\"Rough token estimation (4 chars ≈ 1 token).\"\"\"\n    return len(text) // 4\n\ndef detect_complexity(prompt: str) -> Tuple[bool, List[str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Detect if prompt is complex based on heuristics.\n    Returns (should_decompose, reasons).\n    \"\"\"\n    reasons = []\n    \n    # Token count\n    tokens = estimate_tokens(prompt)\n    if tokens > 4000:  # default MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS\n        reasons.append(f\"Token count {tokens} > 4000\")\n    \n    # Expected steps > 5\n    step_keywords = ['step', 'first', 'then', 'next', 'finally', 'part', 'section', 'chapter', 'task']\n    step_count = sum(1 for word in step_keywords if word in prompt.lower())\n    if step_count > 5:\n        reasons.append(f\"Step-like keywords {step_count} > 5\")\n    \n    # Multi-file outputs\n    file_extensions = ['.py', '.md', '.txt', '.json', '.csv', '.html', '.ipynb', '.yml', '.yaml']\n    if any(ext in prompt for ext in file_extensions):\n        reasons.append(\"Contains file extensions (multi‑file outputs)\")\n    \n    # Multi‑agent operations\n    agent_keywords = ['sub‑agent', 'subagent', 'validator', 'spawn', 'delegate', 'parallel']\n    if any(kw in prompt.lower() for kw in agent_keywords):\n        reasons.append(\"Mentions multi‑agent operations\")\n    \n    # Long tool execution sequences\n    tool_keywords = ['run', 'execute', 'call', 'tool', 'command', 'script', 'bash']\n    tool_count = sum(1 for word in tool_keywords if word in prompt.lower())\n    if tool_count > 3:\n        reasons.append(f\"Tool‑like keywords {tool_count} > 3\")\n    \n    should_decompose = len(reasons) > 0\n    return should_decompose, reasons\n\ndef decompose_prompt(prompt: str, max_mini_tasks: int = 20) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Simple rule‑based decomposition for v1.\n    Splits by numbered lists, bullet points, or 'Part X' patterns.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Look for numbered lists (1., 2., etc.)\n    numbered = re.findall(r'\\n\\s*\\d+\\.\\s+(.+?)(?=\\n\\s*\\d+\\.|\\n\\s*$)', prompt, re.DOTALL)\n    # Look for bullet points (‑, *, •)\n    bullet = re.findall(r'\\n\\s*[-*•]\\s+(.+?)(?=\\n\\s*[-*•]|\\n\\s*$)', prompt, re.DOTALL)\n    # Look for 'Part X:' or 'Step X:'\n    parts = re.findall(r'\\n\\s*(?:Part|Step)\\s+\\w+\\s*:\\s*(.+?)(?=\\n\\s*(?:Part|Step)|\\n\\s*$)', prompt, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL)\n    \n    segments = []\n    if numbered:\n        segments = numbered\n    elif bullet:\n        segments = bullet\n    elif parts:\n        segments = parts\n    else:\n        # Fallback: split by sentences? Too naive; just treat as single task.\n        return []\n    \n    # Limit to max_mini_tasks\n    if len(segments) > max_mini_tasks:\n        segments = segments[:max_mini_tasks]\n    \n    tasks = []\n    for i, seg in enumerate(segments, start=1):\n        task_id = f\"task_{i:02d}\"\n\n[64 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772746200971}}
{"type":"message","id":"0a41f852","parentId":"9ee47fc6","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:30:10.374Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Parece que decompose.py está bien implementado. El problema es que el prompt del ejemplo básico no activa las heurísticas porque es corto. Necesitamos modificar run_demo_basic para que use un prompt más largo o fuerce la descomposición. Dado que el sub-agent no terminó, voy a hacer un ajuste rápido para que el demo funcione y muestre la funcionalidad. Modificaré orchestrate.py para forzar la descomposición en el demo básico. Primero, voy a leer el resto del archivo para ver la función completa. Luego editaré.\n\nPrimero, obtengamos las líneas de run_demo_basic:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_fAHBhKjmnYeI9Gqpu3KuALXm","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator && sed -n '/^def run_demo_basic():/,/^def [a-zA-Z]/p' scripts/orchestrate.py | head -100"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":1280,"output":391,"cacheRead":75008,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76679,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772746200984}}
{"type":"message","id":"54e5d6f2","parentId":"0a41f852","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:30:10.844Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_fAHBhKjmnYeI9Gqpu3KuALXm","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def run_demo_basic():\n    \"\"\"Run basic demo from example_basic.md.\"\"\"\n    print(\"=== Running Basic Demo ===\")\n    ensure_taskboards_dir()\n    \n    # Load example prompt\n    example_path = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), '../examples/example_basic.md')\n    with open(example_path, 'r') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    # Extract the prompt (crude extraction for demo)\n    lines = content.split('\\n')\n    prompt = ''\n    in_prompt = False\n    for line in lines:\n        if line.startswith('```'):\n            if not in_prompt:\n                in_prompt = True\n                continue\n            else:\n                break\n        if in_prompt and line:\n            prompt += line + '\\n'\n    if not prompt:\n        prompt = \"Create a comprehensive report about climate change impacts on agriculture...\"\n    \n    print(f\"Original prompt length: {len(prompt)} chars\")\n    \n    # Detect and decompose\n    tasks = detect_and_decompose(prompt, max_prompt_tokens=MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS, max_mini_tasks=MAX_MINI_TASKS)\n    if not tasks:\n        print(\"No decomposition needed.\")\n        return\n    \n    print(f\"Decomposed into {len(tasks)} mini-tasks.\")\n    for task in tasks:\n        print(f\"  {task['id']}: {task['objective'][:60]}...\")\n    \n    # Create checklist\n    task_id = \"demo_basic_\" + str(int(os.times().elapsed))\n    checklist = Checklist(task_id, prompt[:200])\n    for task in tasks:\n        checklist.add_item(\n            task['id'],\n            task['objective'],\n            task['dependencies'],\n            artifacts=task.get('outputs', [])\n        )\n    checklist_path = os.path.join(TASKBOARDS_DIR, f\"{task_id}.md\")\n    checklist.save(checklist_path)\n    print(f\"Checklist saved to {checklist_path}\")\n    \n    # Token budget\n    budget = TokenBudget(\n        global_budget=GLOBAL_TOKEN_BUDGET,\n        input_limit=INPUT_TOKEN_LIMIT,\n        output_limit=OUTPUT_TOKEN_LIMIT\n    )\n    \n    # Execute tasks in topological order (simple dependency sort)\n    executed = {}\n    for task in tasks:\n        # Wait for dependencies\n        deps = task['dependencies']\n        if deps and any(dep not in executed for dep in deps):\n            print(f\"Skipping {task['id']} — dependencies not ready\")\n            continue\n        \n        print(f\"Executing {task['id']}...\")\n        checklist.update_state(task['id'], 'in_progress')\n        \n        # Assemble context (simplified)\n        context = f\"Objective: {task['objective']}\\n\"\n        for dep in deps:\n            if dep in executed:\n                context += f\"Output from {dep}: {executed[dep][:100]}...\\n\"\n        \n        # Check token budget\n        input_tokens = budget.estimate_tokens(context)\n        if not budget.can_consume(input_tokens, task['max_token_budget']):\n            emit_incident(\n                \"tokens|BUDGET|token_budget|input_overflow|truncate_required\",\n                \"Input token overflow\",\n                f\"step_id={task['id']}, input_tokens={input_tokens}, limit={INPUT_TOKEN_LIMIT}\"\n            )\n            print(\"Token budget exceeded — stopping.\")\n            break\n        \n        # Simulate model call\n        output = simulate_model_call(context, task['max_token_budget'])\n        output_tokens = budget.estimate_tokens(output)\n        budget.consume(input_tokens + output_tokens)\n        \n        executed[task['id']] = output\n        checklist.update_state(task['id'], 'complete', artifacts=[f\"{task['id']}_output.txt\"])\n        \n        # Write checkpoint\n        checkpoint = {\n            'task_id': task['id'],\n            'output': output,\n            'input_tokens': input_tokens,"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":106,"aggregated":"def run_demo_basic():\n    \"\"\"Run basic demo from example_basic.md.\"\"\"\n    print(\"=== Running Basic Demo ===\")\n    ensure_taskboards_dir()\n    \n    # Load example prompt\n    example_path = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), '../examples/example_basic.md')\n    with open(example_path, 'r') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    # Extract the prompt (crude extraction for demo)\n    lines = content.split('\\n')\n    prompt = ''\n    in_prompt = False\n    for line in lines:\n        if line.startswith('```'):\n            if not in_prompt:\n                in_prompt = True\n                continue\n            else:\n                break\n        if in_prompt and line:\n            prompt += line + '\\n'\n    if not prompt:\n        prompt = \"Create a comprehensive report about climate change impacts on agriculture...\"\n    \n    print(f\"Original prompt length: {len(prompt)} chars\")\n    \n    # Detect and decompose\n    tasks = detect_and_decompose(prompt, max_prompt_tokens=MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS, max_mini_tasks=MAX_MINI_TASKS)\n    if not tasks:\n        print(\"No decomposition needed.\")\n        return\n    \n    print(f\"Decomposed into {len(tasks)} mini-tasks.\")\n    for task in tasks:\n        print(f\"  {task['id']}: {task['objective'][:60]}...\")\n    \n    # Create checklist\n    task_id = \"demo_basic_\" + str(int(os.times().elapsed))\n    checklist = Checklist(task_id, prompt[:200])\n    for task in tasks:\n        checklist.add_item(\n            task['id'],\n            task['objective'],\n            task['dependencies'],\n            artifacts=task.get('outputs', [])\n        )\n    checklist_path = os.path.join(TASKBOARDS_DIR, f\"{task_id}.md\")\n    checklist.save(checklist_path)\n    print(f\"Checklist saved to {checklist_path}\")\n    \n    # Token budget\n    budget = TokenBudget(\n        global_budget=GLOBAL_TOKEN_BUDGET,\n        input_limit=INPUT_TOKEN_LIMIT,\n        ou