{"type":"message","id":"9ecc3111","parentId":"c9c276db","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:46:23.899Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Veo que \"agent-watchdog\" existe como directorio. Ahora revisaré si tiene SKILL.md y cuál es su contenido. También revisaré si otros skills (error-learning-loop y long-prompt-orchestrator) tienen SKILL.md bien formados para comparar.\n\nPrimero, leeré SKILL.md de agent-watchdog.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_fHo1uQzR7UgISI79qOMrOMEn","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":565,"output":242,"cacheRead":61568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62375,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772747177263}}
{"type":"message","id":"da8fe749","parentId":"9ecc3111","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:46:23.940Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_fHo1uQzR7UgISI79qOMrOMEn","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\nMonitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks.\nAttempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\n\n## When to Use\n- Long running tasks\n- Multi-agent workflows\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses\n\n## Inputs\n- session_id\n- run_id\n- task_description\n- expected_runtime\n\n## Outputs\n- watchdog_status\n- recovery_actions_taken\n- incident_report\n\n## Instructions\n1. Register the session and run to monitor.\n\n[101 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772747183919}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b0c4136","parentId":"da8fe749","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:46:29.442Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"El SKILL.md parece tener contenido básico. Necesito ver si tiene una sección de metadatos YAML frontmatter que OpenClaw use para detectar el skill. Revisaré el inicio del archivo para ver si tiene formato YAML frontmatter (--- al inicio). Leeré las primeras líneas.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_AyMBWaG3fzchRrbE9zH4h4CA","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":386,"output":204,"cacheRead":62080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62670,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772747183942}}
{"type":"message","id":"a35aad24","parentId":"4b0c4136","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:46:29.458Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_AyMBWaG3fzchRrbE9zH4h4CA","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\nMonitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks.\nAttempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\n\n## When to Use\n- Long running tasks\n- Multi-agent workflows\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses\n\n## Inputs\n- session_id\n- run_id\n- task_description\n- expected_runtime\n\n## Outputs\n- watchdog_status\n- recovery_actions_taken\n- incident_report\n\n## Instructions\n1. Register the session and run to monitor.\n2. Periodically inspect session state, run state, and last activity timestamp.\n3. If inactivity exceeds stall timeout, classify as stall.\n4. Execute staged recovery:\n   - Level 1: send nudge (\"continue\")\n   - Level 2: cancel run and resume task\n   - Level 3: close session and relaunch agent\n5. Log telemetry about the stall.\n6. Generate structured incident for error-learning-loop.\n\n## Safety Rules\n- Maximum 3 recovery attempts.\n- Never restart agents indefinitely.\n- Always emit incident report.\n\n## Recovery Escalation\nLevel 1: Nudge -> send \"continue\"\nLevel 2: Soft Reset -> cancel run and resume task\nLevel 3: Relaunch -> close session and start new agent\n\n## ACP Runtime Support\nThe watchdog must monitor both subagent and ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) sessions.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `runtime_type`: `subagent` | `acp`\n\n**ACP monitoring detects**:\n- ACP process running but no output\n- No session updates\n- Session stalled without completion callback\n\n**ACP stall pattern key**:\n`runtime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck`\n\n## Multi‑Agent Deadlock Detection\nThe watchdog must detect dependency cycles between agents (deadlocks).\n\n**Detection mechanism**:\n1. Track active agents and their dependency relationships.\n   - `agent_id`\n   - `waiting_for_agent_id`\n   - `task_state`\n2. Build a dependency graph of agents.\n3. Periodically check for cycles in the dependency graph.\n\n**Deadlock pattern key**:\n`multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting`\n\n**Deadlock recovery strategy**:\n- Level 1 — Request progress update from all agents\n- Level 2 — Force resolution of one dependency edge\n- Level 3 — Restart one agent in the cycle\n\n**Deadlock incident telemetry**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- cycle_size\n- agents_involved\n- recovery_strategy\n- success\n\n**Reporting**: Deadlock incidents must be appended to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n\n## Learning Loop Integration\nGenerate incidents with pattern key format:\n\nmodel|STALL|<model>|no_response|runtime_stuck\n\nTelemetry fields:\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success_or_failure\n\n### Incident Reporting Procedure\nAfter recovery attempts, the watchdog must emit incidents to the learning system:\n\n1. Generate incident telemetry using the schema above.\n2. Append incident to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n3. Invoke the `error-learning-loop` skill to process the incident.\n\n**Incident schema**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success\n- task_type\n- items_count\n\n**Integration sequence**:\n- watchdog detects stall\n- → recovery escalation\n- → incident generated\n- → incident appended to ERRORS.md\n- → error-learning-loop executed\n- → deduplication\n- → learning extraction\n- → guardrail promotion\n- → INDEX.md updated\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772747189450}}
