{"type":"message","id":"2496ee50","parentId":"daebd5d2","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:46:36.449Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_wcBrQR8BId5VGQR8ZvqfhuqZ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: error-learning-loop\ndescription: Capture errors and near-misses from the current task and from sub-agent handoff reports, perform semantic deduplication of incidents, convert them into actionable learnings, and promote guardrails into AGENTS.md and TOOLS.md so the main agent avoids repeating mistakes. Supports manual invocation and end-of-task wrap-up.\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"category\":\"meta\",\"user-invocable\":true,\"command-dispatch\":\"model\",\"requires\":[\"workspace_write\"],\"optional_requires\":[\"sessions_history\",\"python\",\"bash\"],\"safety_level\":\"high\",\"wrap_up_enabled\":true}}\n---\n\n# error-learning-loop\n\n## Purpose\nCreate a structured feedback loop where the **main agent** learns from:\n\n[221 more lines in file. Use offset=11 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772747196430}}
{"type":"message","id":"94e4d93e","parentId":"2496ee50","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:46:43.688Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sí, error-learning-loop tiene frontmatter YAML con metadatos, incluyendo `\"user-invocable\":true`. El skill watchdog no tiene frontmatter. Eso podría ser la razón por la cual no aparece en el dashboard. El dashboard probablemente lista solo skills que tienen metadatos específicos, especialmente `\"user-invocable\":true`.\n\nRevisaré long-prompt-orchestrator también.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_SkerQtyvxhvylZlzhjt7HOTB","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":390,"output":277,"cacheRead":63360,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64027,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772747196450}}
{"type":"message","id":"dad41b0c","parentId":"94e4d93e","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:46:43.735Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_SkerQtyvxhvylZlzhjt7HOTB","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: long-prompt-orchestrator\ndescription: A production-ready Long Prompt Optimizer that automatically decomposes overly long/complex tasks into smaller dependent mini-prompts executed sequentially, manages token budgets, maintains persistent ToDo checklists, validates final output, and supports recovery from interruptions.\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"category\":\"planning\",\"user-invocable\":true,\"command-dispatch\":\"model\",\"requires\":[\"python\",\"workspace_write\"],\"optional_requires\":[\"bash\"],\"safety_level\":\"high\",\"wrap_up_enabled\":false}}\n---\n\n# long-prompt-orchestrator\n\n## Purpose\nAutomatically detect overly long prompts or complex tasks, decompose them into smaller dependent mini-prompts, execute them sequentially, maintain a persistent ToDo checklist with state tracking, manage token budgets per API call, optimize context to reduce hallucinations, validate final output against original objective, and support recovery from interruptions.\n\n[189 more lines in file. Use offset=11 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772747203713}}
{"type":"message","id":"f00cb6e7","parentId":"dad41b0c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:47:40.578Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ambos tienen frontmatter con `\"user-invocable\":true`. El dashboard probablemente filtra skills que no tienen este frontmatter o que no tienen `\"user-invocable\":true`. El skill watchdog no tiene frontmatter, por lo tanto no es reconocido como un skill invocable por el usuario.\n\nNecesito agregar frontmatter al SKILL.md de agent-watchdog. Pero primero debo verificar si hay algún otro requisito, como la categoría. Podemos copiar la estructura de los otros skills. También necesito considerar si el watchdog debería ser \"user-invocable\". El watchdog es un skill de sistema que se ejecuta automáticamente, pero también podría ser invocado manualmente para verificar el estado. Podemos establecer `\"user-invocable\":true` para que aparezca en el dashboard.\n\nTambién debo asegurarme de que el archivo SKILL.md tenga el formato correcto. Agregaré frontmatter al inicio del archivo, antes del título \"# agent-watchdog\". Necesito editar el archivo.\n\nPrimero, leeré el archivo completo para asegurarme de no perder contenido. Luego crearé el frontmatter. El contenido actual comienza con \"# agent-watchdog\". Insertaré el frontmatter antes de esa línea. Usaré el formato similar a los otros skills.\n\nTambién verificaré si hay un archivo `package.json` o algo similar en el directorio del skill. No es necesario.\n\nProcederé a editar SKILL.md.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_yep3nNk65bMn8ZuhEJumaiEz","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md","oldText":"# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\nMonitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks.\nAttempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\n\n## When to Use\n- Long running tasks\n- Multi-agent workflows\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses\n\n## Inputs\n- session_id\n- run_id\n- task_description\n- expected_runtime\n\n## Outputs\n- watchdog_status\n- recovery_actions_taken\n- incident_report\n\n## Instructions\n1. Register the session and run to monitor.\n2. Periodically inspect session state, run state, and last activity timestamp.\n3. If inactivity exceeds stall timeout, classify as stall.\n4. Execute staged recovery:\n   - Level 1: send nudge (\"continue\")\n   - Level 2: cancel run and resume task\n   - Level 3: close session and relaunch agent\n5. Log telemetry about the stall.\n6. Generate structured incident for error-learning-loop.\n\n## Safety Rules\n- Maximum 3 recovery attempts.\n- Never restart agents indefinitely.\n- Always emit incident report.\n\n## Recovery Escalation\nLevel 1: Nudge -> send \"continue\"\nLevel 2: Soft Reset -> cancel run and resume task\nLevel 3: Relaunch -> close session and start new agent\n\n## ACP Runtime Support\nThe watchdog must monitor both subagent and ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) sessions.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `runtime_type`: `subagent` | `acp`\n\n**ACP monitoring detects**:\n- ACP process running but no output\n- No session updates\n- Session stalled without completion callback\n\n**ACP stall pattern key**:\n`runtime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck`\n\n## Multi‑Agent Deadlock Detection\nThe watchdog must detect dependency cycles between agents (deadlocks).\n\n**Detection mechanism**:\n1. Track active agents and their dependency relationships.\n   - `agent_id`\n   - `waiting_for_agent_id`\n   - `task_state`\n2. Build a dependency graph of agents.\n3. Periodically check for cycles in the dependency graph.\n\n**Deadlock pattern key**:\n`multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting`\n\n**Deadlock recovery strategy**:\n- Level 1 — Request progress update from all agents\n- Level 2 — Force resolution of one dependency edge\n- Level 3 — Restart one agent in the cycle\n\n**Deadlock incident telemetry**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- cycle_size\n- agents_involved\n- recovery_strategy\n- success\n\n**Reporting**: Deadlock incidents must be appended to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n\n## Learning Loop Integration\nGenerate incidents with pattern key format:\n\nmodel|STALL|<model>|no_response|runtime_stuck\n\nTelemetry fields:\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success_or_failure\n\n### Incident Reporting Procedure\nAfter recovery attempts, the watchdog must emit incidents to the learning system:\n\n1. Generate incident telemetry using the schema above.\n2. Append incident to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n3. Invoke the `error-learning-loop` skill to process the incident.\n\n**Incident schema**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success\n- task_type\n- items_count\n\n**Integration sequence**:\n- watchdog detects stall\n- → recovery escalation\n- → incident generated\n- → incident appended to ERRORS.md\n- → error-learning-loop executed\n- → deduplication\n- → learning extraction\n- → guardrail promotion\n- → INDEX.md updated","newText":"---\nname: agent-watchdog\ndescription: Monitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks. Attempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"category\":\"monitoring\",\"user-invocable\":true,\"command-dispatch\":\"model\",\"requires\":[\"workspace_write\",\"python\"],\"optional_requires\":[\"sessions_list\",\"sessions_history\"],\"safety_level\":\"high\",\"wrap_up_enabled\":false}}\n---\n\n# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\nMonitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks.\nAttempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.\n\n## When to Use\n- Long running tasks\n- Multi-agent workflows\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses\n\n## Inputs\n- session_id\n- run_id\n- task_description\n- expected_runtime\n\n## Outputs\n- watchdog_status\n- recovery_actions_taken\n- incident_report\n\n## Instructions\n1. Register the session and run to monitor.\n2. Periodically inspect session state, run state, and last activity timestamp.\n3. If inactivity exceeds stall timeout, classify as stall.\n4. Execute staged recovery:\n   - Level 1: send nudge (\"continue\")\n   - Level 2: cancel run and resume task\n   - Level 3: close session and relaunch agent\n5. Log telemetry about the stall.\n6. Generate structured incident for error-learning-loop.\n\n## Safety Rules\n- Maximum 3 recovery attempts.\n- Never restart agents indefinitely.\n- Always emit incident report.\n\n## Recovery Escalation\nLevel 1: Nudge -> send \"continue\"\nLevel 2: Soft Reset -> cancel run and resume task\nLevel 3: Relaunch -> close session and start new agent\n\n## ACP Runtime Support\nThe watchdog must monitor both subagent and ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) sessions.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `runtime_type`: `subagent` | `acp`\n\n**ACP monitoring detects**:\n- ACP process running but no output\n- No session updates\n- Session stalled without completion callback\n\n**ACP stall pattern key**:\n`runtime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck`\n\n## Multi‑Agent Deadlock Detection\nThe watchdog must detect dependency cycles between agents (deadlocks).\n\n**Detection mechanism**:\n1. Track active agents and their dependency relationships.\n   - `agent_id`\n   - `waiting_for_agent_id`\n   - `task_state`\n2. Build a dependency graph of agents.\n3. Periodically check for cycles in the dependency graph.\n\n**Deadlock pattern key**:\n`multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting`\n\n**Deadlock recovery strategy**:\n- Level 1 — Request progress update from all agents\n- Level 2 — Force resolution of one dependency edge\n- Level 3 — Restart one agent in the cycle\n\n**Deadlock incident telemetry**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- cycle_size\n- agents_involved\n- recovery_strategy\n- success\n\n**Reporting**: Deadlock incidents must be appended to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n\n## Learning Loop Integration\nGenerate incidents with pattern key format:\n\nmodel|STALL|<model>|no_response|runtime_stuck\n\nTelemetry fields:\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success_or_failure\n\n### Incident Reporting Procedure\nAfter recovery attempts, the watchdog must emit incidents to the learning system:\n\n1. Generate incident telemetry using the schema above.\n2. Append incident to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n3. Invoke the `error-learning-loop` skill to process the incident.\n\n**Incident schema**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success\n- task_type\n- items_count\n\n**Integration sequence**:\n- watchdog detects stall\n- → recovery escalation\n- → incident generated\n- → incident appended to ERRORS.md\n- → error-learning-loop executed\n- → deduplication\n- → learning extraction\n- → guardrail promotion\n- → INDEX.md updated"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":411,"output":2454,"cacheRead":63744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66609,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772747203735}}
