{"type":"message","id":"976cac35","parentId":"c7a7a81c","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:50:59.998Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Leamos `creating-skills.md`.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_m15TC9qMEcSoFZ2juXqc8hiJ","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/creating-skills.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":378,"output":81,"cacheRead":73856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74315,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772747455673}}
{"type":"message","id":"de579fe8","parentId":"976cac35","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:51:00.042Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_m15TC9qMEcSoFZ2juXqc8hiJ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ntitle: \"Creating Skills\"\nsummary: \"Build and test custom workspace skills with SKILL.md\"\nread_when:\n  - You are creating a new custom skill in your workspace\n  - You need a quick starter workflow for SKILL.md-based skills\n---\n\n# Creating Custom Skills 🛠\n\nOpenClaw is designed to be easily extensible. \"Skills\" are the primary way to add new capabilities to your assistant.\n\n## What is a Skill?\n\nA skill is a directory containing a `SKILL.md` file (which provides instructions and tool definitions to the LLM) and optionally some scripts or resources.\n\n## Step-by-Step: Your First Skill\n\n### 1. Create the Directory\n\nSkills live in your workspace, usually `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/`. Create a new folder for your skill:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/hello-world\n```\n\n### 2. Define the `SKILL.md`\n\nCreate a `SKILL.md` file in that directory. This file uses YAML frontmatter for metadata and Markdown for instructions.\n\n```markdown\n---\nname: hello_world\ndescription: A simple skill that says hello.\n---\n\n# Hello World Skill\n\nWhen the user asks for a greeting, use the `echo` tool to say \"Hello from your custom skill!\".\n```\n\n### 3. Add Tools (Optional)\n\nYou can define custom tools in the frontmatter or instruct the agent to use existing system tools (like `bash` or `browser`).\n\n### 4. Refresh OpenClaw\n\nAsk your agent to \"refresh skills\" or restart the gateway. OpenClaw will discover the new directory and index the `SKILL.md`.\n\n## Best Practices\n\n- **Be Concise**: Instruct the model on _what_ to do, not how to be an AI.\n- **Safety First**: If your skill uses `bash`, ensure the prompts don't allow arbitrary command injection from untrusted user input.\n- **Test Locally**: Use `openclaw agent --message \"use my new skill\"` to test.\n\n## Shared Skills\n\nYou can also browse and contribute skills to [ClawHub](https://clawhub.com).\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772747460017}}
{"type":"message","id":"d45abe1f","parentId":"de579fe8","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:51:12.403Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Dice que debemos \"refresh OpenClaw\" o reiniciar el gateway. Tal vez el gateway necesita ser reiniciado para detectar el nuevo skill. Pero el skill \"agent-watchdog\" existía antes, pero tal vez no fue detectado porque no tenía frontmatter. Ahora que agregamos frontmatter, necesitamos refrescar.\n\nPodemos intentar reiniciar el gateway. Pero eso podría interrumpir la sesión actual. En su lugar, podríamos intentar ejecutar un comando para refrescar skills. No sé si hay un comando específico. Podríamos probar `openclaw skills refresh` o similar. Veamos si hay subcomando refresh.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_bc4ghYZbmXgbr3MuwhnDKTla","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw skills --help 2>&1 | grep -A5 -B5 refresh"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":25497,"output":361,"cacheRead":48000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73858,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772747460043}}
