 or       │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│           │                  │ spotify_player.                                                 │                    │\\n│ ✗ missing │ 🧾 summarize      │ Summarize or extract text/transcripts from URLs, podcasts, and  │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│           │                  │ local files (great fallback for “transcribe this YouTube/       │                    │\\n│           │                  │ video”).                                                        │                    │\\n│ ✗ missing │ ✅ things-mac     │ Manage Things 3 via the `things` CLI on macOS (add/update       │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│           │                  │ projects+todos via URL scheme; read/search/list from the local  │                    │\\n│           │                  │ Things database). Use when a user asks OpenClaw to add a task   │                    │\\n│           │                  │ to Things, list inbox/today/upcoming, search tasks, or inspect  │                    │\\n│           │                  │ projects/areas/tags.                                            │                    │\\n│ ✗ missing │ 🧵 tmux           │ Remote-control tmux sessions for interactive CLIs by sending    │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│           │                  │ keystrokes and scraping pane output.                            │                    │\\n│ ✗ missing │ 📋 trello         │ Manage Trello boards, lists, and cards via the Trello REST API. │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│ ✗ missing │ 🎞️ video-frames  │ Extract frames or short clips from videos using ffmpeg.         │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│ ✗ missing │ 📞 voice-call     │ Start voice calls via the OpenClaw voice-call plugin.           │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│ ✗ missing │ 📱 wacli          │ Send WhatsApp messages to other people or search/sync WhatsApp  │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│           │                  │ history via the wacli CLI (not for normal user chats).          │                    │\\n│ ✓ ready   │ 🌤️ weather       │ Get current weather and forecasts via wttr.in or Open-Meteo.    │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│           │                  │ Use when: user asks about weather, temperature, or forecasts    │                    │\\n│           │                  │ for any location. NOT for: historical weather data, severe      │                    │\\n│           │                  │ weather alerts, or detailed meteorological analysis. No API     │                    │\\n│           │                  │ key needed.                                                     │                    │\\n│ ✗ missing │ 𝕏 xurl           │ A CLI tool for making authenticated requests to the X           │ openclaw-bundled   │\\n│           │                  │ (Twitter) API. Use this skill when you need to post tweets,     │                    │\\n│           │                  │ reply, quote, search, read posts, manage followers, send DMs,   │                    │\\n│           │                  │ upload media, or interact with any X API v2 endpoint.           │                    │\\n│ ✓ ready   │ 📦 agent-monitor  │ Monitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model      │ openclaw-workspace │\\n│           │                  │ hangs or execution deadlocks. Attempts automatic recovery and   │                    │\\n│           │                  │ reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.       │                    │\\n│ ✓ ready   │ 📦 error-         │ Capture errors and near-misses from the current task and from   │ openclaw-workspace │\\n│           │ learning-loop    │ sub-agent handoff reports, perform semantic deduplication of    │                    │\\n│           │                  │ incidents, convert them into actionable learnings, and promote  │                    │\\n│           │                  │ guardrails into AGENTS.md and TOOLS.md so the main agent        │                    │\\n│           │                  │ avoids repeating mistakes. Supports manual invocation and end-  │                    │\\n│           │                  │ of-task wrap-up.                                                │                    │\\n│ ✓ ready   │ 📦 long-prompt-   │ A production-ready Long Prompt Optimizer that automatically     │ openclaw-workspace │\\n│           │ orchestrator     │ decomposes overly long/complex tasks into smaller dependent     │                    │\\n│           │                  │ mini-prompts executed sequentially, manages token budgets,      │                    │\\n│           │                  │ maintains persistent ToDo checklists, validates final output,   │                    │\\n│           │                  │ and supports recovery from interruptions.                       │                    │\\n│ ✓ ready   │ 📦 test-skill-123 │ Test skill.                                                     │ openclaw-workspace │\\n│ ✓ ready   │ 📦 watchdog-test  │ Test watchdog.                                                  │ openclaw-workspace │\\n└───────────┴──────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────┘\\n\\nTip: use `npx clawhub` to search, install, and sync skills.\",\"_meta\":{\"runtime\":\"node\",\"runtimeVersion\":\"22.22.0\",\"hostname\":\"unknown\",\"name\":\"openclaw\",\"date\":\"2026-03-05T22:21:34.152Z\",\"logLevelId\":3,\"logLevelName\":\"INFO\",\"path\":{\"fullFilePath\":\"file:///home/openclaw/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-kl-vrkYi.js:258:46\",\"fileName\":\"subsystem-kl-vrkYi.js\",\"fileNameWithLine\":\"subsystem-kl-vrkYi.js:258\",\"fileColumn\":\"46\",\"fileLine\":\"258\",\"filePath\":\"/home/openclaw/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-kl-vrkYi.js\",\"filePathWithLine\":\"/home/openclaw/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-kl-vrkYi.js:258\",\"method\":\"console.log\"}},\"time\":\"2026-03-05T17:21:34.154-05:00\"}\n{\"0\":\"{\\\"subsystem\\\":\\\"gateway/ws\\\"}\",\"1\":\"⇄ res ✓ skills.status 222ms conn=7283b484…f323 id=7ef0cc80…3459\",\"_meta\":{\"runtime\":\"node\",\"runtimeVersion\":\"22.22.0\",\"hostname\":\"unknown\",\"name\":\"{\\\"subsystem\\\":\\\"gateway/ws\\\"}\",\"parentNames\":[\"openclaw\"],\"date\":\"2026-03-05T22:23:14.621Z\",\"logLevelId\":3,\"logLevelName\":\"INFO\",\"path\":{\"fullFilePath\":\"file:///home/openclaw/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BfkFJ4uQ.js:427:14\",\"fileName\":\"subsystem-BfkFJ4uQ.js\",\"fileNameWithLine\":\"subsystem-BfkFJ4uQ.js:427\",\"fileColumn\":\"14\",\"fileLine\":\"427\",\"filePath\":\".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BfkFJ4uQ.js\",\"filePathWithLine\":\".npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-BfkFJ4uQ.js:427\",\"method\":\"logToFile\"}},\"time\":\"2026-03-05T17:23:14.621-05:00\"}","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772749727216}}
{"type":"message","id":"a8ef8c18","parentId":"88d9e2ff","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:28:56.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Veo que hay un error \"Cannot find module: agent-watchdog\". Esto sugiere que OpenClaw está tratando de importar el skill como un módulo Node.js, no como un skill de OpenClaw. Esto podría ser un problema de configuración o de cómo OpenClaw está buscando los skills.\n\nVamos a verificar la estructura de los skills que funcionan. Comparemos el skill `error-learning-loop` con `agent-watchdog`. También necesitamos entender cómo OpenClaw descubre los skills. Según la documentación, los skills deben tener un archivo SKILL.md con metadatos en formato YAML frontmatter.\n\nVeamos los metadatos de ambos skills para ver las diferencias. También podríamos necesitar reiniciar el gateway después de hacer cambios. Vamos a comparar primero.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Rk2EeXgA0EecMdrw5tAYVQRn","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":703,"output":449,"cacheRead":75520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76672,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772749727229}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ab56270","parentId":"a8ef8c18","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:28:56.764Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_Rk2EeXgA0EecMdrw5tAYVQRn","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: error-learning-loop\ndescription: Capture errors and near-misses from the current task and from sub-agent handoff reports, perform semantic deduplication of incidents, convert them into actionable learnings, and promote guardrails into AGENTS.md and TOOLS.md so the main agent avoids repeating mistakes. Supports manual invocation and end-of-task wrap-up.\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"category\":\"meta\",\"user-invocable\":true,\"command-dispatch\":\"model\",\"requires\":[\"workspace_write\"],\"optional_requires\":[\"sessions_history\",\"python\",\"bash\"],\"safety_level\":\"high\",\"wrap_up_enabled\":true}}\n---\n\n# error-learning-loop\n\n## Purpose\nCreate a structured feedback loop where the **main agent** learns from:\n\n[221 more lines in file. Use offset=11 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772749736724}}
{"type":"message","id":"364c0725","parentId":"0ab56270","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:29:05.565Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Los metadatos se ven similares. Ambos tienen `metadata: {\"openclaw\": {...}}`. La diferencia es que `error-learning-loop` tiene `\"category\":\"meta\"` mientras que `agent-watchdog` también tiene `\"category\":\"meta\"`. \n\nPodría ser un problema de permisos o de cómo se está cargando el módulo. Vamos a verificar si hay algún archivo de configuración que controle la carga de skills. También podríamos intentar mover el skill a una ubicación diferente temporalmente para ver si es un problema específico de este skill.\n\nPrimero, vamos a crear un skill de prueba muy simple para ver si el problema es con todos los skills o solo con `agent-watchdog`. Ya hemos creado `test-skill-123` y `watchdog-test` antes. Vamos a verificar si esos aparecen en la lista. Primero, reiniciemos el gateway y luego verifiquemos.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ZBAntHD8z6lsoa7WiYmftyuU","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway restart 2>&1 | tail -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":519,"output":463,"cacheRead":76160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77142,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772749736764}}
