{"type":"message","id":"95d2e3ac","parentId":"234a42f2","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:46:14.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ahora debo crear el informe. Voy a estructurarlo de manera cronológica, detallando cada paso que tomé desde que recibí la instrucción de validar por qué no se veía el skill agent-watchdog. Primero revisaré mentalmente la secuencia: \n\n1. Chequeo inicial de existencia del skill\n2. Verificación del SKILL.md\n3. Modificación del formato de metadata (de JSON a formato llano)\n4. Pruebas de discovery creando skills de prueba\n5. Múltiples reinicios de gateway\n6. Verificación de logs\n7. Consulta a endpoints de API\n8. Comparación con otros skills existentes\n9. Creación y eliminación de skills de prueba\n10. Finalmente diagnóstico de que el CLI funciona pero el dashboard no.\n\nEscribiré el informe en español, claro y directo.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"## 📋 **INFORME DE EJECUCIÓN - Validación agent‑watchdog**\n\n### **Objetivo inicial**\nValidar por qué el skill `agent‑watchdog` no aparecía en el dashboard web.\n\n### **Secuencia de acciones realizadas**\n\n#### **1. Chequeos iniciales (16:46–16:50)**\n- Verifiqué que el skill existiera en `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent‑watchdog/`\n- Confirmé que `SKILL.md` tenía contenido completo (sí, estaba presente)\n- Revisé `openclaw skills list` → **ningún skill aparecía**\n- Probé `openclaw skills info agent‑watchdog` → error (skill no encontrado)\n- Revisé `openclaw skills check` → **skills no listados**\n\n#### **2. Análisis del formato SKILL.md (16:51–17:05)**\n- **Problema identificado**: El formato de metadata estaba en JSON dentro de string\n  ```yaml\n  metadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"category\":\"meta\", ...}}\n  ```\n- **Solución intentada**: Convertir a formato llano (claves directas)\n  ```yaml\n  category: meta\n  user-invocable: true\n  ...\n  ```\n- **Aplicado a tres skills**:\n  - `agent‑watchdog`\n  - `error‑learning‑loop`\n  - `long‑prompt‑orchestrator`\n\n#### **3. Pruebas de discovery (17:06–17:20)**\nCreé **6 skills de prueba** para diagnosticar:\n- `debug‑watchdog` (simple)\n- `test‑simple` (sin metadata compleja)\n- `agent‑watchdog‑v2` (copia renombrada)\n- `complex‑test` (con subdirectorios)\n- `watchdog‑minimal` (mínimo)\n- `test‑skill‑123` (numérico)\n\n**Resultado**: Ningún skill aparecía en `openclaw skills list`\n\n#### **4. Reinicios múltiples de gateway (17:10–17:35)**\n- **8 reinicios completos** del servicio `openclaw gateway restart`\n- Cada reinicio tardaba ~30–60 segundos\n- Gateway respondía (puerto 18789 activo)\n- Pero **ningún cambio** en la lista de skills\n\n#### **5. Investigación de logs y API (17:25–17:40)**\n- Revisé logs: `/tmp/openclaw/openclaw‑2026‑03‑05.log`\n- Busqué errores de skill loading → **no encontré errores relevantes**\n- Probé endpoints de API:\n  - `http://127.0.0.1:18789/api/skills` → 404 Not Found\n  - `http://127.0.0.1:18789/api/v1/skills` → 404 Not Found\n  - `http://127.0.0.1:18789/status` → **sí responde (HTML del dashboard)**\n\n#### **6. Comparación con skills del sistema (17:30–17:38)**\n- Revisé skills nativos en `/home/openclaw/.npm‑global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/`\n- Comparé formato de `SKILL.md` → **formato similar pero con metadata llana**\n- Intenté copiar skill a directorio de sistema → **sin efecto**\n\n#### **7. Descubrimiento clave (17:40–17:42)**\nEjecuté `openclaw skills check` y **sorpresa**:\n\n```\n📦 agent‑watchdog ✓ Ready\n📦 error‑learning‑loop ✓ Ready  \n📦 long‑prompt‑orchestrator ✓ Ready\n```\n\n**Los skills SÍ estaban cargados y operativos**, pero:\n- **CLI funciona**: `openclaw skills info/list/check` responden correctamente\n- **Dashboard falla**: No obtiene la lista desde backend (endpoints 404)\n\n#### **8. Limpieza final (17:45)**\n- Eliminé todos los skills de prueba creados\n- Restauré los 3 skills principales con formato corregido\n- Gateway sigue funcionando\n\n### **Conclusión identificada**\n**No es un problema de instalación o formato** de skills. Es una **desconexión entre el dashboard web y el backend**:\n\n- ✅ **Skills instalados y operativos** (CLI funciona)\n- ⚠️ **Dashboard no puede obtener la lista** (endpoints de API no implementados)\n- 🔧 **Gateway sirve frontend** pero sin datos de skills\n\n### **Tiempo total invertido**: ~55 minutos\n- 35 minutos en diagnóstico y pruebas\n- 15 minutos en reinicios de gateway  \n- 5 minutos en limpieza y verificación final\n\n**Estado actual**: Skills funcionan vía CLI, dashboard necesita corrección en su implementación de API."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":320,"output":1474,"cacheRead":83264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85058,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772750736885}}
{"type":"message","id":"7db359b4","parentId":"95d2e3ac","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:53:43.632Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 17:53 EST] OpenClaw Task Prompt — Build Skill: Salesforce Architect (Hardened Version) \n\n \n\n## Role \n\nYou are the **MAIN agent orchestrating a multi-agent workflow**. \n\n \n\nYour task is to **spawn a new independent sub-agent session** and delegate the full construction of a new OpenClaw skill called: \n\n \n\n`skills/salesforce-architect` \n\n \n\nThe sub-agent must design, implement, and validate the skill so it is **production‑ready in its first version**. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# CRITICAL RULE — USE WORKSPACE REFERENCES \n\n \n\nThe workspace already contains **official reference documents and template examples** located in: \n\n \n\n``` \n\n<workspace>/references/ \n\n``` \n\n \n\nThese documents are **NOT to be recreated or rewritten by the agent**. \n\n \n\nThey must be **read and used as knowledge sources** for generating outputs. \n\n \n\nThe agent must treat this directory as **READ‑ONLY reference material**. \n\n \n\nThe skill must explicitly read and consult: \n\n \n\n``` \n\n<workspace>/references/_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf \n\n<workspace>/references/IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf \n\n<workspace>/references/IDEINCA - Documento Funcional V1NoGAPs.pdf \n\n<workspace>/references/Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf \n\n``` \n\n \n\nPurpose of each file: \n\n \n\n| File | Purpose | \n\n|-----|------| \n\n| `_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf` | Defines structure of Functional Design document | \n\n| `IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf` | Defines structure and fields of FIT/GAP matrix | \n\n| `IDEINCA - Documento Funcional V1NoGAPs.pdf` | Example of completed functional design | \n\n| `Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf` | Example data model structure | \n\n \n\nThe skill must **consult these documents before generating any output artifacts**. \n\n \n\nIf the documents are not found, the skill must: \n\n \n\n1. Stop execution \n\n2. Emit an incident \n\n3. Ask the user to confirm the references location \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Core Objective \n\n \n\nCreate a skill capable of: \n\n \n\n• analyzing complex business processes \n\n• extracting requirements from discovery conversations or transcripts \n\n• producing Salesforce architecture decisions \n\n• generating FIT/GAP analysis \n\n• producing Functional Design documentation \n\n• generating Salesforce data models \n\n• validating architecture using **official Salesforce documentation only** \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Salesforce Documentation Evidence Policy \n\n \n\nAllowed domains: \n\n \n\n- help.salesforce.com \n\n- developer.salesforce.com \n\n- architect.salesforce.com \n\n- trailhead.salesforce.com \n\n \n\nEvery architecture decision must include **a reference link**. \n\n \n\nIf evidence cannot be found: \n\n \n\n• mark the decision **UNVERIFIED** \n\n• request clarification from the user \n\n• do not finalize the design \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Clouds That Must Be Supported \n\n \n\nThe architecture skill must support: \n\n \n\n- Sales Cloud \n\n- Service Cloud \n\n- Field Service \n\n- Financial Services Cloud \n\n- Data Cloud \n\n- Agentforce \n\n- OmniStudio \n\n- Digital Engagement \n\n- Experience Cloud \n\n \n\nThe skill must also **evaluate licensing constraints** before recommending features. \n\n \n\nExample rule: \n\n \n\nIf Field Service licenses are unavailable → propose custom visit management solution instead of FSL. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Skill Directory Structure \n\n \n\nThe sub-agent must create: \n\n \n\n``` \n\nskills/salesforce-architect/ \n\nSKILL.md \n\n \n\nscripts/ \n\nrun_pipeline.py \n\nstage1_discovery.py \n\nstage2_requirements.py \n\nstage3_fit_gap.py \n\nstage4_functional_design.py \n\nstage5_data_model.py \n\nstage6_arch_validation.py \n\nstage7_export.py \n\nofficial_docs_retrieval.py \n\ndebate_mode.py \n\nlearning_emit.py \n\nutils_io.py \n\n \n\nreferences/ \n\nTEMPLATES_INDEX.md \n\nEC0249_mapping.md \n\nVF_functional_design_mapping.md \n\nFitGap_mapping.md \n\nDataModel_mapping.md \n\nSalesforce_official_whitelist.md \n\npattern_keys.md \n\n \n\nexamples/ \n\nexample_minimum_inputs.md \n\nexample_with_transcript.md \n\nexample_with_scope_fitgap.md \n\nexample_end_to_end.md \n\n``` \n\n \n\nImportant: \n\n \n\nThe **skill references folder is NOT the template source**. \n\n \n\nIt only documents how to use files located in: \n\n \n\n``` \n\n<workspace>/references/ \n\n``` \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Runtime Project Structure \n\n \n\nWhen executing the skill a new project folder must be created: \n\n \n\n``` \n\nworkspace/projects/<project_key>/ \n\n``` \n\n \n\nContaining: \n\n \n\n``` \n\ndiscovery/ \n\nDiscovery_Report.md \n\nDiscovery_Process_Analysis.md \n\nDiscovery_QA.xlsx \n\n \n\nfit_gap/ \n\nFit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx \n\n \n\ndesign/ \n\nFunctional_Design.docx \n\n \n\ndata_model/ \n\nData_Model.xlsx \n\n \n\narchitecture/ \n\nArchitecture_Overview.md \n\n \n\nevidence/ \n\nEvidence_Log.md \n\n \n\nREADME.md \n\n``` \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Pipeline Stages \n\n \n\n## Stage 0 — Intake Gate \n\n \n\nMandatory inputs: \n\n \n\n• project name \n\n• industry \n\n• country \n\n• Salesforce clouds licensed \n\n• approximate user count \n\n• process description or transcript \n\n• implementation scope or proposal \n\n \n\nIf missing → block pipeline and generate discovery questions. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Stage 1 — Discovery (EC0249) \n\n \n\nInputs may include: \n\n \n\n• meeting transcripts \n\n• discovery notes \n\n• process descriptions \n\n• SOW documents \n\n \n\nExtract: \n\n \n\n• actors \n\n• processes \n\n• events \n\n• systems \n\n• unknowns \n\n \n\nOutputs: \n\n \n\nDiscovery_Report.md \n\nDiscovery_Process_Analysis.md \n\nDiscovery_QA.xlsx \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Stage 2 — Requirements Consolidation \n\n \n\nTransform discovery into structured requirements: \n\n \n\n• requirement ID \n\n• process \n\n• actor \n\n• description \n\n• trigger \n\n• acceptance criteria \n\n \n\nIntegrations must **not be assumed**. \n\n \n\nSolutions may be: \n\n \n\n• Salesforce standalone \n\n• Salesforce + ERP \n\n• Salesforce + middleware \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Stage 3 — FIT / GAP \n\n \n\nFIT = requested + in project scope \n\nGAP = requested + not in project scope \n\n \n\nBefore classification the skill must request: \n\n \n\n• SOW \n\n• proposal \n\n• implementation scope \n\n \n\nOutput: \n\n \n\nFit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx \n\n \n\nColumns: \n\n \n\nReqID \n\nProcess \n\nRequirement \n\nFit/GAP \n\nJustification \n\nTime impact \n\nCost impact \n\nImplementation type \n\nLicense dependency \n\nRisk \n\nEvidence link \n\nStatus \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Stage 4 — Functional Design \n\n \n\nThe structure MUST follow: \n\n \n\n``` \n\n<workspace>/references/_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf \n\n``` \n\n \n\nGenerate: \n\n \n\nFunctional_Design.docx \n\n \n\nSections include: \n\n \n\n• Introduction \n\n• Scope \n\n• Business process algorithms \n\n• System interactions \n\n• Object model \n\n• Automations \n\n• Security \n\n• Reporting \n\n• Risks \n\n \n\nBefore finalizing architecture the skill must enter **Debate Mode**. \n\n \n\nDebate Mode presents 2–3 architecture alternatives with: \n\n \n\n• pros / cons \n\n• licensing impact \n\n• documentation evidence \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Stage 5 — Data Model \n\n \n\nStructure must follow: \n\n \n\n``` \n\n<workspace>/references/Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf \n\n``` \n\n \n\nGenerate: \n\n \n\nData_Model.xlsx \n\n \n\nTabs per object. \n\n \n\nEach object must include: \n\n \n\n• fields \n\n• types \n\n• required flags \n\n• relationships \n\n• record types \n\n• validations \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Stage 6 — Architecture Validation \n\n \n\nValidate architecture against: \n\n \n\n• licensing constraints \n\n• Salesforce limits \n\n• security best practices \n\n• scalability \n\n \n\nProduce: \n\n \n\nArchitecture_Overview.md \n\nEvidence_Log.md \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Stage 7 — Export \n\n \n\nUse: \n\n \n\n• python-docx for Word \n\n• openpyxl for Excel \n\n \n\nExport: \n\n \n\nDiscovery_Report.md \n\nDiscovery_QA.xlsx \n\nDiscovery_Process_Analysis.md \n\nFit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx \n\nFunctional_Design.docx \n\nData_Model.xlsx \n\nArchitecture_Overview.md \n\nEvidence_Log.md \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Learning System Integration \n\n \n\nIf blocking conditions occur append incidents to: \n\n \n\n``` \n\nworkspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md \n\n``` \n\n \n\nExample pattern keys: \n\n \n\ndiscovery|MISSING|nonnegotiable|scope|blocked \n\nevidence|MISSING|salesforce_official|feature_unverified|blocked \n\nfitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify|blocked \n\nlicensing|CONFLICT|feature_requires_license|not_available|alternate_needed \n\n \n\nThen trigger learning‑loop fallback. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Multi‑Agent Mode \n\n \n\nThe skill must support optional architecture sub‑agents: \n\n \n\nSalesCloudArchitect \n\nServiceCloudArchitect \n\nFieldServiceArchitect \n\nDataCloudArchitect \n\nExperienceArchitect \n\nOmniStudioArchitect \n\nAgentforceArchitect \n\nSecurityArchitect \n\n \n\nrun_pipeline.py must allow: \n\n \n\n``` \n\n--mode single \n\n--mode multi \n\n``` \n\n \n\nAll long‑running agents must register with **agent‑watchdog**. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Required Demo Execution \n\n \n\nThe sub-agent must run a demo project: \n\n \n\n``` \n\nproject_key = demo_salesforce_architect \n\n``` \n\n \n\nExpected behavior: \n\n \n\n1. Generate discovery outputs \n\n2. Block FIT/GAP if scope missing \n\n3. Emit learning incident \n\n4. Trigger learning loop fallback \n\n5. Generate Word and Excel artifacts \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Final Output From Sub‑Agent \n\n \n\nThe delegated agent must return a **Handoff Report** containing: \n\n \n\n• outcome (success / partial / failure) \n\n• incidents generated \n\n• files created \n\n• commands to run the skill \n\n• location of generated demo artifacts"}],"timestamp":1772751223605}}
