{"type":"message","id":"215a9751","parentId":"635f766f","timestamp":"2026-03-05T22:54:43.057Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Los archivos existen. Ahora debo spawnear un sub-agent con la tarea. Usaré runtime=\"subagent\", agentId=\"main\", label=\"salesforce-architect-creator\". Incluiré todas las especificaciones, enfatizando que debe leer los documentos de referencia como READ-ONLY, consultarlos antes de generar artefactos, y detenerse si no los encuentra.\n\nTambién debo recordar que el sub-agent debe terminar con Handoff Report. Voy a preparar el mensaje.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Y2SJyvBSblQfk4Lu4X5jmmHZ","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"Create a production-ready OpenClaw skill \"salesforce-architect\" in the workspace under /skills/ with comprehensive Salesforce architecture capabilities.\n\n## CRITICAL RULE — USE WORKSPACE REFERENCES\nThe workspace already contains official reference documents in:\n<workspace>/references/\nThese documents are NOT to be recreated or rewritten. They must be read and used as READ‑ONLY knowledge sources for generating outputs.\n\nThe skill must explicitly read and consult:\n<workspace>/references/_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf\n<workspace>/references/IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf\n<workspace>/references/IDEINCA - Documento Funcional V1NoGAPs.pdf\n<workspace>/references/Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf\n\nPurpose of each file:\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| _F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf | Defines structure of Functional Design document |\n| IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf | Defines structure and fields of FIT/GAP matrix |\n| IDEINCA - Documento Funcional V1NoGAPs.pdf | Example of completed functional design |\n| Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf | Example data model structure |\n\nIf the documents are not found, the skill must:\n1. Stop execution\n2. Emit an incident\n3. Ask the user to confirm the references location\n\n## Core Objective\nCreate a skill capable of:\n• analyzing complex business processes\n• extracting requirements from discovery conversations or transcripts\n• producing Salesforce architecture decisions\n• generating FIT/GAP analysis\n• producing Functional Design documentation\n• generating Salesforce data models\n• validating architecture using official Salesforce documentation only\n\n## Salesforce Documentation Evidence Policy\nAllowed domains:\n- help.salesforce.com\n- developer.salesforce.com\n- architect.salesforce.com\n- trailhead.salesforce.com\n\nEvery architecture decision must include a reference link.\nIf evidence cannot be found:\n• mark the decision UNVERIFIED\n• request clarification from the user\n• do not finalize the design\n\n## Clouds That Must Be Supported\n- Sales Cloud\n- Service Cloud\n- Field Service\n- Financial Services Cloud\n- Data Cloud\n- Agentforce\n- OmniStudio\n- Digital Engagement\n- Experience Cloud\n\nThe skill must also evaluate licensing constraints before recommending features.\nExample rule: If Field Service licenses are unavailable → propose custom visit management solution instead of FSL.\n\n## Skill Directory Structure REQUIRED\nskills/salesforce-architect/\n  SKILL.md\n  scripts/\n    run_pipeline.py\n    stage1_discovery.py\n    stage2_requirements.py\n    stage3_fit_gap.py\n    stage4_functional_design.py\n    stage5_data_model.py\n    stage6_arch_validation.py\n    stage7_export.py\n    official_docs_retrieval.py\n    debate_mode.py\n    learning_emit.py\n    utils_io.py\n  references/\n    TEMPLATES_INDEX.md\n    EC0249_mapping.md\n    VF_functional_design_mapping.md\n    FitGap_mapping.md\n    DataModel_mapping.md\n    Salesforce_official_whitelist.md\n    pattern_keys.md\n  examples/\n    example_minimum_inputs.md\n    example_with_transcript.md\n    example_with_scope_fitgap.md\n    example_end_to_end.md\n\n## Runtime Project Structure\nWhen executing the skill a new project folder must be created:\nworkspace/projects/<project_key>/\nContaining:\ndiscovery/\n  Discovery_Report.md\n  Discovery_Process_Analysis.md\n  Discovery_QA.xlsx\nfit_gap/\n  Fit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx\ndesign/\n  Functional_Design.docx\ndata_model/\n  Data_Model.xlsx\narchitecture/\n  Architecture_Overview.md\nevidence/\n  Evidence_Log.md\nREADME.md\n\n## Pipeline Stages\nStage 0 — Intake Gate: Mandatory inputs (project name, industry, country, Salesforce clouds licensed, user count, process description, implementation scope). If missing → block pipeline and generate discovery questions.\n\nStage 1 — Discovery (EC0249): Extract actors, processes, events, systems, unknowns from transcripts/notes/SOW. Outputs: Discovery_Report.md, Discovery_Process_Analysis.md, Discovery_QA.xlsx.\n\nStage 2 — Requirements Consolidation: Transform discovery into structured requirements (ID, process, actor, description, trigger, acceptance criteria). Integrations must not be assumed.\n\nStage 3 — FIT / GAP: FIT = requested + in project scope, GAP = requested + not in project scope. Must request SOW/proposal/scope before classification. Output: Fit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx with columns: ReqID, Process, Requirement, Fit/GAP, Justification, Time impact, Cost impact, Implementation type, License dependency, Risk, Evidence link, Status.\n\nStage 4 — Functional Design: Structure MUST follow <workspace>/references/_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf. Generate Functional_Design.docx. Sections: Introduction, Scope, Business process algorithms, System interactions, Object model, Automations, Security, Reporting, Risks. Before finalizing architecture, enter Debate Mode presenting 2–3 architecture alternatives with pros/cons, licensing impact, documentation evidence.\n\nStage 5 — Data Model: Structure must follow <workspace>/references/Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf. Generate Data_Model.xlsx with tabs per object. Each object must include fields, types, required flags, relationships, record types, validations.\n\nStage 6 — Architecture Validation: Validate against licensing constraints, Salesforce limits, security best practices, scalability. Produce Architecture_Overview.md, Evidence_Log.md.\n\nStage 7 — Export: Use python-docx for Word, openpyxl for Excel. Export all artifacts.\n\n## Learning System Integration\nIf blocking conditions occur append incidents to workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md.\nExample pattern keys:\n- discovery|MISSING|nonnegotiable|scope|blocked\n- evidence|MISSING|salesforce_official|feature_unverified|blocked\n- fitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify|blocked\n- licensing|CONFLICT|feature_requires_license|not_available|alternate_needed\nThen trigger learning‑loop fallback.\n\n## Multi‑Agent Mode\nThe skill must support optional architecture sub‑agents:\nSalesCloudArchitect, ServiceCloudArchitect, FieldServiceArchitect, DataCloudArchitect, ExperienceArchitect, OmniStudioArchitect, AgentforceArchitect, SecurityArchitect.\n\nrun_pipeline.py must allow:\n--mode single\n--mode multi\n\nAll long‑running agents must register with agent‑watchdog.\n\n## Required Demo Execution\nThe sub-agent must run a demo project:\nproject_key = demo_salesforce_architect\n\nExpected behavior:\n1. Generate discovery outputs\n2. Block FIT/GAP if scope missing\n3. Emit learning incident\n4. Trigger learning loop fallback\n5. Generate Word and Excel artifacts\n\n## Delivery Requirements\n- MUST write files to disk in the workspace\n- MUST read and consult the reference PDFs before generating any output artifacts\n- MUST implement all pipeline stages with production-ready Python code\n- MUST include learning system integration (incident emission + learning loop trigger)\n- MUST provide a short validation run (dry-run) demonstrating the scripts work\n- MUST end with Handoff Report including: Outcome + Incidents + Files created/changed + commands to run the skill + location of generated demo artifacts\n\n## Handoff Report Format\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**: list or \"none\"\n- **Files touched**: list of files created/changed\n- **Next action**: 1-line suggestion\n- **Watchdog fields**: session_id, run_id, last_activity_at, progress_marker\n\nSTART WORK NOW. Read the reference PDFs first, then implement the skill.","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"main","label":"salesforce-architect-creator"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":311,"output":2027,"cacheRead":86976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89314,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772751236751}}
