{"type":"message","id":"e928d684","parentId":"97be9a70","timestamp":"2026-03-05T23:29:36.650Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_YWnCDCaHQ2sfv8O0kdTaImBQ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n### Stage 0 – Intake Gate\n**Mandatory inputs** (block pipeline if missing):\n- Project name\n- Industry\n- Country\n- Salesforce clouds licensed\n- User count\n- Process description\n- Implementation scope\n\nIf any mandatory input is missing, generate discovery questions and stop.\n\n### Stage 1 – Discovery (EC0249)\nExtract actors, processes, events, systems, unknowns from transcripts/notes/SOW.\n**Outputs:**\n- `Discovery_Report.md`\n- `Discovery_Process_Analysis.md`\n- `Discovery_QA.xlsx`\n\n### Stage 2 – Requirements Consolidation\nTransform discovery into structured requirements with:\n- ID\n- Process\n- Actor\n- Description\n- Trigger\n- Acceptance criteria\n\nIntegrations must not be assumed.\n\n### Stage 3 – FIT / GAP Analysis\nFIT = requested + in project scope, GAP = requested + not in project scope.\nMust request SOW/proposal/scope before classification.\n**Output:** `Fit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx` with columns:\n- ReqID\n- Process\n- Requirement\n- Fit/GAP\n- Justification\n- Time impact\n- Cost impact\n- Implementation type\n- License dependency\n- Risk\n- Evidence link\n- Status\n\n### Stage 4 – Functional Design\nStructure MUST follow `<workspace>/references/_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf`.\nGenerate `Functional_Design.docx` with sections:\n- Introduction\n- Scope\n- Business process algorithms\n- System interactions\n- Object model\n- Automations\n- Security\n- Reporting\n- Risks\n\nBefore finalizing architecture, enter **Debate Mode** presenting 2–3 architecture alternatives with pros/cons, licensing impact, documentation evidence.\n\n### Stage 5 – Data Model\nStructure must follow `<workspace>/references/Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf`.\nGenerate `Data_Model.xlsx` with tabs per object. Each object must include:\n- Fields, types, required flags\n- Relationships\n- Record types\n- Validations\n\n### Stage 6 – Architecture Validation\nValidate against licensing constraints, Salesforce limits, security best practices, scalability.\n**Outputs:**\n- `Architecture_Overview.md`\n- `Evidence_Log.md`\n\n### Stage 7 – Export\nUse `python-docx` for Word, `openpyxl` for Excel. Export all artifacts.\n\n## Learning System Integration\nIf blocking conditions occur, append incidents to `workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\nExample pattern keys:\n- `discovery|MISSING|nonnegotiable|scope|blocked`\n- `evidence|MISSING|salesforce_official|feature_unverified|blocked`\n- `fitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify|blocked`\n- `licensing|CONFLICT|feature_requires_license|not_available|alternate_needed`\n\nThen trigger learning‑loop fallback.\n\n## Multi‑Agent Mode\nThe skill supports optional architecture sub‑agents:\n- SalesCloudArchitect\n- ServiceCloudArchitect\n- FieldServiceArchitect\n- DataCloudArchitect\n- ExperienceArchitect\n- OmniStudioArchitect\n- AgentforceArchitect\n- SecurityArchitect\n\n[50 more lines in file. Use offset=200 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772753376610}}
