{"type":"message","id":"1ff31081","parentId":"a17b6857","timestamp":"2026-03-05T23:34:14.848Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 18:24 EST] You are the MAIN agent. Do NOT create a new skill. \n\n \n\nObjective: \n\nUpdate the existing skill at: \n\n<workspace>/skills/salesforce-architect \n\nto properly implement EC0249 as a methodology (not a label), using the official EC0249 PDF that the user will place in: \n\n<workspace>/references/EC0249.pdf (or similarly named EC0249*.pdf) \n\n \n\nCritical clarification: \n\nEC0249 is a formal consulting/process methodology standard. The skill must treat it as the governing framework for Stage 1 (Discovery) and must explicitly read the EC0249 reference from <workspace>/references/. \n\n \n\nRequired changes (surgical, production-ready, minimal churn): \n\n \n\n1) Reference enforcement (Stage 1 Gate) \n\n- In stage1_discovery.py (and/or run_pipeline.py preflight), add a check that: \n\n - Finds EC0249 PDF in <workspace>/references/ by filename match: EC0249*.pdf \n\n - If missing: BLOCK Stage 1 and emit incident to .learnings/ERRORS.md with pattern key: \n\n discovery|MISSING|reference|EC0249|blocked \n\n - Write a clear message in Discovery_Report.md: \"EC0249 reference missing — cannot execute methodology-based discovery.\" \n\n \n\n2) EC0249 method mapping (explicit, not generic) \n\n- Create/Update: skills/salesforce-architect/references/EC0249_mapping.md \n\n Include: \n\n - a short definition: \"EC0249 is a methodology/standard for consulting process discovery and requirements elicitation.\" \n\n - a Stage 1 structured flow that mirrors EC0249 intent: \n\n - Context capture \n\n - Stakeholder/roles \n\n - Current-state process (AS-IS) \n\n - Pain points \n\n - Business rules \n\n - Exceptions/variants \n\n - Data inputs/outputs \n\n - Non-functional constraints \n\n - Open questions & validation \n\n - Map each section to the artifacts we generate: \n\n - Discovery_Report.md sections \n\n - Discovery_QA.xlsx columns \n\n - Discovery_Process_Analysis.md structure \n\n \n\n3) Stage 1 outputs must explicitly state “EC0249 applied” \n\n- Update stage1_discovery.py so Discovery_Report.md begins with: \n\n - \"Discovery executed under EC0249 methodology\" \n\n - Reference path used: <workspace>/references/<EC0249 file> \n\n - Timestamp + project_key \n\n \n\n4) Discovery_QA.xlsx must reflect EC0249 discipline \n\n- Ensure Discovery_QA.xlsx includes columns: \n\n - Question_ID \n\n - EC0249_Category (e.g., Scope, Actors, AS-IS, Rules, Exceptions, Data, NFR, Risks) \n\n - Question \n\n - Answer \n\n - Status (open/answered/validated) \n\n - Source (transcript/user/doc) \n\n - Evidence_needed (yes/no) \n\n - Notes \n\n \n\n5) Transcript ingestion alignment \n\n- If transcripts are provided, ensure extraction writes: \n\n - Source tags per finding (line/time if available) \n\n - Ambiguities -> open questions categorized by EC0249_Category \n\n \n\n6) Update SKILL.md (only the relevant parts) \n\n- In SKILL.md: \n\n - Add a short note in Stage 1 explaining EC0249 is a methodology and the skill enforces using the EC0249 PDF in workspace references. \n\n - Add the preflight requirement: EC0249 PDF must exist in <workspace>/references/. \n\n \n\n7) Validate quickly \n\n- Run the demo once: \n\n - Case A: EC0249 missing -> must block + incident emitted + Discovery_Report explains block. \n\n - Case B: EC0249 present -> Stage 1 runs and outputs show \"EC0249 applied\" + QA file has EC0249_Category. \n\n \n\nReturn: \n\n- A Handoff Report with: \n\n - Outcome \n\n - Files changed (exact list) \n\n - Demo commands run \n\n - Evidence: show the first ~15 lines of generated Discovery_Report.md for Case B and the incident block header for Case A."}],"timestamp":1772753654825}}
