{"type":"message","id":"09946aad","parentId":"2243cd61","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:08:02.515Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-05 19:08 EST] # Prompt for MAIN Agent \n\n## Task: Build New Skill — `salesforce-code-auditor` \n\n \n\nYou are the **MAIN orchestration agent**. \n\n \n\nYour task is to **spawn a new independent sub-agent session** and delegate the construction of a new skill called: \n\n \n\n`skills/salesforce-code-auditor` \n\n \n\nThis skill must support **progressive technical analysis of Salesforce codebases** (Apex, LWC, Visualforce, Triggers, Flows, Metadata). \n\n \n\nThe goal is **token‑efficient auditing** where the agent requests **only the minimal necessary code** to reconstruct the real execution logic of a process. \n\n \n\nThis skill must be designed to **work together with the previously created `salesforce-architect` skill**. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Core Objective \n\n \n\nThe skill must allow agents to: \n\n \n\n• analyze Salesforce code progressively \n\n• reconstruct execution flow from UI → controller → services → triggers → integrations \n\n• avoid loading entire repositories into context \n\n• request specific files when needed \n\n• generate structured technical audit documentation \n\n• detect architecture, security, and governor-limit risks \n\n \n\nThe skill must operate **incrementally and interactively** to minimize token usage. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Workspace Code Intake Model \n\n \n\nThe skill must require the user to place code inside a case folder created by the skill. \n\n \n\nDirectory created automatically: \n\n \n\n<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/inputs/ \n\n \n\nUsers will place source files there. \n\n \n\nSupported formats: \n\n \n\n• Apex `.cls` \n\n• Apex Triggers `.trigger` \n\n• LWC `.js`, `.html`, `.xml` \n\n• Visualforce `.page` \n\n• Metadata `.xml` \n\n• Flow metadata \n\n• DTO / integration classes \n\n \n\nThe skill must **index files first instead of reading them immediately**. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Required Runtime Structure \n\n \n\n<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/ \n\nCASE.md \n\ninputs/ \n\nwork/ \n\nsnippets/ \n\ntemp_analysis/ \n\noutputs/ \n\nINDEX.md \n\nMANIFEST.json \n\nDEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json \n\nENTRYPOINTS.json \n\nEXECUTION_TRACE.md \n\nFINDINGS.md \n\nTEST_MATRIX.md \n\nAUDIT_REPORT.md \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Skill Directory Structure \n\n \n\nskills/salesforce-code-auditor/ \n\nSKILL.md \n\nscripts/ \n\ninit_case.py \n\nindex_inputs.py \n\ndetect_entrypoints.py \n\nbuild_dependency_graph.py \n\nextract_snippets.py \n\ngenerate_reports.py \n\nutils_fs.py \n\nreferences/ \n\nFILE_TYPES.md \n\nREVIEW_CHECKLISTS.md \n\nTOKEN_STRATEGY.md \n\nREPORT_TEMPLATE.md \n\nexamples/ \n\nexample_intake.md \n\nexample_manifest.md \n\nexample_audit_report.md \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Analysis Methodology \n\n \n\nThe skill must reconstruct system behavior in the following order: \n\n \n\n1 — UI Layer \n\n \n\nIdentify entry points: \n\n• Visualforce pages \n\n• Lightning Web Components \n\n• Aura Components \n\n• Flow Screens \n\n \n\nDetect: \n\n• buttons \n\n• actions \n\n• Apex calls \n\n• events \n\n \n\n2 — Controller Layer \n\n \n\nAnalyze controller classes called by the UI. \n\n \n\nDetect: \n\n• invoked methods \n\n• validations \n\n• business logic \n\n• SOQL queries \n\n• DML operations \n\n \n\n3 — Auxiliary Classes \n\n \n\nTrace additional classes used by controllers such as service classes, utility classes, validators and parsers. \n\n \n\n4 — Integration and DTO Layer \n\n \n\nIdentify classes responsible for: \n\n• callouts \n\n• response parsing \n\n• external API integrations \n\n• DTO transport objects \n\n \n\n5 — Triggers \n\n \n\nDetect triggers related to objects used by the process. \n\n \n\nAnalyze: \n\n• trigger context events \n\n• automation side effects \n\n• recursive logic risks \n\n \n\n6 — Metadata and Automation \n\n \n\nDetect: \n\n• flows \n\n• process builders \n\n• platform events \n\n• async logic \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Token Optimization Strategy \n\n \n\nThe skill must **never load all code simultaneously**. \n\n \n\nInstead it must: \n\n \n\n1. Index files using `index_inputs.py` \n\n2. Detect entrypoints \n\n3. Request specific files or snippets \n\n4. Extract only required methods using `extract_snippets.py` \n\n \n\nThe analysis must proceed **incrementally**. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# SFDX Support \n\n \n\nThe skill must support both: \n\n \n\nOption A — SFDX structure: \n\nforce-app/main/default/ \n\n \n\nOption B — loose files in inputs/ \n\n \n\nThe indexing script must detect both. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Dependency Reconstruction \n\n \n\n`build_dependency_graph.py` must generate: \n\n \n\nDEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json \n\n \n\nContaining: \n\n• class dependencies \n\n• method calls \n\n• trigger relationships \n\n• integration flows \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Execution Trace \n\n \n\nGenerate: \n\n \n\nEXECUTION_TRACE.md \n\n \n\nDescribing runtime order: \n\nUI → Controller → Services → Integrations → Triggers \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Audit Findings \n\n \n\nFINDINGS.md must identify: \n\n \n\n• governor limit risks \n\n• SOQL in loops \n\n• missing FLS checks \n\n• mixed responsibilities \n\n• weak error handling \n\n• security vulnerabilities \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Testing Matrix \n\n \n\nGenerate: \n\n \n\nTEST_MATRIX.md \n\n \n\nContaining: \n\n \n\n• scenario \n\n• trigger action \n\n• expected system behavior \n\n• related code location \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Final Audit Report \n\n \n\nAUDIT_REPORT.md must include: \n\n \n\nSummary \n\nArchitecture Observations \n\nTechnical Risks \n\nPerformance Risks \n\nSecurity Risks \n\nRefactor Opportunities \n\nDesign Alignment \n\n \n\nThe last section must compare the real code behaviour against outputs produced by the **salesforce-architect skill** when available. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Integration with Learning System \n\n \n\nIf critical issues are detected append incidents to: \n\n \n\nworkspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md \n\n \n\nExample pattern keys: \n\n \n\nsecurity|FLS_MISSING|apex \n\nlimits|SOQL_IN_LOOP|apex \n\narchitecture|MIXED_CONCERNS|controller \n\nintegration|UNHANDLED_CALLOUT_FAILURE \n\n \n\nThen trigger: \n\n \n\nerror-learning-loop index rebuild fallback. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Demonstration Test \n\n \n\nThe sub-agent must run a demo case: \n\n \n\ndemo_code_audit \n\n \n\nThe test must: \n\n \n\n1. Create case folder \n\n2. Simulate input files \n\n3. Generate INDEX.md \n\n4. Build dependency graph \n\n5. Produce audit report \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Final Output From Sub-Agent \n\n \n\nReturn a **Handoff Report** containing: \n\n \n\n• outcome (success / partial / failure) \n\n• incidents generated \n\n• files created \n\n• commands required to run the skill \n\n• location of demo outputs"}],"timestamp":1772755682492}}
{"type":"message","id":"c89d15a7","parentId":"09946aad","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:08:33.647Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"El usuario me pide crear un nuevo skill: `salesforce-code-auditor`. Es un skill de auditoría de código Salesforce, complementario al skill `salesforce-architect` ya creado. Debo spawnear un sub‑agente para construirlo.\n\nPrimero, revisaré el workspace actual para verificar que no haya conflictos. Luego, prepararé la especificación completa para el sub‑agente, basándome en el prompt detallado del usuario. El skill debe ser capaz de analizar código Salesforce de manera progresiva, eficiente en tokens, y generar documentación estructurada de auditoría.\n\nEl sub‑agente debe crear la estructura de directorios, scripts Python, referencias, ejemplos, y ejecutar un demo. También debe integrarse con el sistema de learning (incidentes, error-learning-loop).\n\nVoy a spawnear el sub‑agente con la tarea detallada. Necesito incluir todos los requisitos: metodología de análisis progresivo, estructura de directorios, estrategia de optimización de tokens, integración con learning system, y demo.\n\nPrimero, verificaré que no exista ya el skill `salesforce-code-auditor`. Luego, lanzaré el sub‑agente. Usaré `sessions_spawn` con `runtime=\"subagent\"`, `agentId=\"main\"`, y un label descriptivo. La tarea debe ser la especificación completa.\n\nProcedamos.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_acH78CSgCyiwuu8qw8aVo9qT","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"salesforce-code\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":108144,"output":693,"cacheRead":2752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111589,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772755682508}}
