{"type":"message","id":"43163d00","parentId":"6db0231c","timestamp":"2026-03-06T00:09:21.456Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No existe el skill todavía. Bien. Ahora preparo la tarea para el sub‑agente. Voy a construir un prompt detallado que incluya todos los requisitos del usuario, manteniendo el formato de especificaciones técnicas. Aseguraré de que el sub‑agente entienda que debe construir un skill completo y ejecutar un demo.\n\nTambién debo recordar incluir el requisito de Handoff Report al final. Usaré el mismo formato que en tareas anteriores.\n\nVoy a spawnear el sub‑agente.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ttf1Ci5IiWvGALOf9UWn1aW3","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"Create a production-ready OpenClaw skill \"salesforce-code-auditor\" in the workspace under /skills/ with comprehensive Salesforce code auditing capabilities.\n\n## Core Objective\nThe skill must support **progressive technical analysis of Salesforce codebases** (Apex, LWC, Visualforce, Triggers, Flows, Metadata) with **token‑efficient auditing** where the agent requests **only the minimal necessary code** to reconstruct the real execution logic of a process.\n\nThe skill must be designed to **work together with the previously created `salesforce‑architect` skill**.\n\n## Workspace Code Intake Model\nThe skill must require the user to place code inside a case folder created by the skill.\n\nDirectory created automatically:\n<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/inputs/\n\nUsers will place source files there.\n\nSupported formats:\n• Apex `.cls`\n• Apex Triggers `.trigger`\n• LWC `.js`, `.html`, `.xml`\n• Visualforce `.page`\n• Metadata `.xml`\n• Flow metadata\n• DTO / integration classes\n\nThe skill must **index files first instead of reading them immediately**.\n\n## Required Runtime Structure\n<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/\n  CASE.md\n  inputs/\n  work/\n  snippets/\n  temp_analysis/\n  outputs/\n  INDEX.md\n  MANIFEST.json\n  DEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json\n  ENTRYPOINTS.json\n  EXECUTION_TRACE.md\n  FINDINGS.md\n  TEST_MATRIX.md\n  AUDIT_REPORT.md\n\n## Skill Directory Structure REQUIRED\nskills/salesforce-code-auditor/\n  SKILL.md\n  scripts/\n    init_case.py\n    index_inputs.py\n    detect_entrypoints.py\n    build_dependency_graph.py\n    extract_snippets.py\n    generate_reports.py\n    utils_fs.py\n  references/\n    FILE_TYPES.md\n    REVIEW_CHECKLISTS.md\n    TOKEN_STRATEGY.md\n    REPORT_TEMPLATE.md\n  examples/\n    example_intake.md\n    example_manifest.md\n    example_audit_report.md\n\n## Analysis Methodology\nThe skill must reconstruct system behavior in the following order:\n\n1 — UI Layer\n  Identify entry points: Visualforce pages, Lightning Web Components, Aura Components, Flow Screens\n  Detect: buttons, actions, Apex calls, events\n\n2 — Controller Layer\n  Analyze controller classes called by the UI.\n  Detect: invoked methods, validations, business logic, SOQL queries, DML operations\n\n3 — Auxiliary Classes\n  Trace additional classes used by controllers: service classes, utility classes, validators, parsers\n\n4 — Integration and DTO Layer\n  Identify classes responsible for: callouts, response parsing, external API integrations, DTO transport objects\n\n5 — Triggers\n  Detect triggers related to objects used by the process.\n  Analyze: trigger context events, automation side effects, recursive logic risks\n\n6 — Metadata and Automation\n  Detect: flows, process builders, platform events, async logic\n\n## Token Optimization Strategy\nThe skill must **never load all code simultaneously**.\n\nInstead it must:\n1. Index files using `index_inputs.py`\n2. Detect entrypoints\n3. Request specific files or snippets\n4. Extract only required methods using `extract_snippets.py`\n\nThe analysis must proceed **incrementally**.\n\n## SFDX Support\nThe skill must support both:\nOption A — SFDX structure: force-app/main/default/\nOption B — loose files in inputs/\n\nThe indexing script must detect both.\n\n## Dependency Reconstruction\n`build_dependency_graph.py` must generate DEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json containing:\n• class dependencies\n• method calls\n• trigger relationships\n• integration flows\n\n## Execution Trace\nGenerate EXECUTION_TRACE.md describing runtime order:\nUI → Controller → Services → Integrations → Triggers\n\n## Audit Findings\nFINDINGS.md must identify:\n• governor limit risks\n• SOQL in loops\n• missing FLS checks\n• mixed responsibilities\n• weak error handling\n• security vulnerabilities\n\n## Testing Matrix\nGenerate TEST_MATRIX.md containing:\n• scenario\n• trigger action\n• expected system behavior\n• related code location\n\n## Final Audit Report\nAUDIT_REPORT.md must include:\nSummary\nArchitecture Observations\nTechnical Risks\nPerformance Risks\nSecurity Risks\nRefactor Opportunities\nDesign Alignment\n\nThe last section must compare the real code behaviour against outputs produced by the **salesforce‑architect skill** when available.\n\n## Integration with Learning System\nIf critical issues are detected append incidents to workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md\n\nExample pattern keys:\n• security|FLS_MISSING|apex\n• limits|SOQL_IN_LOOP|apex\n• architecture|MIXED_CONCERNS|controller\n• integration|UNHANDLED_CALLOUT_FAILURE\n\nThen trigger error‑learning‑loop index rebuild fallback.\n\n## Demonstration Test\nThe sub‑agent must run a demo case: `demo_code_audit`\n\nThe test must:\n1. Create case folder\n2. Simulate input files\n3. Generate INDEX.md\n4. Build dependency graph\n5. Produce audit report\n\n## Delivery Requirements\n- MUST write files to disk in the workspace\n- MUST implement progressive token‑efficient analysis (index first, load snippets as needed)\n- MUST generate all required runtime artifacts (INDEX.md, MANIFEST.json, DEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json, ENTRYPOINTS.json, EXECUTION_TRACE.md, FINDINGS.md, TEST_MATRIX.md, AUDIT_REPORT.md)\n- MUST include learning system integration (incident emission + learning loop trigger)\n- MUST provide a short validation run (dry‑run) demonstrating the scripts work\n- MUST end with Handoff Report including: Outcome + Incidents + Files created/changed + commands to run the skill + location of generated demo artifacts\n\n## Handoff Report Format\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**: list or \"none\"\n- **Files touched**: list of files created/changed\n- **Next action**: 1-line suggestion\n- **Watchdog fields**: session_id, run_id, last_activity_at, progress_marker\n\nSTART WORK NOW. Build the skill with production‑ready Python code.","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"main","label":"salesforce-code-auditor-creator"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":457,"output":1664,"cacheRead":110848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112969,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772755713722}}
